ngtime friend, Philippe Meylan. Gallay provided through his sailing experience, knowledge of yachts and full-time involvement, while Meylan provided legal background and worked as a trusted adviser. In 1996, after two years of operation, BGYB became a member of the Mediterranean Yacht Brokerage Association (MYBA).<ref>[http://www.myba-association.com/pages/members.cfm Official website MYBA (Mediterranean Yacht Broker Association)] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111121115950/http://www.myba-association.com/pages/members.cfm |date=21 November 2011 }}</ref>, which includes the largest international brokerage companies in the world. Its contracts and practices have become the standard for the professional yachting industry. BGYB's reputation rose through the purchase, sale, chartering, and management of motor, sailing, and racing yachts. The boats sold range from 18 to 50 meters for budgets ranging from several hundred thousand to several million Euros.<ref>[http://www.superyachts.com/news/2011-mys:-bernard-gallay-discusses-his-passion-for-yacht-racing-1469.htm Vid\u00e9o de Bernard Gallay sur le Monaco Yacht Show par Superyachts.com]</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gallay, Bernard}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French sailors]]\n[[Category:Vend\u00e9e Globe finishers]]\n", "name_user": "HolyMakkirel", "label": "safe", "comment": "reformatted infobox", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bernard_Gallay"}
