{"title_page": "Toni Braxton", "text_new": "{{short description|American R&B singer-songwriter}}\n{{For|the singer's eponymous album|Toni Braxton (album)}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use American English|date=June 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Toni Braxton\n| image              = Toni Braxton press photo 2015.png\n| caption            = Braxton in 2015\n| birth_name         = Toni Michele Braxton<ref> https://books.google.com/books?id=ENoDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA166&lpg=PA166&dq=Toni+Michele+Braxton&source=bl&ots=4cMLhHF1f8&sig=ACfU3U0S6qUzS3c4cd4aD3YgEjYAn3VxUw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiJhMGkpMXnAhVMXq0KHdAPAaoQ6AEwFnoECAYQAQ#v=onepage&q=Toni%20Michele%20Braxton&f=false</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age  |1967|10|07}}\n| birth_place        = [[Severn, Maryland]], U.S.\n| occupation         = <!--Please do not add any more occupations to the list, it is long enough already-->{{hlist|Singer|songwriter|actress|record producer|television personality}}\n| years_active       = 1989\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Keri Lewis|2001|2013|reason=divorced}}\n| children           = 2\n| partner            = [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]] (fianc\u00e9)\n| relatives          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Traci Braxton]] (sister)\n* [[Trina Braxton]] (sister)\n* [[Towanda Braxton]] (sister)\n* [[Tamar Braxton]] (sister)\n}}\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Toni Braxton|Full list]]\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| instrument       = {{flat list |\n*Vocals \n*piano}}\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{flat list |\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=stevehuey/><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.thewrap.com/lifetime-casts-its-toni-braxton-for-biopic/ |work = [[TheWrap]] |date = October 6, 2015 |accessdate = September 1, 2016 |title = Lifetime Finds Its Toni Braxton for Biopic |first = Joe |last = Otterson }}</ref>\n*[[soul music|soul]]\n*[[hip hop soul]]\n*[[soft rock]]\n*[[dance music|dance]]\n*[[pop music|pop]]}}\n| label            = {{hlist|[[LaFace Records|LaFace]] <small>(1992-2001)</small>\n\n[[Arista Records|Arista]] <small>(2001-2003)</small>\n\n[[Universal Music Group|Universal]]/[[Blackground Records|Blackground]] <small>(2003-2006)</small>\n\n[[Edel Records|Edel]] <small>(2005-2006)</small>\n\n[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] <small>(2008-2010)</small>\n\n[[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]] <small>(2017-2018)</small>\n\n[[Island Records]] <small>(2020-Present)</small>}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[The Braxtons]]|[[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]]|[[Antonio \"L.A.\" Reid]]}}\n| website          = {{url|http://www.tonibraxton.com|ToniBraxton.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Toni Michele Braxton''' (born October 7, 1967) is an American singer, songwriter, pianist, record producer, actress, television personality, and philanthropist. Braxton has sold over 67 million records worldwide, including 41 million albums. She is one of the highest-selling female [[R&B]] artists in history. Braxton has won seven Grammy Awards, nine [[Billboard Music Awards]], seven [[American Music Awards]], and numerous other accolades. In 2011, Braxton was inducted into the [[Georgia Music Hall of Fame]].\n\nIn the late 1980s, Braxton began performing with her sisters in a music group known as [[The Braxtons]]; the group was signed to [[Arista Records]]. After attracting the attention of producers [[Antonio \"L.A.\" Reid]] and [[Kenneth \"Babyface\" Edmonds]] and being signed to [[LaFace Records]], Braxton released her [[Toni Braxton (album)|self-titled debut studio album]] in 1993. The album reached number one on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart and sold 10 million copies worldwide. In addition, the singles \"[[Another Sad Love Song]]\" and \"[[Breathe Again]]\" became international successes. The album brought Braxton three [[Grammy Awards]], including the Grammy for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]].\n\nBraxton experienced continued success with the albums ''[[Secrets (Toni Braxton album)|Secrets]]'' (1996), which included the U.S. #1 hit singles \"[[You're Makin' Me High]]/[[Let It Flow (song)|Let It Flow]]\" and \"[[Un-Break My Heart]]\"; and ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]'' (2000), which opened at #2 on the ''Billboard'' 200 and included the U.S. #2 hit single \"[[He Wasn't Man Enough]]\". Braxton's subsequent studio albums, ''[[More Than a Woman (album)|More Than a Woman]]'' (2002), ''[[Libra (Toni Braxton album)|Libra]]'' (2005) and ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]'' (2010), were released amid contractual disputes and health issues. In 2014, Braxton and longtime collaborator [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]] released a duet album entitled ''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' that earned the duo a Grammy Award for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Album|Best R&B Album]] in 2015. In 2018, Braxton released her ninth studio album, ''[[Sex & Cigarettes]]''.\n\nBraxton is also a television executive producer and personality. She competed in the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 7)|seventh season]] of the reality competition series ''[[Dancing with the Stars]]''. She has executive produced and starred in ''[[Braxton Family Values]]'', a reality television series that has aired on [[We TV]] since 2011. Braxton is also an executive producer of  ''[[Tamar & Vince]]'', a spinoff reality TV series starring her younger sister, Tamar.\n\n==Early life==\nToni Michelle Braxton was born in [[Severn, Maryland]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ollison|first1=Rashod D.|title=Toni Braxton's back, with a pretty 'Please'|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2005-09-25/news/0509270511_1_toni-braxton-libra-albums|accessdate=November 15, 2015|newspaper=[[The Baltimore Sun]]|date=September 25, 2005}}</ref> on October 7, 1967.<ref>{{cite news|last=Taylor|first=Derrick Bryson|title=Happy 45th Birthday, Toni Braxton!|url=http://www.essence.com/2012/10/07/happy-45th-birthday-toni-braxton|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]|date=October 7, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/07/toni-braxton-celebrates-46th-birthday-_n_1945819.html|title=PHOTOS: Toni Blows Out The Candles For Her 46th Birthday|date=October 7, 2012|website=The Huffington Post|access-date=June 30, 2016}}</ref> Her father, Michael Conrad Braxton Sr., was a [[Methodist]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adherents.com/largecom/fam_meth.html|title=Famous Methodists|website=Adherents.com|accessdate=November 12, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Jet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=I7sDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA21|accessdate=December 2, 2013|date=June 20, 1994|publisher=Johnson Publishing Company|page=21|issn=0021-5996}}</ref> clergyman and power company worker, and her mother, Evelyn Jackson, a native of [[South Carolina]], was a former opera singer and cosmetologist, as well as a pastor.<ref>{{cite news|last=Dougherty|first=Steve|title=Greener Pastures|url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20132603,00.html|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=October 9, 2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Braxton Family Values \u2013 Evelyn Braxton|url=http://www.wetv.com/shows/braxton-family-values/cast/evelyn-braxton|website=Wetv.com|accessdate=December 2, 2013}}</ref> Braxton's maternal grandfather was also a pastor.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ney|first=Angela Winter|title=Award-winning pastor reaches out to teen-agers|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/1994-02-06/news/1994037080_1_toni-braxton-inside-the-church-award|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=The Baltimore Sun|date=February 6, 1994}}</ref>\n\nBraxton is the eldest of six siblings.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Rizzo|first1=Monica|title=Toni Braxton: Still Dancing|journal=People|date=October 27, 2008|volume=70|issue=17|url= http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20238199,00.html|accessdate=November 15, 2015}}</ref> She has a younger brother Michael Jr. (born 1968) and four younger sisters [[Traci Braxton|Traci Renee]] (born 1971), [[Towanda Braxton|Towanda Chloe]] (born 1973), [[Trina Braxton|Trina Evette]] (born 1974), and [[Tamar Braxton|Tamar Estine]] (born 1977). They were raised in a strict religious household,<ref name=\"psu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.premiumseatsusa.com/concert/Toni-Braxton|title=Toni Braxton Tickets|accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=Premium Seats USA}}</ref> and Braxton's first performing experience was singing in her church choir.<ref name=\"psu\"/>\n\nBraxton attended [[Bowie State University]] to obtain a teaching degree,<ref>{{Cite news|first=Joy Bennett|last=Kinnon|title=The Rise and Fall and Rise of Toni Braxton|work=Ebony|date=December 2000}}</ref> but decided to sing professionally after she was discovered by William E. Pettaway Jr., who reportedly heard her singing to herself while pumping gas.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Morgan|last=Joan|title=Fully Exposed|work=Vibe|date=December 2002|quote=One day in 1990, songwriter Bill Pettaway heard Toni singing to herself at an Annapolis gas station, liked what he heard, and got her an audition with L.A.}}</ref>\n\nOn her appearance May 24, 2014 broadcast of [[NPR]]'s ''[[Wait Wait... Don't Tell Me!]]'', she stated that she was not singing to herself at the gas station. Pettaway, working as an attendant at the [[Annapolis]] service station where she was refueling, recognized her from local performances and introduced himself, saying he wanted to produce her. Although skeptical, Braxton decided to, in her words, \"take a chance\" and accepted.<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.npr.org/programs/wait-wait-dont-tell-me/315248388/wait-wait-dont-tell-me-for-may-24-2014|title=\"Wait, Wait, Don't Tell Me! For May 24, 2014\"|website=Npr.org|accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===1989\u20131995: The Braxtons, ''Toni Braxton'' and breakthrough===\n{{Main|The Braxtons}}\nBraxton and her four sisters (Traci, Towanda, Trina, and Tamar) began performing as [[The Braxtons]] in the late 1980s and were signed to [[Arista Records]] in 1989. Their first single, \"[[Good Life (The Braxtons song)|Good Life]]\", was released in 1990.<ref name=\"vibe\">{{cite web |url = http://www.vibe.com/music/search/artist.html?id=UCAgICAzNzU3Ng |title = Toni Braxton |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = VIBE.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071112190035/http://www.vibe.com/music/search/artist.html?id=UCAgICAzNzU3Ng |archivedate = November 12, 2007 }}</ref> Though the song was not successful, it attracted the attention of [[Antonio \"L.A.\" Reid]] and [[Kenneth \"Babyface\" Edmonds]].<ref name=\"vibe\"/>\n\nReid and Babyface recruited her to record a demo of \"Love Shoulda Brought You Home\", a song that they had written for Anita Baker for the soundtrack of [[Eddie Murphy]]'s film, ''[[Boomerang (1992 film)|Boomerang]]''. Baker, who was pregnant at the time,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://uk.askmen.com/women/singer/8c_toni_braxton.html |title = Toni Braxton |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = AskMen |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070930181638/http://uk.askmen.com/women/singer/8c_toni_braxton.html |archive-date = September 30, 2007 |url-status=dead |df = mdy-all }}</ref> did not record the song but suggested that Braxton record it. Her recording was later included on the soundtrack along with \"[[Give U My Heart]]\", a duet by Braxton and Babyface. Braxton, meanwhile, was signed to Reid and Edmonds' Arista-distributed imprint, [[LaFace Records]], and immediately began recording her solo debut album.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nOn July 13, 1993, LaFace Records released Braxton's self-titled debut album, ''[[Toni Braxton (album)|Toni Braxton]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Toni-Braxton/dp/B0000013G5|title=''Toni Braxton'': Music: Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Amazon.com}}</ref> The album, which was primarily produced by Reid, [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]], and [[Daryl Simmons]], peaked at number one on the U.S. [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] albums chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=30331&aid=146011|title=Discography&nbsp;\u2013 Toni Braxton \u2013 ''Toni Braxton''|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Billboard.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929141413/http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=30331&aid=146011|archivedate=September 29, 2007}}</ref> The first single, \"[[Another Sad Love Song]]\", peaked at number seven and number two on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks|R&B Singles]] charts respectively. The song was also the very first #1 song on the newly created Adult R&B Charts. Billboard created the chart in September 1993.<ref name=\"billboard singles\">{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=30331&model.vnuAlbumId=146011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929211922/http://billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=30331&model.vnuAlbumId=146011|url-status=dead|archive-date=September 29, 2007|title=Artist Chart History&nbsp;\u2013 Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Billboard.com}}</ref> The album's second single, \"[[Breathe Again]]\", peaked in the top five of both the Hot 100 and R&B singles charts<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/> and no 2 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com|title=UK Top 40 Chart Archive, British Singles & Album Charts|website=Everyhit.com|date=March 16, 2000|accessdate=January 16, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702234638/http://www.everyhit.com/|archivedate=July 2, 2007}}</ref> More singles from ''Toni Braxton'' were released in 1994, including \"[[You Mean the World to Me (Toni Braxton song)|You Mean the World to Me]]\", \"[[Seven Whole Days]]\", and \"[[I Belong to You/How Many Ways]]\".<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/>\n\nBraxton's debut album won her several awards, including three [[Grammy Award]]s (for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] and two consecutive awards for [[Grammy Award for Best Female R&B Vocal Performance|Best Female R&B Vocal Performance]] in 1994 and 1995).<ref name=\"YTV\">{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/toni-braxton/contributor/38261/awards|title=Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 26, 2006|work=Yahoo! TV|date=March 14, 2003}}</ref> She won two [[American Music Award]]s (for Favorite Soul/R&B New Artist and Favorite New Adult Contemporary Artist)<ref name=\"YTV\"/> in 1994 and another one in 1995 (for Favorite Soul/R&B Album).<ref name=\"YTV\"/> ''Toni Braxton'' was certified 8x platinum in USA and has sales of over 10 million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gp/bestsellers/topalbums.asp|title=Gold&Platinum: Top 100 albums|accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=RIAA|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061214122646/http://www.riaa.com/gp/bestsellers/topalbums.asp|archivedate=December 14, 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"books.google.com\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ArUDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA56&dq=toni+braxton+sold&hl=pt-BR&ei=kBKETJGqLoP98Ab5vb2aAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=toni%20braxton%20sold&f=false|title=Jet&nbsp;\u2013 Google Livros|website=Books.google.com|date=July 17, 2000|accessdate=November 12, 2010}}</ref>\n\n===1996\u20131999: ''Secrets'' and financial issues===\nIn June 1996, Braxton released her second and most successful album, ''[[Secrets (Toni Braxton album)|Secrets]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0000013GH|title=''Secrets'': Music: Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Amazon.com}}</ref> Braxton said of the album: \"The motivation for this album was to include a little bit of everything. Our aim was to come up with material, that would have a familiar 'feel' to the people, who bought the first album without being musically redundant.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockonthenet.com/artists-b/tonibraxton_main.htm|title=Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=Rock on the Net}}</ref> Along with Babyface, Braxton also worked with [[R. Kelly]], [[Tony Rich]], and [[David Foster]] on the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artistdirect.com/nad/store/artist/album/0,,230175,00.html?src=search#credits|title=Toni Braxton: ''Secrets'' |accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=ArtistDirect}}</ref> Braxton co-produced the album and co-wrote two of its songs, including the 1997 single \"How Could an Angel Break My Heart\", which was also later included on ''Diana Princess of Wales Tribute,'' a [[Princess Diana]] memorial album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000002C4U|title=''Diana Princess of Wales Tribute''|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Amazon.com}}</ref>\n\nWith help from the album's first single, \"[[You're Makin' Me High]]\", which became Braxton's first number-one hit on the Hot 100 singles chart,<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/> the album peaked at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?JSESSIONID=FHJ2kFF9nFq0gg5KtPxXY8nGJ2sqxnQLL1brcY1T26XLrc1Q1lcF!-1562377538&pid=30331&aid=185866|title=Discography&nbsp;\u2013 Toni Braxton \u2013 ''Secrets''|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Billboard.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929141203/http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?JSESSIONID=FHJ2kFF9nFq0gg5KtPxXY8nGJ2sqxnQLL1brcY1T26XLrc1Q1lcF%21-1562377538&pid=30331&aid=185866|archivedate=September 29, 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref> \"You're Makin' Me High\" also topped the R&B singles chart for two weeks<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/> and saw similar success in Europe and Asia.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nThe album's second single, \"[[Un-Break My Heart]]\", written and composed by [[Diane Warren]], became the biggest hit of Braxton's career, spending 11 consecutive weeks at number one on the Hot 100<ref name=\"vibe\"/> and also topping the [[Hot Dance Singles Sales]] chart for eleven weeks and the [[Hot Dance Music/Club Play]] chart for four weeks.<ref name=\"mfc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicfanclubs.org/tonibraxton/timeline.htm|title=Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 26, 2006|work=Music Fan Clubs}}</ref> as well as reaching no 2 in the UK<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com|title=UK Top 40 Chart Archive, British Singles & Album Charts|website=Everyhit.com|date=March 16, 2000|accessdate=February 1, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702234638/http://www.everyhit.com/|archivedate=July 2, 2007}}</ref>\n\nOther singles from the album included the double A-side \"[[I Don't Want To]]\"/\"[[I Love Me Some Him]]\" (which peaked at number one on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart)<ref name=\"billboard singles\" /> and \"How Could an Angel Break My Heart;\" this last featured [[Kenny G]], with whom Braxton later toured.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://livedesignonline.com/mag/lighting_kenny_toni_lds |title = Kenny G and Toni B: Lds Valerie Groth and Justin Collie manipulate one lighting system to create two shows |accessdate = December 26, 2006 |work = Live Design |date = May 1, 1997 }}</ref> After 92 weeks in the charts, ''Secrets'' was certified 8x platinum, becoming Braxton's second straight 8 million-seller. Internationally, ''Secrets'' sold more than 15 million copies, thus cementing Braxton's superstar status.<ref name=\"books.google.com\" /> Braxton topped the ''Billboard'' Year-End Charts as the Top Hot 100 Singles Artist&nbsp;\u2013 Female,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/charts/yearend_chart_display.jsp?f=The+Billboard+Hot+100&g=Year-end+Singles&year=1997 |title=Year End Charts&nbsp;\u2013 Year-end Singles&nbsp;\u2013 The Billboard Hot 100 |accessdate=December 26, 2006 |website=Billboard.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061224112647/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/charts/yearend_chart_display.jsp?f=The+Billboard+Hot+100&g=Year-end+Singles&year=1997 |archivedate=December 24, 2006 }}</ref> Top R&B Artist&nbsp;\u2013 Female (singles and albums),<ref name=\"mfc\" /> Top Hot R&B Singles Artist&nbsp;\u2013 Female,<ref name=\"mfc\" /> Top Hot Dance Club Play Artist, and Top Hot Adult Contemporary Artist, while \"Un-Break My Heart\" became the Top Hot Dance Club Play Single and the Top Hot Adult Contemporary Track of the year. She won two Grammy Awards; one for [[Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Performance|Best Female Pop Vocal Performance]]<ref name=\"YTV\" /> for \"Un-Break My Heart\" and Best Female R&B Vocal Performance for \"You're Makin' Me High\" as well as two [[American Music Award]]s for Favorite Female Soul/R&B Artist and Favorite Soul/R&B Album.<ref name=\"YTV\" />\n\nBy 1996, Braxton had sold more than 20 million records; unfortunately, she was still waiting on her financial rewards, eventually launching an unsuccessful lawsuit against Arista and LaFace Records. Soon after, she filed for chapter 7 bankruptcy. Public reaction to these events was very harsh, having been expressed most clearly in an interview on ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]].''<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ftLjr4CQcrQ |title = \"She was so frickin' mean to me\": Toni Braxton's Original Full Interview with Oprah (1998) |publisher = YouTube |date = March 29, 2013 |accessdate = July 8, 2015 }}</ref> Upon successfully filing for bankruptcy, Braxton relinquished the rights to many of her valued possessions, including the Grammys and American Music Awards she had previously been granted.{{citation needed|date=September 2017}}\n\nBraxton has appeared in two [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] shows: She made her Broadway debut as Belle in ''[[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' beginning September 9, 1998 when she replaced Kim Huber.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/40798-Braxton-Taylor-Barbour-Beast-to-Be-Unveiled-Sept-9-New-Menken-Song-to-Follow |title=Braxton-Taylor-Barbour Beast to Be Unveiled Sept. 9; New Menken Song to Follow |accessdate=June 27, 2010 |work=playbill |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144402/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/40798-Braxton-Taylor-Barbour-Beast-to-Be-Unveiled-Sept-9-New-Menken-Song-to-Follow |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> During her run in the show [[Alan Menken]] wrote and composed a new song for the musical, titled \"A Change in Me\", which he specially wrote and composed for Braxton, and was still being used in the musical as of late July 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/41311-Toni-Braxton-Premieres-Beauty-s-New-Song-Oct-7-On-Rosie |title=Toni Braxton Premieres Beauty's New Song, Oct. 7 On 'Rosie' |website=Playbill.com |date= |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144507/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/41311-Toni-Braxton-Premieres-Beauty-s-New-Song-Oct-7-On-Rosie |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> She left the production on February 28, 1999 and was succeeded by [[Andrea McArdle]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/43273-Bways-Beauty-Turns-2000-Sat-Matinee-Jan-30-McArdle-Arrives-March-3 |title=Bway's Beauty Turns 2,000 Sat. Matinee Jan. 30; McArdle Arrives March 3 |website=Playbill.com |date= |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144741/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/43273-Bways-Beauty-Turns-2000-Sat-Matinee-Jan-30-McArdle-Arrives-March-3 |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> Her role in ''Beauty and the Beast'' marked the first (and only) time a black woman commanded the leading role of Belle on Broadway. (In the UK, [[Michelle Gayle]] played the role in the West End.) It also marked the first time a black woman would star in a Disney musical on Broadway. In 1999, the lawsuit against LaFace Records was settled and Braxton was given back all her possessions, giving her time to record ''The Heat'', her first album in four years.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.lifetimetv.com/shows/ip/portraits/0223/0223_bio.html |title = Toni Braxton |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = Lifetime's intimate portrait |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20051205012041/http://www.lifetimetv.com/shows/ip/portraits/0223/0223_bio.html |archivedate = December 5, 2005 }}</ref>\n\n===2000\u20132001: ''The Heat'' and acting debut===\nAfter Braxton's three-year-long dispute with LaFace and Arista had been settled, Toni signed a new $20 million contract. In March 2000, LaFace Records released \"[[He Wasn't Man Enough]]\", the first single from Braxton's third studio album, ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]''. By June 2000, the song peaked at number two on the Hot 100 chart and No. 1 on the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop chart. ''The Heat'' was released on April 25, 2000, debuting at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart with first-week sales of 194,448 copies sold,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitsdailydouble.com/sales/archcht.cgi?cht692|title=Previous Album Sales Chart|publisher=HITS Daily Double|accessdate=November 12, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120908231013/http://www.hitsdailydouble.com/sales/archcht.cgi?cht692|archivedate=September 8, 2012}}</ref> it remained in the top 20 for fifteen consecutive weeks. Braxton again worked with producers Babyface and Foster; also included in the staple were [[Rodney Jerkins]], and new beau musician [[Keri Lewis]].\n\nBraxton took a more hands-on approach, co-writing and co-producing a handful of the tracks. One selection on ''The Heat'', titled \"Gimme Some\", featured a rap verse from [[TLC (group)|TLC]] star [[Lisa \"Left Eye\" Lopes]]. The album's second single, \"[[Just Be a Man About It]]\", peaked at number 32 on the Hot 100 and number six on the R&B Charts. The third single, \"[[Spanish Guitar (song)|Spanish Guitar]]\", peaked at number 98 on the Hot 100 and number one on the Hot Dance & Club charts. The fourth single, \"Maybe\", peaked at 74 on the R&B charts. ''The Heat'' was certified double platinum in the U.S. and, by 2002, had sold over 4 million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"books.google.com\"/><ref name=vibe2002>{{cite book|title=Vibe Magazine|url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_uyUEAAAAMBAJ|quote=THE HEAT.|work=[[Vibe Magazine]]|publisher=[[Internet Archive]]|accessdate=May 24, 2014}}</ref>\n\n''The Heat'' was nominated for many awards. At the [[43rd Annual Grammy Awards]], the album's lead single, \"He Wasn't Man Enough\", was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Song|Best R&B Song]] and eventually won a [[Grammy Award for Best Female R&B Vocal Performance]], while the album itself was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Album|Best R&B Album]].<ref name=rockonthenet>{{cite web|title=Rock on the Net: Toni Braxton|url=http://www.rockonthenet.com/artists-b/tonibraxton_main.htm|work=Rock on the Net|accessdate=May 24, 2014}}</ref> She was also nominated for [[Soul Train Music Award for Best R&B/Soul Album, Female|Best R&B/Soul album, Female]] on the [[Soul Train Music Awards]],<ref name=rockonthenet/> but she lost to \"[[Who Is Jill Scott? Words and Sounds Vol. 1]]\" by [[Jill Scott]]. She won 2 [[American Music Awards]] for [[American Music Award for Favorite Soul/R&B Female Artist|Favorite Soul/R&B Female Artist]] and [[American Music Award for Favorite Soul/R&B Album|Favorite Soul/R&B Album]] (''The Heat'').<ref name=rockonthenet/>\n\nIn 2001, she made her movie acting debut in the feature film ''[[Kingdom Come (2001 film)|Kingdom Come]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imdb.com/title/tt0246002|title=Kingdom Come|accessdate=December 19, 2006|website=IMDb.com}} {{better source|date=November 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2002\u20132005: ''More Than a Woman'' and ''Libra'' ===\n\nIn 2002, while gearing up for the release of her fourth studio album, Braxton discovered she was pregnant with her second child. Knowing that she would be unable to promote the album properly, she unsuccessfully lobbied [[Arista Records]] to get the label to postpone its release until after she was to give birth. [[Arista Records]] refused, and the album was released as planned. It received very little promotion from either Arista or Braxton herself, due in Braxton's case to the complicated pregnancy that had confined her to [[bed rest]]. Braxton accused the company of being unwilling to compromise and punishing her for not putting her career over family.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nIn November 2002, Braxton's fourth studio album ''[[More Than a Woman (album)|More Than a Woman]]'' was released. Opening to an instant commercial disappointment, the album peaked at number 13. The first single, [[The Neptunes]] -produced \"[[Hit the Freeway]]\", failed at radio and peaked at number 86 on the Hot 100. The two singles, that followed (\"A Better Man\", \"Lies, Lies, Lies\") were scrapped, failed to make a dent and missed the Hot 100 completely. ''More Than a Woman'' was certified gold by [[RIAA]] and sold more than 800,000 copies worldwide.<ref name=\"musicmp3.ru\">{{cite web |url = http://musicmp3.ru/artist_toni-braxton.html |title = Toni Braxton mp3 music download |publisher = MusicMp3.Ru |date = |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref> Prior to the release of the album, a dispute erupted between Braxton and [[Irv Gotti]], when he played a rough cut of \"No More Love\", a song that he produced for the album, that was to be the first single. Disapproving of Gotti broadcasting the unfinished track, Braxton withheld it from being released. The same year, Braxton was further annoyed, when [[Jay-Z]] used the same sample of [[Tupac Shakur|2Pac]]'s \"Me and My Girlfriend\", that she had already used on her track \"Me & My Boyfriend\" for his and Beyonc\u00e9's \"[['03 Bonnie & Clyde]]\".{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nIn April 2003, Braxton abruptly left Arista Records, having been there for 14 years, and immediately signed with [[Blackground Records]], headed by [[Barry Hankerson]], her manager at the time. She then starred in ''[[Aida (musical)|Aida]]'' as Aida beginning June 30, 2003 when she replaced [[Simone (actress)|Simone]]<ref>{{cite web |url = http://music.yahoo.com/read/news/12037443 |title = Toni Braxton Set To Return To Broadway |accessdate = December 19, 2006 |work = Yahoo! Music |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070612053315/http://music.yahoo.com/read/news/12037443 |archivedate = June 12, 2007 }}</ref> and left the cast on November 16, 2003 where she was replaced by [[Michelle Williams (singer)|Michelle Williams]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/82297-Its-Destiny-RB-Singer-Michelle-Williams-to-Replace-Toni-Braxton-in-Aida |title=It's Destiny: R&B Singer Michelle Williams to Replace Toni Braxton in Aida |website=Playbill.com |date= |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144804/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/82297-Its-Destiny-RB-Singer-Michelle-Williams-to-Replace-Toni-Braxton-in-Aida |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nShe was to star in a half-hour sitcom pilot where she would play a version of herself for [[The WB Television Network]]'s fall 2006\u201307 lineup, though plans to put the show into full-production fell through once The WB announced it would cease to exist in fall 2006.<ref>{{cite web |title = Development Update: September 29\u201330 |url = http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2004/09/30/development-update-september-29-30-17006/6747/ |work = The Futon Critic |accessdate = November 6, 2013 |date = September 30, 2004 }}</ref> She has also starred in the TV sitcom, ''Kevin Hill''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.contactmusic.com/new/xmlfeed.nsf/mndwebpages/toni.s%20tv%20deal |title = Toni's TV Deal |accessdate = January 24, 2007 |work = Contact Music |date = September 20, 2004 }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2005, Braxton's new label, Blackground/Universal, released \"[[Please (Toni Braxton song)|Please]]\", the first single from her fifth album, ''[[Libra (Toni Braxton album)|Libra]]''. The album was originally planned for a June release, but it was pushed back several times and was finally issued on September 27. Unfortunately for Braxton, her troubles with weak album promotion and lack of label commitment were not over. \"Please\" peaked at number 36 on ''Billboard'' Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs, while altogether missing the Hot 100.\n\n''Libra'' still managed to debut at number four on the ''Billboard'' 200 selling 114,593 copies in the first week. ''Libra'' also peaked at number two on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums. Although that is strong for an album with little to no promotion, it became yet another commercial disappointment for Braxton. The album's second single, \"[[Trippin' (That's the Way Love Works)]]\", received less airplay and peaked at number 67 on the R&B chart. The failure was ascribed to the non-video presence of the single and lack of label support. The album was certified gold in late 2005 and has since sold 679,000 copies worldwide.<ref name=\"musicmp3.ru\" />\n\n=== 2006\u20132007: ''Toni Braxton: Revealed'' and label conflicts ===\n\nBraxton recorded a song in 2006 with [[Il Divo]], titled \"[[The Time of Our Lives (Il Divo and Toni Braxton song)|The Time of Our Lives]]\". The song was used as the official [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] anthem and was performed at the opening ceremony in [[Berlin]], Germany, on June 9. The song was also performed at the closing ceremonies making Braxton and Il Divo the first artists to be asked to perform for the opening and closing ceremonies.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/tm_objectid=16862049&method=full&siteid=94762&headline=fiona--divo--name_page.html |title = Fiona: divo |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = Mirror.co.uk }}</ref>\n\nBraxton made an appearance on the season finale of ''[[American Idol (season 5)|American Idol 5]]'', where she performed [[Elvis Presley]]'s \"[[In the Ghetto]]\" with soon-to-be winner [[Taylor Hicks]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1532468/20060524/hicks__taylor.jhtml |title = Soul Patrol Rides On: Taylor Hicks Wins 'American Idol' |accessdate = December 27, 2006 |work = MTV News |date = May 25, 2006 }}</ref>\n\nOn May 19, 2006, the [[Flamingo Las Vegas|Flamingo Hotel and Casino]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada|Las Vegas]] announced that Braxton would replace [[Wayne Newton]] as the casino's new headlining act from August 3, 2006.<ref>{{cite news |title = Toni Braxton to be headliner at Flamingo Las Vegas to 2007 |url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/travel/hotels/2006-05-19-braxtons-back_x.htm |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[USA Today]] |date = May 19, 2006 |agency = Associated Press }}</ref> The show, entitled [[Toni Braxton: Revealed]], was to be performed six nights a week and was scheduled to run through to March 2007. Braxton later confirmed that she was extending her show through to August 2007. Due to its success, it was reported that Braxton would extend her show through to August 2008. The show was later cancelled in order for Braxton to focus on her health.<ref>{{cite news |last = Mascia |first = Kristen |title = Toni Braxton Cancels Vegas Show |url = http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20203349,00.html |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = People |date = May 30, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nIn an October 2006 concert at the [[Flamingo Las Vegas]], Braxton broke down in tears while announcing to the audience that just before the concert began she had been told that her son, Diezel, had been diagnosed with [[autism]].<ref>{{cite news |last = Walls |first = Jeannette |title = O.J. Simpson to confess \u2013 hypothetically, Plus: Toni Braxton sobs while discussing autistic son |url = http://www.today.com/id/15066202 |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Today.com]] |date = October 30, 2006 }}</ref> Braxton has been outspoken regarding her doctor's failure to diagnose Diezel's condition earlier, contending that if he had been diagnosed earlier he could have received treatment earlier.<ref>{{cite news |title = Braxton Upset With Doctor's Over Son's Autism |url = http://www.contactmusic.com/news/braxton-upset-with-doctors-over-sons-autism_1009575 |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Contactmusic.com]] |date = September 29, 2006 }}</ref> As well as becoming a spokeswoman for [[Autism Speaks]],<ref>{{cite news |title = Toni Braxton Named National Celebrity Spokesperson for Autism Speaks |url = http://www.autismspeaks.org/about-us/press-releases/toni-braxton-named-national-celebrity-spokesperson-autism-speaks |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Autism Speaks]] |date = March 7, 2007 }}</ref> she is also a spokeswoman for the [[American Heart Association]].\n\nOn January 12, 2007, Braxton filed a lawsuit in the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York]] against her former manager Barry Hankerson for $10 million, alleging \"fraud, deception and double dealing\", in addition to mismanaging her relationship with Arista Records.<ref name=tbmgr>{{cite news |last = Neumeister |first = Larry |title = Toni Braxton Sues Her Former Manager |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/01/12/AR2007011201814.html |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[The Washington Post]] |date = January 12, 2007 |agency = AP }}</ref> According to Braxton's lawsuit, Hankerson placed his personal financial interests ahead of hers by using 'double-talk' to compromise the relationship between Braxton and her former recording label, [[Arista Records]], with Hankerson allegedly telling Arista that \"Braxton no longer wanted to record for Arista\", and telling Braxton that \"Arista was not interested in working with her anymore\".<ref name=tbmgr />\n\nThe suit was settled with Braxton being forced to return a $375,000 advance to Hankerson, who would also receive a percentage of the sales of her next album, and Hankerson releasing Braxton from her contract with him. The settlement also temporarily limited the companies with which Braxton can sign.<ref>{{cite news |title = Braxton Settles Lawsuit Against Ex-Manager |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1054986/braxton-settles-lawsuit-against-ex-manager |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = Billboard |date = February 14, 2007 |agency = AP }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = https://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/20070113/ap_on_en_mu/braxton_lawsuit_2 |title = Toni Braxton sues her former manager |accessdate = January 12, 2007 |work = Yahoo |date = January 12, 2007 }}{{Dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Hankerson claimed that the problems initially arose due to a number of disputes with Braxton and her wish to include her husband in her music.<ref>{{cite news |last = Finn |first = Natalie |title = Braxton Settles Up with Ex-Manager |url = http://au.eonline.com/news/54395/braxton-settles-up-with-ex-manager |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[E! Online]] |date = February 13, 2007 }}</ref>\n\n=== 2008\u20132010: ''Pulse'' and television ===\nBraxton appeared on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 7)|seventh season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''; her partner was [[Alec Mazo]].<ref>{{Cite news |title = Announcing the Stars |url = http://abc.go.com/primetime/dancingwiththestars/index?pn=announcement |work = abc.go.com |year = 2008 |accessdate = September 16, 2008 }}</ref> They were voted off in the fifth week of the competition.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:left;\"\n|-  style=\"text-align:Center; background:#ccc;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Week'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Dance/Song'''\n| colspan=\"3\"|'''Judges' score'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Result'''\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#ccc;\"\n|  style=\"width:10%; \"|Inaba\n|  style=\"width:10%; \"|Goodman\n|  style=\"width:10%; \"|Tonioli\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|1A\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|[[cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]]/ \"[[Smooth (song)|Smooth]]\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|7\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|7\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|8\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|Safe\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|1B\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|[[Quickstep]]/ \"[[Blue Skies (1926 song)|Blue Skies]]\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|8\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|7\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|8\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|Last to Be Called Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||2\n||[[Rhumba|Rumba]]/ \"[[I Can't Make You Love Me]]\"\n||7\n||8\n||8\n||Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||3\n||[[Viennese Waltz]]/ \"[[F\u00fcr Elise]]\"\n||8\n||7\n||7\n||Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||4\n||[[Samba]]/ \"De Donde Soy\"\n||7\n||7\n||8\n||Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||5\n||[[West Coast Swing]]/ \"[[The Way You Make Me Feel]]\"\n||7\n||7\n||8\n||Eliminated\n|}{{Clear}}\n\n[[File:Toni Braxton 2009 VH1 Divas.jpg|thumb|Braxton at the 2009 VH1 Divas Red Carpet]]\n\nIn October 2008 Braxton signed to [[Atlantic Records]]. The DJ Frank E produced song \"[[Yesterday (Toni Braxton song)|Yesterday]]\" premiered on September 11, 2009 and features [[Trey Songz]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.essence.com/news_entertainment/entertainment/articles/listen_to_toni_braxtons_new_single_yesterday |title = Exclusive: Be the First to Listen to Toni Braxton's New Single 'Yesterday' |accessdate = September 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090914055322/http://www.essence.com/news_entertainment/entertainment/articles/listen_to_toni_braxtons_new_single_yesterday |archivedate = September 14, 2009 }}</ref> It was released as the lead single from her sixth studio album ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/960751/toni-braxton-pulse-album-preview |title = Toni Braxton \"Pulse\" Album Preview |magazine = Billboard |accessdate = June 29, 2013 }}</ref> \"Yesterday\" peaked at No. 12 on the U.S. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart making it her highest chart performance since her 2000 single \"[[Just Be a Man About It]]\", which peaked at No. 6. The single has been released worldwide on May 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web |author=Praxis Media |url=http://www.radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_singles.htm |title=Radio1 Rodos Greece ::: UK Forthcoming Singles ::: Charts, DJ Promos, Dance, Lyrics, Free Mp3 Samples Downloads |website=Radio1.gr |date= |accessdate=November 12, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121122103050/http://radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_singles.htm |archivedate=November 22, 2012 |df=mdy }}</ref> In the UK, \"Yesterday\" became Braxton's first hit single since the release of \"[[Hit the Freeway]]\", peaking at No. 50 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and at No. 17 on the [[UK R&B Chart|UK R&B Singles Chart]]. The song also became a moderate hit in Europe, peaking at No. 20 on the [[German Singles Chart]], at No. 17 on the [[Swiss Singles Chart]] and charting at No. 50 on the [[European Hot 100]].\n\nBy November 2009 Braxton had separated from Lewis.<ref>{{cite news |title = Toni Braxton Confirms 'Single' and 'Separated' Post Divorce Rumor |url = http://www.singersroom.com/content/2009-11-20/Toni-Braxton-Confirms-Single-and-Separated-Post-Divorce-Rumor/ |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Singersroom]] |date = November 20, 2009 }}</ref> Two songs were released from her upcoming album, \"[[Hands Tied]]\" and \"Make My Heart\". The former peaked at No. 29 on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]], the latter was sent to dance/club radio.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tonibraxton.com/news/hands-tied-make-my-heart-are-now-available-to-buy-exclusively-on-tonibraxtoncom/ |title = \"Hands Tied\" & \"Make My Heart\" Are Now Available To Buy Exclusively on ToniBraxton.com! \u2013 Blog Detail |publisher = ToniBraxton.com |date = January 29, 2010 |accessdate = November 12, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110108182712/http://www.tonibraxton.com/news/hands-tied-make-my-heart-are-now-available-to-buy-exclusively-on-tonibraxtoncom/ |archivedate = January 8, 2011 }}</ref>\nShe performed \"Make My Heart\" on ''[[The Wendy Williams Show]]''.\n\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Toni Braxton Soul Beach.JPG|thumb|left|Soul Beach Music Festival press conference, Braxton with [[Gee Money]], May 2010]] -->\nBraxton released her sixth studio album ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]'' on May 4, 2010 in the US<ref>{{cite web |url = http://thatgrapejuice.net/2010/01/toni-braxtons-pulse-pushed/ |title = Toni Braxton's 'Pulse' Pushed Back&nbsp;\u2013 Again &#124; ..::That Grape Juice // ThatGrapeJuice.net::.. &#124;&#124; Thirsty? |publisher = Thatgrapejuice.net |date = January 21, 2010 |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref> and on May 10, 2010 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web |author = Praxis Media |url = http://www.radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_albums.htm |title = Radio1 Rodos Greece ::: UK Forthcoming Albums ::: Charts, DJ Promos, Dance, Lyrics, Free Mp3 Samples Downloads |publisher = Radio1.gr |date = |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref>\nDespite the fact that 27 songs were leaked, the album consisting of only 11 tracks, debuted at No. 9 on the US Billboard 200 chart and hit No. 1 on Billboard's [[R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]] chart, becoming Braxton's fifth US top-ten album. It also achieved moderate chart success around the world. In Canada, it debuted at No. 72 on the Top 100 Albums chart and in the United Kingdom, it debuted at No. 28 on the Top 40 Albums and at No. 7 on the R&B Albums chart. It entered at No. 18 on the German Album Chart. In Switzerland, the album hit No. 9. ''Pulse'', although a commercial flop, became Toni's first album to chart inside the [[European Top 100 Albums]] since her 2000 album ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]''.\n\nOn June 28, 2010, Braxton posted a video for ''Woman''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tonibraxton.com/ |title = Toni Braxton &#124; Official Website: Photos, Blog, Videos, Interactive and more. |publisher = ToniBraxton.com |date = |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref>\n\nBraxton was included as part of the \"[[We Are the World 25 for Haiti]]\" remake of the 1985 hit \"[[We Are the World]]\" to help benefit the people of Haiti following the January 12, 2010 magnitude 7.0 MW earthquake in Haiti. The new version of the song was recorded on February 1, 2010. Music legends [[Quincy Jones]] and [[Lionel Richie]] act as Executive Producers as well as [[Wyclef Jean]]. Artists involved included [[Celine Dion]], [[Barbra Streisand]], [[Janet Jackson]], [[Tony Bennett]], [[Wyclef Jean]], [[Josh Groban]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]], [[Mary J. Blige]], [[Jennifer Hudson]], [[Adam Levine]], [[Justin Bieber]], [[LL Cool J]], among others.\n\nAccording to Braxton, via a lawsuit, [[TMZ]], and [[VH1]]'s [[Behind the Music]], after her ''Toni Braxton: Revealed'' show was abruptly cancelled back in 2008, the insurance agency, [[Lloyd's of London]] refused to honor her policy that she purchased for upwards of $70,000 that included financial compensations for financial losses that occurred as results of concert cancellations.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toni Braxton: My Insurance Co. Has No Heart|url=http://www.tmz.com/2009/04/29/toni-braxton-lawsuit|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=[[TMZ]]|date=April 29, 2009}}</ref> The policy was reported to insure Braxton up to $2.8 million.<ref name=\"hinterlandgazette.com\">{{cite news|last=Shan|first=Janet|title=Legal Briefs: Singer Toni Braxton Sues Lloyd's of London Over Cancelled Shoes|url=http://hinterlandgazette.com/2009/05/legal-briefs-singer-toni-braxton-sues.html|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=The Hinterland Gazette|date=May 3, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"vh1.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/behind_the_music/episode.jhtml?episodeID=200331|title=Ep. 238 &#124; Toni Braxton &#124; Behind The Music|website=VH1.com|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref>\n\nLloyd's of London responded with a counter-suit seeking damages against Braxton and remarked that Braxton's policy was null and void because of an unrelated heart condition that the company was not made aware of at the time the application was filed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Insurance Co. Claims Braxton's a Hearty Liar|url=http://www.tmz.com/2009/10/01/lloyds-of-london-toni-braxton-lawsuit-heart-condition|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=TMZ|date=October 1, 2009}}</ref> Braxton responded to the counter-suit by saying that she did disclose her full medical history at the time.<ref name=\"hinterlandgazette.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hellobeautiful.com/509107/lloyds-of-london-sues-toni-braxton|title=Lloyds of London Sues Toni Braxton|website=Hellobeautiful.com|date=October 1, 2009|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsok.com/toni-braxton-sues-her-insurance-company/article/3816464|title=Toni Braxton sues her insurance company|website=Newsok.com|date=April 29, 2009|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref> As a result of the insurance company nullifying Braxton's contract, Braxton has said that she was on the hook for all damages because of the cancelled shows, being sued by multiple companies, and had to once again file for bankruptcy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toni Braxton: My Vegas Show Broke Me|url=http://www.tmz.com/2010/10/07/toni-braxton-files-chapter-7-bankruptcy-las-vegas-show-broke-debt|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=TMZ|date=October 7, 2010}}</ref> As of 2013, Braxton has completed required financial management courses and most of her debt has been discharged.<ref name=\"vh1.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2013/07/06/toni-braxton-bankruptcy-case-settled|title=Toni Braxton \u2013 Bankruptcy Case finally settled|website=Tmz.com|date=June 7, 2013}}</ref>\n\nLater that year rumors began circulating that Braxton was in talks to star in her own reality show with [[Bravo (U.S. TV network)|Bravo]]. Braxton would later confirm the rumors during an appearance on Ellen after a performance of her single \"Make My Heart\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/02/bravo-snags-singer-toni-braxton-for-new-reality-series.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100214093552/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/02/bravo-snags-singer-toni-braxton-for-new-reality-series.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 14, 2010|title=Bravo snags singer Toni Braxton for new reality series|website=Blog.zap2it.com|accessdate=February 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===2011\u20132012: Television success and initial retirement===\n[[File:Toni Braxton Romania.jpg|thumb|left|Braxton performing in [[Romania]] during New Year's Eve 2011]]\nBraxton signed with [[WE tv]] for a [[reality series]], ''[[Braxton Family Values]]'', and the series debuted April 12, 2011, with Braxton, her mother, and her four sisters; Trina, [[Tamar Braxton|Tamar]], Traci and Towanda.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/01/04/wetv-toni-braxton-staten-island-cakes-tagline/ |title = WEtv unveils new details on Toni Braxton series, new cake series, and announces new tagline |author = James Hibberd |date = January 4, 2011 |accessdate = April 16, 2011 }}</ref> Toni parted ways with her long-time manager Vincent Herbert, who is also husband of sister Tamar Braxton, and signed a new management deal with Los Angeles -based entertainment/production company 'The Collective'.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://thatgrapejuice.net/2011/09/toni-braxton-signs-management/ |title = Toni Braxton Signs New Management Deal &#124; ..::That Grape Juice // ThatGrapeJuice.net::.. &#124;&#124; Thirsty? |publisher = Thatgrapejuice.net |date = September 6, 2011 |accessdate = May 5, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nBraxton completed filming of ''[[The Oogieloves in the Big Balloon Adventure]]'' alongside [[Jaime Pressly]] and [[Cloris Leachman]] which was released in 2012. Her character&nbsp;\u2013 Rosalie Rosebud&nbsp;\u2013 is a singer, whose over-the-top personality was apparently inspired by [[Mariah Carey]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.bluesandsoul.com/feature/538/ms_impulsive/ |title = Toni Braxton interview by Pete Lewis, 'Blues & Soul' May 2010 |publisher = Bluesandsoul.com |date = |accessdate = January 16, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last = Moss |first = Ricki |url = http://www.bet.com/news/celebrities/2012/08/24/watch-toni-braxton-stars-in-childrens-film.html |title = Watch: Toni Braxton Stars in Children's Film &#124; News |publisher = BET |date =  |accessdate = November 25, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nLater that year Braxton confirmed work on her eighth studio album.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://welovetoni.com/forum/topics/breaking-news-toni-is-working-with-l-a-reid-on-new-album|title=BREAKING NEWS: Toni is working with L.A. Reid on new album|website=WeLoveToni.com|date=October 28, 2011|accessdate=January 16, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120405123535/http://welovetoni.com/forum/topics/breaking-news-toni-is-working-with-l-a-reid-on-new-album |archivedate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> Braxton announced at Mercedes-Benz 2012 Fall/Winter Fashion Week in an interview with Rocco Leo Gaglioti as a part of \"Fashion News Live\", that she would be releasing a new single titled \"[[I Heart You (Toni Braxton song)|I Heart You]]\" in March 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toyazworld.com/2012/02/10/toni-braxton-confirms-new-single-i-heart-you/#more-14993|title=Toni Braxton confirms new single 'I Heart You'...|website=ToyazWorld.com}}</ref> Braxton premiered \"I Heart You\" on March 9, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author=Pro Motion|url=http://blog.promotion-us.com/exclusive-mp3-toni-braxton-i-heart-you|title=Exclusive: Toni Braxton 'I Heart You'|website=Blog.promotion-us.com|date=March 9, 2012|accessdate=April 9, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311172728/http://blog.promotion-us.com/exclusive-mp3-toni-braxton-i-heart-you|archivedate=March 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe song has peaked at number 1 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Dance/Club play chart.<ref>{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=toni braxton|chart=all}}</ref> The music video for \"I Heart You\" was directed by [[Bille Woodruff]]. Shortly after the release of [[I Heart You (Toni Braxton song)|I Heart You]] rumors began circulating that Braxton would soon retire. These rumors would later be confirmed by Braxton herself on February 7, 2013. Braxton flew to Canada to begin shooting for her lead role in ''Twist of Faith'' later that year. Braxton appeared on Good Morning America to promote her new movie when she also confirmed the rumors of her retirement revealing that she is retiring from music and stated that she would like to focus on acting: \"I have to do shows here and there, but I'm not gonna do any albums, I'm falling out of love with it, it's weird. I don't know what to say when I hear songs. They don't impact me. I've been trying to listen to songs, record companies have been calling me, so it's a good situation to be in, but I'm not really interested at all\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/387118/toni-braxton-retiring-from-music-to-focus-on-film-career|title=Toni Braxton Retiring From Music to Focus on Film Career|website=Eonline.com|date=February 11, 2013|accessdate=February 17, 2013}}</ref> ''Twist of Faith'' premiered on the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] February 9, 2013.\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Love, Marriage and Divorce,'' Broadway return, and memoir===\n''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' was released on February 4, 2014, under [[Motown Records]]. The lead single from ''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' was titled \"[[Hurt You (song)|Hurt You]];\" it premiered on August 17, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2013/08/17/new-music-toni-braxton-babyface-hurt-you|title=New Music: Toni Braxton & Babyface \u2013 'Hurt You'|publisher = Rap-Up.com|date=August 17, 2013|accessdate=February 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://singersroom.com/content/2013-06-11/Toni-Braxton-Babyface-Unite-For-Duet-Album-Can-The-Duo-Make-A-Hit-Again|title=News &#124; Toni Braxton & Babyface Unite For Duet Album, Can The Duo Make A Hit Again?|publisher=[[Singersroom]]|date=June 11, 2013|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref> The song attained success, claiming the No. 1 spot on two charts: the Billboard Adult R&B Songs chart for four weeks, and the Urban Adult Contemporary (Urban AC) for the week ending December 14, 2013. This marked Braxton's seventh No. 1 hit on the Adult R&B Songs chart and first since her 2000 release \"Just Be a Man About It.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2013-12-11/Toni-Braxton-and-Babyfaces-Hurt-You-Hits-No1-On-Two-Charts-Fantasia-Soars|title=Toni Braxton and Babyface's 'Hurt You' Hits No.1 on Two Charts|publisher=[[Singersroom]]|date=December 11, 2013}}</ref> The song also hit number 16 on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Hot R&B/ Hip Hop Airplay chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/430180/toni-braxton/chart?f=364|title=Toni Braxton: Chart History|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=February 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=Toni Braxton \u2013 Chart history|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> The second single from the album was called \"Where Did We Go Wrong?\" It peaked at No. 11 on the Adult R&B Songs chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2014-01-21/Toni-Braxton-Babyface-and-Ledisi-Soar-With-Thicke-on-Adult-RB-Songs-Charts|title=Toni Braxton, Babyface and Ledisi Soar with Thicke on Adult R&B Songs Chart|publisher=[[Singersroom]]|date=December 11, 2013}}</ref> The album was nominated for World's Best Album at the [[2014 World Music Awards]]. The album won for [[Best R&B Album]] at the 57th Annual Grammy Awards in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees|title=The Official Site of Music's Biggest Night|website=Grammy.com|accessdate=July 8, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201120225/http://www.grammy.com/nominees|archivedate=February 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, it was announced that Braxton would make her return to Broadway alongside collaborator [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]] in Broadway's ''[[After Midnight (musical)|After Midnight]].'' They were scheduled to perform from March 18 to March 31, 2014, at the Brooks Atkinson Theatre. In succession, they would be third in rotation in the role of \"Special Guest Star\" following [[Fantasia Barrino]] and [[KD Lang]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/toni-braxton-kenny-babyface-edmonds-636524|title=Toni Braxton and Kenny 'Babyface' Edmonds Join Broadway's 'After Midnight' Lineup|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=September 25, 2013|accessdate=February 1, 2014|first=David|last=Rooney}}</ref>\n\nOn January 20, 2014, Braxton announced that she would publish a memoir, titled ''Unbreak My Heart: A Memoir,'' through [[Harper Collins Publishers]]. In it, Braxton said, she would discuss her career success and struggles and the self-healing she took charge of after her own diagnosis with the auto-immune disease [[lupus]] and her son's diagnosis with autism. ''Unbreak My Heart: A Memoir'' was published on May 20, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/music/240653651.html |title=Toni Braxton memoir, 'Unbreak My Heart,' coming in May; to cover her hit songs, lupus |newspaper=[[Star Tribune]] |date=January 16, 2014 |accessdate=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202115248/http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/music/240653651.html |archivedate=February 2, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===2015\u20132016: ''Braxton Family Christmas'', biographical film, and The Hits Tour===\nOn May 14, 2015, Braxton said she was headed back to the studio for an upcoming eighth album. She promised that a new single would be released before the end of the year.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://thatgrapejuice.net/2015/05/watch-toni-braxton-announces-new-single-album-due-this-year|title=Watch: Toni Braxton Announces New Single & Album Due This Year|website=Thatgrapejuice.net|date=May 14, 2015|accessdate=July 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, Lifetime greenlighted a biographical film on Braxton's life, ''[[Toni Braxton: Unbreak My Heart]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/toni-braxton-life-story-lifetime-movie-unbreak-my-heart-1201528565|website=Deadline.com|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|date=September 15, 2015|accessdate=September 15, 2015|title=Toni Braxton's Life Story Heading To Lifetime As Original Movie|first=Denise|last=Petski}}</ref> The film's premiere generated 3.6 million viewers, earning the highest rating for an original movie with adults ages 25\u201354, women 25-54 and women 18-49 since \"Whitney,\" the January 2015 biopic on Whitney Houston.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toni Braxton biopic earns high ratings|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/entertainment/music/midnight-sun-blog/bal-toni-braxton-biopic-earns-high-ratings-story.html|newspaper=[[Baltimore Sun]]|accessdate=January 25, 2016}}</ref> The film has an [[IMDb]] rating of a 6.5 out of 10 stars.<ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton: Unbreak my Heart (2016) IMDb|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5037902/|website=IMDb.com|accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref> In October 2015, [[The Braxtons]] released ''[[Braxton Family Christmas]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.essence.com/2015/10/09/braxtons-are-releasing-christmas-album|title=Braxton Family Christmas|website=Essence.com|accessdate=October 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.target.com/p/the-braxtons-braxton-family-christmas/-/A-50059014#prodSlot=medium_1_1&term=Braxton+Family+Christmas|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Braxton Family Christmas|website=Target.com|accessdate=October 11, 2015}}</ref> ''Braxton Family Christmas'' debuted at number 27 on the US [[Billboard R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart|''Billboard'' R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=333|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Chart history|website=Billboard.com|date=October 5, 1996|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref> number 10 on the [[US R&B]] Chart and number 12 on US Top Holiday Albums on November 21, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=1235|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Chart history|website=Billboard.com|date=October 5, 1996|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=325|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Chart history|website=Billboard.com|date=October 5, 1996|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref> The album charted at number 1 on the US [[Top Heatseekers|Heatseekers Albums]] on December 12, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=324 |title = The Braxtons \u2013 Chart History |work = The Braxtons |publisher = Billboard |accessdate = December 17, 2015 }}</ref> Braxton announced in an interview with Sway in the Morning on January 22, 2016 that she and Babyface will collaborate again with ''Love, Marriage & Divorce Pt. II''.<ref name=\"soultracks\">{{cite web |url = http://www.soultracks.com/story-toni-braxton-babyface-recording |title = Toni Braxton and Babyface to team for 2nd album of duets |work = Toni Braxton Babyface |publisher = soultracks |accessdate = January 27, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nOn July 25, 2016, Braxton announced that she would be embarking on a tour in late 2016 titled \"[[The Hits Tour (Toni Braxton)|The Hits Tour]]\" in North America.<ref>{{cite web|title=So excited to announce my new tour starting in October! Get your tickets now! Can't wait to see you all \u2764\ufe0f \u2022The Hits Tour\u2022|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BITLo4GgvTu/|website=Instagram|publisher=Toni Braxton|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> On October 3, five days before the first date of the tour Braxton was hospitalized due to complications with [[Lupus]] resulting in canceling the first two dates of the tour. The dates canceled were rescheduled for January 28 and 29, 2017 and kicked off the tour on in Detroit at the [[MotorCity Casino Hotel]] on October 12, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=TONI BRAXTON HOSPITALIZED Birdman Rushes to Her Side|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/10/03/toni-braxton-hospitalized-birdman/|website=Tmz.com|accessdate=October 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Singer Toni Braxton hospitalized with lupus complications|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/video/tvshowbiz/video-1336092/Singer-Toni-Braxton-hospitalized-lupus-complications.html|website=Dailymail.co.uk|accessdate=October 4, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton (Rescheduled from 10/8) Oakland Tickets - 1/28/17|url=http://www.vividseats.com/concerts/toni-braxton-tickets/toni-braxton-paramount-theatre-oakland-10-8-2109718.html|website=Vividseats.com|accessdate=October 12, 2016}}</ref> On October 15, 2016, Braxton was admitted once again to hospital with complications with Lupus resulting to cancel another tour date October 15, 2016, which was later scheduled to November 14, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=TONI BRAXTON BACK IN HOSPITAL ... Postpones Show|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/10/16/toni-braxton-hospital-postpones-show/|website=Tmz.com|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton Hospitalized Again With Lupus, Postpones Concert|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7542066/toni-braxton-hospitalized-lupus-postpones-concert|website=Billboard|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref> On October 16, 2016, Braxton posted a photo of herself leaving the hospital on her Instagram, announcing that she was on her way to that night's performance in Chicago.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hey guys, thanks for all of your well wishes and understanding. I am out of the hospital, and en route to CHICAGO! I can not wait to see you all TONIGHT at the Arie Crown Theater!! #TheHitsTour \u2764\ufe0f|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BLoeUDkDWH5/|website=Instagram|publisher=Toni Braxton|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn December 1, 2016, Braxton announced a short statement via [[Twitter]] that the dates for The Hits Tour in January 2017 were canceled, a new album would be coming soon and back touring in the summer, \"Hey Guys, Unfortunately, Under doctor\u2019s recommendation, I'm going to have to cancel my shows in Oakland on January 28th and Los Angeles on January 29th, 2017. I'm feeling better and better every day and I want to be at my best when performing for you all. I\u2019m excited to say that I will be completing my new record this spring/summer of 2017 and can't wait to share it with you. Stay tuned for more details. I look forward to seeing everyone back on tour in the summer of 2017!!!\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Hey Guys, Unfortunately, Under doctor's recommendation, I'm going to have to cancel my shows in Oakland on January 28th and|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483723957850112|website=Twitter|accessdate=December 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Los Angeles on January 29th, 2017. I'm feeling better and better every day and I want to be at my best when performing for you all.|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483509410791424|website=Twitter|accessdate=December 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=I\u2019m excited to say that I will be completing my new record this spring/summer of 2017 and can\u2019t wait to share it with you.|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483598283898884|website=Twitter|date=December 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stay tuned for more details.  I look forward to seeing everyone back on tour in the summer of 2017!!!|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483723957850112|website=Twitter|accessdate=December 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132019: ''Sex & Cigarettes'', touring, and other ventures ===\nOn September 14, 2017, Braxton released the lead single \"[[Deadwood (Toni Braxton song)|Deadwood]]\"<ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|title=Deadwood \u2013 Single by Toni Braxton on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/deadwood-single/id1280577966|website=Apple Music (U.S. Store)|accessdate=September 14, 2017}}</ref> from her eighth studio album ''[[Sex & Cigarettes]]''. The single reached #7 on the Adult R&B Charts.<ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton Is Back On The Music Scene With \u2018Sex & Cigarettes\u2019|url=https://hellobeautiful.com/2957549/toni-braxton-announces-new-album|accessdate=September 8, 2017|date=September 7, 2017}}</ref> A remix EP for the song \"Coping\" was released on November 10, 2017. The single reached #1 on the Billboard Dance Charts, marking Braxton's 6th single to reach #1 on that chart.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coping (Remixes) \u2013 EP by Toni Braxton|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/coping-remixes-ep/1306316861|website=Apple Music|accessdate=November 10, 2017}}</ref> The album was nominated for three [[Grammy Awards]]: [[Best R&B Performance]], [[Best R&B Song]] for \"[[Long as I Live (Toni Braxton song)|Long as I Live]]\", and for [[Best R&B Album]] at the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/61st-annual-grammy-awards|title=61st Annual GRAMMY Awards|date=December 6, 2018|website=Grammy.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Faith Under Fire'' premiered on the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] January 22, 2018.<ref name=\"mylifetime\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mylifetime.com/movies/faith-under-fire/about|title=About Faith Under Fire: The Antoinette Tuff Story - Lifetime|website=Mylifetime.com}}</ref> The second single \"[[Long as I Live (Toni Braxton song)|Long as I Live]]\" was released on February 9, 2018. The single reached #1 on the Adult R&B Charts, giving Braxton her eighth #1 on the chart. Braxton also broke a tie with Maxwell and R. Kelly to give her sole possession of the second-most No. 1s in the chart's 24-year history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Long As I Live \u2013 by Toni Braxton|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/long-as-i-live-single/1342585144?l=en|accessdate=February 9, 2018}}</ref> On April 20, 2018, Trina, Towanda and Toni appears as featuring on their sister Traci's single \"Broken Things\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tracibraxton.com/news|title=TraciBraxton - NEWS|website=Traci Braxton Reality Tv Celebrity|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thatgrapejuice.net/2018/04/new-single-traci-braxton-broken-things-featuring-toni-braxton-towanda-braxton-trina-braxton/|title=New Single: Traci Braxton - 'Broken Things' (Featuring Toni Braxton, Towanda Braxton, & Trina Braxton) - That Grape Juice|website=Thatgrapejuice.net|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thisisrnb.com/2018/04/new-music-traci-braxton-feat-toni-braxton-towanda-braxton-trina-braxton-broken-things/|title=New Music: Traci Braxton feat. Toni Braxton, Towanda Braxton & Trina Braxton - Broken Things|date=April 20, 2018|website=Thisisrnb.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref> On October 23, 2018, Braxton announced a joint tour with [[SWV]], As Long As I Live Tour for 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.essence.com/entertainment/toni-braxton-and-swv-are-going-on-tour-next-year/|title=Yassss! Toni Braxton And SWV Are Going On Tour Next Year|first=Keyaira|last=Boone|website=Essence.com}}</ref> Toni and her sister Towanda are the stars on the Christmas TV movie ''Every Day is Christmas'' which premiered on the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] November 24, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9102152/|title=Every Day is Christmas|accessdate=December 15, 2018|website=IMDb.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/03/15/lifetime-doubling-holiday-movies-2018/|title=Lifetime to double number of original holiday movies in 2018|website=Ew.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/lifetime-decks-its-halls-with-23-holiday-themed-movies-more-cheer-1202469310/|title=Lifetime Decks Its Halls With 23 Holiday-Themed Movies & More Cheer|first1=Erik|last1=Pedersen|first2=Erik|last2=Pedersen|date=September 24, 2018|website=Deadline.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/971199/all-the-lifetime-and-hallmark-holiday-movies-you-need-to-watch-this-year|title=Every Holiday Movie Coming to Lifetime and Hallmark This Fall|date=November 1, 2018|website=Eonline.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Braxton and Uncle Bud's Hemp products created a joint marketing campaign for the latter's products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/toni-braxton-and-uncle-buds-natural-hemp-products-join-forces-300710241.html|title=Toni Braxton and Uncle Bud's Natural Hemp Products Join Forces|website=Prnewswire.com|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref> The campaign included multiple videos and pictures online as well as a billboard in New York's Time Square. Braxton is quoted as saying how these products have helped her with her battle against lupus,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unclebudshemp.com/|title=Natural CBD & Hemp Products &#124; Organic Topical Lotions|website=Uncle Bud\u2019s Hemp}}</ref> \"Lupus is a part of who I am, but I am not going to let it define me. I still want to perform & love what I do. Using safe natural products like Uncle Bud's Hemp & CBD makes it possible\".\n\nIn April 2019, it was announced that Braxton would be headlining the 2019 Pittsburgh Pride festival on Saturday, June 8. This is a first for Braxton to perform in a Pride festival.<ref>{{cite news |url = https://www.post-gazette.com/ae/music/2019/04/09/Toni-Braxton-Walk-the-Moon-will-headline-Pittsburgh-Pride-2019/stories/201904090096 |title = Toni Braxton, Walk the Moon will headline Pittsburgh Pride |last = Mervis |first = Scott |date = April 9, 2019 |newspaper=[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]|accessdate = May 8, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, it was announced Braxton would take her As Long As I Live Tour for 2019 international, to South Africa for two dates in November; Johannesburg on the 9th and Cape Town on the 12th. The two shows in South Africa will be followed by a one-off special show in the capital of the United Kingdom, London at the Eventim Apollo in Hammersmith on November 16, 2019; this  will be the first time in 22 years that she has performed a concert in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tonibraxton.com/tour|title=Tour|website=Tonibraxton.com|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2020: Island Records and new music ===\nIn April 2020, it was announced that Braxton had signed with [[Island Records]]. In announcing the news, [[Island Records]] president/CEO Darcus Beese states, \u201cIt\u2019s an honor and pleasure to welcome the incomparable [[Toni Braxton]] to the Island Records family. Her legendary catalogue, unique sound and extraordinary artistry continue to set her apart. We look forward to the world hearing the new music.\u201d\n\nShe released the single, \"Do It\", the first song under the new deal on April 5, 2020. \"Do It\" was not originally going to be the first release from her new album, due in August 2020. The emotional ballad was inspired by a friend of Braxton\u2019s. \u201cWe have all been through situations like this when there is really nothing more to say,\u201d notes Braxton in the Island announcement. \u201cYou know he\u2019s not right and you just need to do what you need to do. There is also an element of hope in the song that after you do what you need to do, things will get better.\u201d<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9351807/toni-braxton-signs-island-records-new-single-do-it-exclusive|title=Toni Braxton Signs with Island Records, Releases New Single \u2018Do It\u2019: Exclusive|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Artistry ==\nBraxton has been recognized for her distinctive [[contralto]] voice.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://articles.courant.com/2012-03-24/entertainment/hc-toni-braxtons-concert-at-foxwoods-20120324_1_toni-braxton-angel-break-concert-review |title = Concert Review: Toni Braxton's Sultry Delivery Scores At Foxwoods |last = Kintner |first = Thomas |date = March 24, 2012 |publisher = courant.com |accessdate = August 11, 2012 }}</ref><ref name=\"books.google.ca\">{{Cite book |title = Rock-N-Roll Gold Rush |last = Dean |first = Maury |authorlink = |year = 2003 |publisher = Algora Publishing |location = |isbn = 0-87586-207-1 |page = 34 |url = https://books.google.com/?id=lJS4EArRBwoC&dq=Rock-N-Roll+Gold+Rush+mariah+carey&pg=PA87&lpg=PA87&q=whitney+houston#PPA34,M1 |accessdate = June 24, 2016 }}</ref> Her voice has been called \"husky, sultry, elegant and sexy.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://myplay.com/artists/toni-braxton |title=My Play: Toni Braxton |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015194514/http://myplay.com/artists/toni-braxton |archivedate=October 15, 2012 }}</ref> Due to the huskiness of her voice, Braxton often used male singers such as [[Michael McDonald (singer)|Michael McDonald]], [[Luther Vandross]] and [[Stevie Wonder]] as vocal style models.<ref name=stevehuey>{{cite web |last = Huey |first = Steve |url = http://www.allmusic.com/artist/toni-braxton-mn0000935330 |title = Toni Braxton&nbsp;\u2013 Music Biography, Credits and Discography |website = AllMusic |accessdate = July 29, 2012 }}</ref> [[Chaka Khan]] and [[Anita Baker]] were two of the few female singers that she could stylize. Steve Huey of [[AllMusic]] cites a key to Braxton's success is the versatility of her voice, which he states as being \"soulful enough for [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] audiences, but smooth enough for adult contemporary; sophisticated enough for adults, but sultry enough for younger listeners; strong enough in the face of heartbreak to appeal to women, but ravishing enough to nab the fellas.\"<ref name=stevehuey/>\n\nBraxton began her career singing traditional R&B and soft rock ballads and love songs on her debut and second albums. However, [[hip-hop soul]] and [[dance music]] elements begun to get spun into her sound on ''The Heat'',<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-heat-mw0000256509 |title = The Heat Review |website = [[AllMusic]] |accessdate = July 8, 2015 }}</ref> ''More Than a Woman'',<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/more-than-a-woman-mw0000224666 |title = More Than A Woman |website = [[AllMusic]] |accessdate = July 8, 2015 }}</ref> and ''Pulse''. She also showcased her classical training while performing in Broadway plays ''[[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' and ''[[Aida]]'' as well as her duet with [[Il Divo]], \"The Time of Our Lives\".\n\n== Legacy ==\n\nToni Braxton became an immediate R&B superstar after the release of her first album. LA Reid stated during an interview with [[VH1]]: \"We called her the first lady of LaFace. She was our Diva. [[Clive Davis|Clive]] had [[Whitney Houston|Whitney]], [[Tommy Mottola|Tommy]] had [[Mariah Carey|Mariah]] and we had Toni.\" BBC called the album \"spiritedly, mature soul at its best \u2013 and just urban enough to make it the bedroom album for the hip hop generation.\"<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/j4fd |title = Music \u2013 Review of Toni Braxton \u2013 Toni Braxton |publisher = BBC |date = July 13, 1993 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> Braxton had the sound of R&B greats like [[Anita Baker]] and the sex appeal to compete with fellow superstars [[Mariah Carey]] and [[Whitney Houston]]. Over the span of her career Braxton has sold over 66 million records,{{citation needed|date=October 2014}} including 40 million albums,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tonibraxton.com/bio/ |title=Toni Braxton Bio |publisher=Toni Braxton Official Website |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140727061235/http://www.tonibraxton.com/bio/ |archivedate=July 27, 2014 }}</ref> worldwide. Braxton's musical catalog contains many classics that have won her many accolades. Her greatest is \"[[Un-Break My Heart]]\", the [[Diane Warren]]-penned ballad that spent 11-weeks at number 1. Bob McCann, author of ''Encyclopedia of African American Actresses in Film and Television'' (2010), considered it \"simply one of the most haunting R&B records ever made.\" Reviewer Mark Edward Nero named it one of the best R&B break-up songs and considered it Braxton's \"finest moment\". He further commented, \"damn, this song is so sad it can make people cry for hours at a time.\" It's Braxton's ability to capture her audience that plays a factor in her continuous success.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}} Braxton is a recipient of seven [[Grammy Award]]s, seven [[American Music Awards]], and nine [[Billboard Music Awards]].{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n\nThroughout Braxton's career, she made several impacts on fashion mostly for her legendary high splits in her dresses. Her now-famous [[Richard Tyler (designer)|Richard Tyler]] white satin gown has gone down in history as one of the most revealing and sexiest dresses. In 2011, Braxton topped the list for the [[Grammy Award]]'s best dressed of the decade.<ref>{{cite news |author = |url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/grammy-fashion-the-best-and-worst-of-the-decade/ |title = Grammy Fashion: The Best and Worst of the Decade |publisher = CBS News |date = February 10, 2011 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> \"I've always gone a little risque with all my other award show outfits.\"<ref>{{cite magazine |url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/racy-grammy-dresses-419267#2-toni-braxton |title = Racy Grammy Dresses |magazine = Hollywood Reporter |date = February 8, 2013 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 |first = Emily |last = Helwig }}</ref> In 2012, Braxton made the list for [[VH1]]'s 50 Greatest Women in Music. Braxton's 2000 performance at [[Super Bowl XXXIV]] is ranked as one of the most memorable Super Bowl performances.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/02/the-super-bowl-top-5-memorable-halftime-shows/ |title = The Super Bowl: Top 5 Memorable Halftime Shows \u2013 ABC News |publisher = Abcnews.go.com |date = February 3, 2012 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> Braxton is featured alongside other R&B and pop divas as a primary character on the popular [[web series|web]] [[parody]] ''[[Got 2B Real: The Diva Variety Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Glazer|first=Eliot|url=https://www.vulture.com/2012/01/got-2-b-real.html|title=Behold the Newest Installment of \u2018Got 2 B Real,\u2019 a Web Series That Dubs Over the Voices of R&B Goddesses|website=Vulture.com}}</ref> Braxton cemented her diva status in the music industry in 2006, with her Las Vegas residency ''Toni Braxton: Revealed'', by becoming the first African American performer in Las Vegas to have her act enter the top ten Vegas shows charting.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}} Braxton also made headlines for her signature and legendary Giantto Million Dollar Microphone that she performed every show with. Braxton said: \"I think it's a great element to the show. You have to have a little sprinkle of [[Liberace]] and this is my little sprinkle of that.\" Braxton's famous prop was made up of white gold and encrusted with 650 karats of diamonds.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tmz.com/2006/09/01/braxtons-million-dollar-baby/ |title = Braxton's Million Dollar Baby |website=Tmz.com |date = January 9, 2006 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> The microphone reportedly cost $1 million.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n\n== Personal life ==\n===Relationships===\nBraxton met musician [[Keri Lewis]] when his group, [[Mint Condition]], opened for her on tour; they married on April 21, 2001. In 2001, she gave birth to their first child, a son named Denim Cole Braxton-Lewis. In 2002, while gearing up for the release of her fourth studio album, Braxton discovered she was pregnant with her second child; the complicated pregnancy confined her to [[bed rest]]. The couple's second son, Diezel Ky Braxton-Lewis, was born in March 2003. As Diezel has been diagnosed with [[autism]], Braxton has become involved with [[Autism Speaks]], serving as their International Spokesperson. In November 2009 Braxton announced that she and her husband had separated. The couple later divorced in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web |author = Zach Johnson |url = http://m.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/toni-braxton-finalizes-divorce-from-keri-lewis-2013257/ |title = Toni Braxton Finalizes Divorce From Keri Lewis |publisher = usmagazine.com |date = July 25, 2013 |accessdate = July 10, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn her early 30s, Braxton had an abortion after discovering she was pregnant with then-boyfriend Keri Lewis. In her memoir ''Unbreak my Heart'', Braxton discusses her abortion and guilt, saying that her son Diezel's autism was \"God's payback.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2014/05/toni-braxton-thinks-god-punished-her-for-getting-an-abortion-by-giving-her-son-autism/371518/|title=Toni Braxton Thinks God Punished Her for Getting an Abortion by Giving Her Son Autism|last=Jones|first=Allie|date=2014-05-23|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref>\n\nBraxton was dating rapper [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]] in May 2016, and the couple announced their engagement in February 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uk/news/914842/toni-braxton-confirms-engagement-to-birdman-see-her-massive-ring|title=Toni Braxton Confirms Engagement to Birdman: See Her Massive Ring|website=Eonline.com|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref> In January 2019, the couple have called off the engagement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-01-02-toni-braxton-birdman-call-of-engagement-its-over/|title=Toni Braxton & Birdman Call Off Engagement: 'It's Over'|last=Blakemore|first=Peyton|work=[[iHeartRadio]]|date=January 2, 2019|accessdate=January 9, 2019}}</ref> However, in April 2019, both Braxton and Birdman confirmed that they were still together.<ref>{{cite web |author = Danilo Castro |url = https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/04/toni-braxton-fiance-birdman-still-together/ |title = Are Toni Braxton & Fiance Birdman Still Together? |date= April 11, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nOn July 8, 2015, Braxton's attorney, Antavius Weems, announced that Braxton had settled her contentious child support case with her former husband, Keri Lewis.<ref>{{cite web |author = Ny Magee |url = http://www.eurweb.com/2015/07/toni-braxton-settles-child-support-battle-with-ex-husband/ |title = Toni Braxton Settles Child Support Battle with Ex-husband |publisher = eurweb.com |date = July 8, 2015 |accessdate = July 10, 2015 }}</ref> On June 2, 2016, the city and county officials of [[Atlanta, Georgia]], named June 2 as Toni Braxton Day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://raycornelius.com/2016/06/toni-braxton-honored-with-atls-phoenix-award-and-more-photos/|title=Toni Braxton honored with ATL\u2019s Phoenix Award and more! [PHOTOS]|website=Raycornelius.com|language=en-US|access-date=December 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Health problems ===\nAs of August 2007, rumors surfaced that she had been diagnosed with breast cancer. Braxton stated to ''[[Access Hollywood]]'', that the breast cancer rumors were false and that her health is in great condition. However, in 2008, she had a [[Benign tumor|benign]] lump removed from her breast. On April 8, 2008, near the end of her two-year run at the [[Flamingo Hotel]], Braxton was briefly hospitalized and the remaining dates on the show, which was scheduled to end on August 23, 2008, were cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.huliq.com/57437/toni-braxton-cancels-more-shows-due-unidentified-illness |accessdate = January 23, 2016 |work = Huliq |title = Toni Braxton Cancels More Shows Due to Unidentified Illness }}</ref> Later, while appearing on Season 7 of ''Dancing with the Stars'', she stated, that she has been diagnosed with [[Microangiopathy|microvascular angina]] (small vessel disease).<ref>{{cite web |url = http://abcnews.go.com/Health/HeartDiseaseNews/story?id=5870125 |accessdate = January 23, 2016 |date = September 24, 2008 |work = [[ABC News]] |publisher = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |first = Radha |last = Chitale |title = Dancing Won't Un-Break Toni Braxton's Heart }}</ref>\n\nOn November 18, 2010, Braxton admitted to [[CBS News]] that she had been diagnosed with [[systemic lupus erythematosus]] (SLE), a potentially life-threatening autoimmune disease.<ref name=\"Lupus\">{{cite web|url=http://heal-good.blogspot.com/2014/02/toni-braxton-is-fighter-of-lupus.html|accessdate=January 23, 2016|work=Heal Good|title=Toni Braxton is a fighter of Lupus}}</ref>\n\nBraxton's uncle died of complications from lupus.<ref name=\"Lupus\"/> While taping her reality series ''[[Braxton Family Values]]'', she went in for surgery. Braxton was hospitalized in Los Angeles in December 2012 because of \"minor health issues\" related to [[lupus]].<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1481514/toni-braxton-hospitalized-for-lupus-related-health-issues|accessdate=January 23, 2016|date=December 8, 2012|agency=Associated Press|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|title=Toni Braxton Hospitalized for Lupus-Related Health Issues}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Toni Braxton discography}} {{see also|The Braxtons discography}}\n\n;Studio albums \n* ''[[Toni Braxton (album)|Toni Braxton]]'' (1993)\n* ''[[Secrets (Toni Braxton album)|Secrets]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[Snowflakes (album)|Snowflakes]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[More Than a Woman (album)|More Than a Woman]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Libra (Toni Braxton album)|Libra]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Sex & Cigarettes]]'' (2018)\n\n;Collaboration albums \n* ''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' <small>(with [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]])</small> (2014)\n\n==Tours==\n'''Headlining'''\n* [[Secrets Tour]] (1996)\n* [[Libra Tour]] (2006)\n* [[2013 Summer Tour (Toni Braxton)|2013 Summer Tour]] (2013)\n* [[The Hits Tour]] (2016)\n* [[As Long As I Live Tour]] (2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Toni-Braxton-Announces-New-Studio-Album-SEX-AND-CIGARETTES-Out-March-23-20180212|title=Toni Braxton Announces New Studio Album SEX AND CIGARETTES Out March 23|website=Broadwayworld.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Residencies'''\n* ''[[Toni Braxton: Revealed]]'' (2006\u20132008)\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Toni Braxton}}\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Kingdom Come (2001 film)|Kingdom Come]]''\n| Juanita Slocumb\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Play'd: A Hip Hop Story]]''\n| Shonda\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Oogieloves in the Big Balloon Adventure]]''\n| Rosalie Rosebud\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Twist of Faith''\n| Nina Jones\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Toni Braxton: Unbreak My Heart]]''\n| Herself\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Faith Under Fire: The Antoinette Tuff Story''\n| [[Antoinette Tuff]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Every Day Is Christmas''\n| Alexis Taylor\n| Television film\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Roc (TV series)|Roc]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Concert\"\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Mad TV]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"6.10\"\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Blue's Clues]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Bluestock\"\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Kevin Hill]]''\n| Terry Knox\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\u2013present\n| ''[[Braxton Family Values]]''\n| Herself\n| Main role; 142 episodes\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Year\n! Artist\n! Notes\n|-\n| \"[[Miss You (Aaliyah song)|Miss You]]\"\n| 2002\n| [[Aaliyah]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Last Call\"\n| 2014\n| [[Traci Braxton]]\n|\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n\n{{Portal|Biography|Film|Music|Television}}\n\n* [[Honorific nicknames in popular music]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one in the United States]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one on the U.S. dance chart]]\n* [[List of best-selling music artists]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Toni Braxton}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p37576|label=Toni Braxton}}\n* {{IMDb name|4772}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{Amg name|285038}}\n\n{{Toni Braxton}}\n{{Toni Braxton singles}}\n{{The Braxtons}}\n{{Grammy Award for Best New Artist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Braxton, Toni}}\n[[Category:Toni Braxton| ]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Activists from California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Maryland]]\n[[Category:African-American activists]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American female singers]]\n[[Category:African-American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American pianists]]\n[[Category:African-American record producers]]\n[[Category:African-American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American television personalities]]\n[[Category:American women television personalities]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B singers]]\n[[Category:American contraltos]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American health activists]]\n[[Category:American hip hop dancers]]\n[[Category:American hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:American hip hop singers]]\n[[Category:American women record producers]]\n[[Category:American Methodists]]\n[[Category:American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American soul singers]]\n[[Category:American women activists]]\n[[Category:Arista Records artists]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Autism activists]]\n[[Category:Ballad musicians]]\n[[Category:Bowie State University alumni]]\n[[Category:The Braxtons members]]\n[[Category:Female dancers]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New jack swing musicians]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Severn, Maryland]]\n[[Category:People from the Las Vegas Valley]]\n[[Category:People with lupus]]\n[[Category:Singers from Maryland]]\n[[Category:Women hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:American female hip hop musicians]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American R&B singer-songwriter}}\n{{For|the singer's eponymous album|Toni Braxton (album)}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use American English|date=June 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Toni Braxton\n| image              = Toni Braxton press photo 2015.png\n| caption            = Braxton in 2015\n| birth_name         = Toni Michele Braxton<ref> https://books.google.com/books?id=ENoDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA166&lpg=PA166&dq=Toni+Michele+Braxton&source=bl&ots=4cMLhHF1f8&sig=ACfU3U0S6qUzS3c4cd4aD3YgEjYAn3VxUw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiJhMGkpMXnAhVMXq0KHdAPAaoQ6AEwFnoECAYQAQ#v=onepage&q=Toni%20Michele%20Braxton&f=false</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age  |1967|10|07}}\n| birth_place        = [[Severn, Maryland]], U.S.\n| occupation         = <!--Please do not add any more occupations to the list, it is long enough already-->{{hlist|Singer|songwriter|actress|record producer|television personality}}\n| years_active       = 1989\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Keri Lewis|2001|2013|reason=divorced}}\n| children           = 2\n| partner            = [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]] (fianc\u00e9)\n| relatives          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Traci Braxton]] (sister)\n* [[Trina Braxton]] (sister)\n* [[Towanda Braxton]] (sister)\n* [[Tamar Braxton]] (sister)\n}}\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Toni Braxton|Full list]]\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| instrument       = {{flat list |\n*Vocals \n*piano}}\n| background       = solo_singer\n| genre            = {{flat list |\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref name=stevehuey/><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.thewrap.com/lifetime-casts-its-toni-braxton-for-biopic/ |work = [[TheWrap]] |date = October 6, 2015 |accessdate = September 1, 2016 |title = Lifetime Finds Its Toni Braxton for Biopic |first = Joe |last = Otterson }}</ref>\n*[[soul music|soul]]\n*[[hip hop soul]]\n*[[soft rock]]\n*[[dance music|dance]]\n*[[pop music|pop]]}}\n| label            = {{hlist|[[LaFace Records|LaFace]] <small>(1992-2001)</small>\n\n[[Arista Records|Arista]] <small>(2001-2003)</small>\n\n[[Universal Music Group|Universal]]/[[Blackground Records|Blackground]] <small>(2003-2006)</small>\n\n[[Edel Records|Edel]] <small>(2005-2006)</small>\n\n[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] <small>(2008-2010)</small>\n\n[[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]] <small>(2017-2018)</small>\n\n[[Island Records]] <small>(2020-Present)</small>}}\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|[[The Braxtons]]|[[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]]|[[Antonio \"L.A.\" Reid]]}}\n| website          = {{url|http://www.tonibraxton.com|ToniBraxton.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Toni Michele Braxton''' (born October 7, 1967) is an American singer, songwriter, pianist, record producer, actress, television personality, and philanthropist. Braxton has sold over 67 million records worldwide, including 41 million albums. She is one of the highest-selling female [[R&B]] artists in history. Braxton has won seven Grammy Awards, nine [[Billboard Music Awards]], seven [[American Music Awards]], and numerous other accolades. In 2011, Braxton was inducted into the [[Georgia Music Hall of Fame]].\n\nIn the late 1980s, Braxton began performing with her sisters in a music group known as [[The Braxtons]]; the group was signed to [[Arista Records]]. After attracting the attention of producers [[Antonio \"L.A.\" Reid]] and [[Kenneth \"Babyface\" Edmonds]] and being signed to [[LaFace Records]], Braxton released her [[Toni Braxton (album)|self-titled debut studio album]] in 1993. The album reached number one on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart and sold 10 million copies worldwide. In addition, the singles \"[[Another Sad Love Song]]\" and \"[[Breathe Again]]\" became international successes. The album brought Braxton three [[Grammy Awards]], including the Grammy for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]].\n\nBraxton experienced continued success with the albums ''[[Secrets (Toni Braxton album)|Secrets]]'' (1996), which included the U.S. #1 hit singles \"[[You're Makin' Me High]]/[[Let It Flow (song)|Let It Flow]]\" and \"[[Un-Break My Heart]]\"; and ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]'' (2000), which opened at #2 on the ''Billboard'' 200 and included the U.S. #2 hit single \"[[He Wasn't Man Enough]]\". Braxton's subsequent studio albums, ''[[More Than a Woman (album)|More Than a Woman]]'' (2002), ''[[Libra (Toni Braxton album)|Libra]]'' (2005) and ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]'' (2010), were released amid contractual disputes and health issues. In 2014, Braxton and longtime collaborator [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]] released a duet album entitled ''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' that earned the duo a Grammy Award for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Album|Best R&B Album]] in 2015. In 2018, Braxton released her ninth studio album, ''[[Sex & Cigarettes]]''.\n\nBraxton is also a television executive producer and personality. She competed in the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 7)|seventh season]] of the reality competition series ''[[Dancing with the Stars]]''. She has executive produced and starred in ''[[Braxton Family Values]]'', a reality television series that has aired on [[We TV]] since 2011. Braxton is also an executive producer of  ''[[Tamar & Vince]]'', a spinoff reality TV series starring her younger sister, Tamar.\n\n==Early life==\nToni Michelle Braxton was born in [[Severn, Maryland]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ollison|first1=Rashod D.|title=Toni Braxton's back, with a pretty 'Please'|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2005-09-25/news/0509270511_1_toni-braxton-libra-albums|accessdate=November 15, 2015|newspaper=[[The Baltimore Sun]]|date=September 25, 2005}}</ref> on October 7, 1967.<ref>{{cite news|last=Taylor|first=Derrick Bryson|title=Happy 45th Birthday, Toni Braxton!|url=http://www.essence.com/2012/10/07/happy-45th-birthday-toni-braxton|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]|date=October 7, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/10/07/toni-braxton-celebrates-46th-birthday-_n_1945819.html|title=PHOTOS: Toni Blows Out The Candles For Her 46th Birthday|date=October 7, 2012|website=The Huffington Post|access-date=June 30, 2016}}</ref> Her father, Michael Conrad Braxton Sr., was a [[Methodist]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adherents.com/largecom/fam_meth.html|title=Famous Methodists|website=Adherents.com|accessdate=November 12, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Jet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=I7sDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA21|accessdate=December 2, 2013|date=June 20, 1994|publisher=Johnson Publishing Company|page=21|issn=0021-5996}}</ref> clergyman and power company worker, and her mother, Evelyn Jackson, a native of [[South Carolina]], was a former opera singer and cosmetologist, as well as a pastor.<ref>{{cite news|last=Dougherty|first=Steve|title=Greener Pastures|url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20132603,00.html|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=October 9, 2000}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Braxton Family Values \u2013 Evelyn Braxton|url=http://www.wetv.com/shows/braxton-family-values/cast/evelyn-braxton|website=Wetv.com|accessdate=December 2, 2013}}</ref> Braxton's maternal grandfather was also a pastor.<ref>{{cite news|last=Ney|first=Angela Winter|title=Award-winning pastor reaches out to teen-agers|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/1994-02-06/news/1994037080_1_toni-braxton-inside-the-church-award|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=The Baltimore Sun|date=February 6, 1994}}</ref>\n\nBraxton is the eldest of six siblings.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Rizzo|first1=Monica|title=Toni Braxton: Still Dancing|journal=People|date=October 27, 2008|volume=70|issue=17|url= http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20238199,00.html|accessdate=November 15, 2015}}</ref> She has a younger brother Michael Jr. (born 1968) and four younger sisters [[Traci Braxton|Traci Renee]] (born 1971), [[Towanda Braxton|Towanda Chloe]] (born 1973), [[Trina Braxton|Trina Evette]] (born 1974), and [[Tamar Braxton|Tamar Estine]] (born 1977). They were raised in a strict religious household,<ref name=\"psu\">{{cite web|url=http://www.premiumseatsusa.com/concert/Toni-Braxton|title=Toni Braxton Tickets|accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=Premium Seats USA}}</ref> and Braxton's first performing experience was singing in her church choir.<ref name=\"psu\"/>\n\nBraxton attended [[Bowie State University]] to obtain a teaching degree,<ref>{{Cite news|first=Joy Bennett|last=Kinnon|title=The Rise and Fall and Rise of Toni Braxton|work=Ebony|date=December 2000}}</ref> but decided to sing professionally after she was discovered by William E. Pettaway Jr., who reportedly heard her singing to herself while pumping gas.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Morgan|last=Joan|title=Fully Exposed|work=Vibe|date=December 2002|quote=One day in 1990, songwriter Bill Pettaway heard Toni singing to herself at an Annapolis gas station, liked what he heard, and got her an audition with L.A.}}</ref>\n\nOn her appearance May 24, 2014 broadcast of [[NPR]]'s ''[[Wait Wait... Don't Tell Me!]]'', she stated that she was not singing to herself at the gas station. Pettaway, working as an attendant at the [[Annapolis]] service station where she was refueling, recognized her from local performances and introduced himself, saying he wanted to produce her. Although skeptical, Braxton decided to, in her words, \"take a chance\" and accepted.<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.npr.org/programs/wait-wait-dont-tell-me/315248388/wait-wait-dont-tell-me-for-may-24-2014|title=\"Wait, Wait, Don't Tell Me! For May 24, 2014\"|website=Npr.org|accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===1989\u20131995: The Braxtons, ''Toni Braxton'' and breakthrough===\n{{Main|The Braxtons}}\nBraxton and her four sisters (Traci, Towanda, Trina, and Tamar) began performing as [[The Braxtons]] in the late 1980s and were signed to [[Arista Records]] in 1989. Their first single, \"[[Good Life (The Braxtons song)|Good Life]]\", was released in 1990.<ref name=\"vibe\">{{cite web |url = http://www.vibe.com/music/search/artist.html?id=UCAgICAzNzU3Ng |title = Toni Braxton |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = VIBE.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071112190035/http://www.vibe.com/music/search/artist.html?id=UCAgICAzNzU3Ng |archivedate = November 12, 2007 }}</ref> Though the song was not successful, it attracted the attention of [[Antonio \"L.A.\" Reid]] and [[Kenneth \"Babyface\" Edmonds]].<ref name=\"vibe\"/>\n\nReid and Babyface recruited her to record a demo of \"Love Shoulda Brought You Home\", a song that they had written for Anita Baker for the soundtrack of [[Eddie Murphy]]'s film, ''[[Boomerang (1992 film)|Boomerang]]''. Baker, who was pregnant at the time,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://uk.askmen.com/women/singer/8c_toni_braxton.html |title = Toni Braxton |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = AskMen |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070930181638/http://uk.askmen.com/women/singer/8c_toni_braxton.html |archive-date = September 30, 2007 |url-status=dead |df = mdy-all }}</ref> did not record the song but suggested that Braxton record it. Her recording was later included on the soundtrack along with \"[[Give U My Heart]]\", a duet by Braxton and Babyface. Braxton, meanwhile, was signed to Reid and Edmonds' Arista-distributed imprint, [[LaFace Records]], and immediately began recording her solo debut album.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nOn July 13, 1993, LaFace Records released Braxton's self-titled debut album, ''[[Toni Braxton (album)|Toni Braxton]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Toni-Braxton/dp/B0000013G5|title=''Toni Braxton'': Music: Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Amazon.com}}</ref> The album, which was primarily produced by Reid, [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]], and [[Daryl Simmons]], peaked at number one on the U.S. [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] albums chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=30331&aid=146011|title=Discography&nbsp;\u2013 Toni Braxton \u2013 ''Toni Braxton''|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Billboard.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929141413/http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?pid=30331&aid=146011|archivedate=September 29, 2007}}</ref> The first single, \"[[Another Sad Love Song]]\", peaked at number seven and number two on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] and [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Singles & Tracks|R&B Singles]] charts respectively. The song was also the very first #1 song on the newly created Adult R&B Charts. Billboard created the chart in September 1993.<ref name=\"billboard singles\">{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=30331&model.vnuAlbumId=146011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929211922/http://billboard.com/bbcom/retrieve_chart_history.do?model.vnuArtistId=30331&model.vnuAlbumId=146011|url-status=dead|archive-date=September 29, 2007|title=Artist Chart History&nbsp;\u2013 Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Billboard.com}}</ref> The album's second single, \"[[Breathe Again]]\", peaked in the top five of both the Hot 100 and R&B singles charts<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/> and no 2 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com|title=UK Top 40 Chart Archive, British Singles & Album Charts|website=Everyhit.com|date=March 16, 2000|accessdate=January 16, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702234638/http://www.everyhit.com/|archivedate=July 2, 2007}}</ref> More singles from ''Toni Braxton'' were released in 1994, including \"[[You Mean the World to Me (Toni Braxton song)|You Mean the World to Me]]\", \"[[Seven Whole Days]]\", and \"[[I Belong to You/How Many Ways]]\".<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/>\n\nBraxton's debut album won her several awards, including three [[Grammy Award]]s (for [[Grammy Award for Best New Artist|Best New Artist]] and two consecutive awards for [[Grammy Award for Best Female R&B Vocal Performance|Best Female R&B Vocal Performance]] in 1994 and 1995).<ref name=\"YTV\">{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/toni-braxton/contributor/38261/awards|title=Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 26, 2006|work=Yahoo! TV|date=March 14, 2003}}</ref> She won two [[American Music Award]]s (for Favorite Soul/R&B New Artist and Favorite New Adult Contemporary Artist)<ref name=\"YTV\"/> in 1994 and another one in 1995 (for Favorite Soul/R&B Album).<ref name=\"YTV\"/> ''Toni Braxton'' was certified 8x platinum in USA and has sales of over 10 million worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaa.com/gp/bestsellers/topalbums.asp|title=Gold&Platinum: Top 100 albums|accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=RIAA|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061214122646/http://www.riaa.com/gp/bestsellers/topalbums.asp|archivedate=December 14, 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"books.google.com\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ArUDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA56&dq=toni+braxton+sold&hl=pt-BR&ei=kBKETJGqLoP98Ab5vb2aAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=toni%20braxton%20sold&f=false|title=Jet&nbsp;\u2013 Google Livros|website=Books.google.com|date=July 17, 2000|accessdate=November 12, 2010}}</ref>\n\n===1996\u20131999: ''Secrets'' and financial issues===\nIn June 1996, Braxton released her second and most successful album, ''[[Secrets (Toni Braxton album)|Secrets]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0000013GH|title=''Secrets'': Music: Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Amazon.com}}</ref> Braxton said of the album: \"The motivation for this album was to include a little bit of everything. Our aim was to come up with material, that would have a familiar 'feel' to the people, who bought the first album without being musically redundant.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rockonthenet.com/artists-b/tonibraxton_main.htm|title=Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=Rock on the Net}}</ref> Along with Babyface, Braxton also worked with [[R. Kelly]], [[Tony Rich]], and [[David Foster]] on the album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artistdirect.com/nad/store/artist/album/0,,230175,00.html?src=search#credits|title=Toni Braxton: ''Secrets'' |accessdate=December 18, 2006|work=ArtistDirect}}</ref> Braxton co-produced the album and co-wrote two of its songs, including the 1997 single \"How Could an Angel Break My Heart\", which was also later included on ''Diana Princess of Wales Tribute,'' a [[Princess Diana]] memorial album.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/dp/B000002C4U|title=''Diana Princess of Wales Tribute''|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Amazon.com}}</ref>\n\nWith help from the album's first single, \"[[You're Makin' Me High]]\", which became Braxton's first number-one hit on the Hot 100 singles chart,<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/> the album peaked at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?JSESSIONID=FHJ2kFF9nFq0gg5KtPxXY8nGJ2sqxnQLL1brcY1T26XLrc1Q1lcF!-1562377538&pid=30331&aid=185866|title=Discography&nbsp;\u2013 Toni Braxton \u2013 ''Secrets''|accessdate=December 18, 2006|website=Billboard.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929141203/http://billboard.com/bbcom/discography/index.jsp?JSESSIONID=FHJ2kFF9nFq0gg5KtPxXY8nGJ2sqxnQLL1brcY1T26XLrc1Q1lcF%21-1562377538&pid=30331&aid=185866|archivedate=September 29, 2007|url-status=dead}}</ref> \"You're Makin' Me High\" also topped the R&B singles chart for two weeks<ref name=\"billboard singles\"/> and saw similar success in Europe and Asia.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nThe album's second single, \"[[Un-Break My Heart]]\", written and composed by [[Diane Warren]], became the biggest hit of Braxton's career, spending 11 consecutive weeks at number one on the Hot 100<ref name=\"vibe\"/> and also topping the [[Hot Dance Singles Sales]] chart for eleven weeks and the [[Hot Dance Music/Club Play]] chart for four weeks.<ref name=\"mfc\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musicfanclubs.org/tonibraxton/timeline.htm|title=Toni Braxton|accessdate=December 26, 2006|work=Music Fan Clubs}}</ref> as well as reaching no 2 in the UK<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.everyhit.com|title=UK Top 40 Chart Archive, British Singles & Album Charts|website=Everyhit.com|date=March 16, 2000|accessdate=February 1, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702234638/http://www.everyhit.com/|archivedate=July 2, 2007}}</ref>\n\nOther singles from the album included the double A-side \"[[I Don't Want To]]\"/\"[[I Love Me Some Him]]\" (which peaked at number one on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart)<ref name=\"billboard singles\" /> and \"How Could an Angel Break My Heart;\" this last featured [[Kenny G]], with whom Braxton later toured.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://livedesignonline.com/mag/lighting_kenny_toni_lds |title = Kenny G and Toni B: Lds Valerie Groth and Justin Collie manipulate one lighting system to create two shows |accessdate = December 26, 2006 |work = Live Design |date = May 1, 1997 }}</ref> After 92 weeks in the charts, ''Secrets'' was certified 8x platinum, becoming Braxton's second straight 8 million-seller. Internationally, ''Secrets'' sold more than 15 million copies, thus cementing Braxton's superstar status.<ref name=\"books.google.com\" /> Braxton topped the ''Billboard'' Year-End Charts as the Top Hot 100 Singles Artist&nbsp;\u2013 Female,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://billboard.com/bbcom/charts/yearend_chart_display.jsp?f=The+Billboard+Hot+100&g=Year-end+Singles&year=1997 |title=Year End Charts&nbsp;\u2013 Year-end Singles&nbsp;\u2013 The Billboard Hot 100 |accessdate=December 26, 2006 |website=Billboard.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061224112647/http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/charts/yearend_chart_display.jsp?f=The+Billboard+Hot+100&g=Year-end+Singles&year=1997 |archivedate=December 24, 2006 }}</ref> Top R&B Artist&nbsp;\u2013 Female (singles and albums),<ref name=\"mfc\" /> Top Hot R&B Singles Artist&nbsp;\u2013 Female,<ref name=\"mfc\" /> Top Hot Dance Club Play Artist, and Top Hot Adult Contemporary Artist, while \"Un-Break My Heart\" became the Top Hot Dance Club Play Single and the Top Hot Adult Contemporary Track of the year. She won two Grammy Awards; one for [[Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Performance|Best Female Pop Vocal Performance]]<ref name=\"YTV\" /> for \"Un-Break My Heart\" and Best Female R&B Vocal Performance for \"You're Makin' Me High\" as well as two [[American Music Award]]s for Favorite Female Soul/R&B Artist and Favorite Soul/R&B Album.<ref name=\"YTV\" />\n\nBy 1996, Braxton had sold more than 20 million records; unfortunately, she was still waiting on her financial rewards, eventually launching an unsuccessful lawsuit against Arista and LaFace Records. Soon after, she filed for chapter 7 bankruptcy. Public reaction to these events was very harsh, having been expressed most clearly in an interview on ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]].''<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ftLjr4CQcrQ |title = \"She was so frickin' mean to me\": Toni Braxton's Original Full Interview with Oprah (1998) |publisher = YouTube |date = March 29, 2013 |accessdate = July 8, 2015 }}</ref> Upon successfully filing for bankruptcy, Braxton relinquished the rights to many of her valued possessions, including the Grammys and American Music Awards she had previously been granted.{{citation needed|date=September 2017}}\n\nBraxton has appeared in two [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] shows: She made her Broadway debut as Belle in ''[[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' beginning September 9, 1998 when she replaced Kim Huber.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/40798-Braxton-Taylor-Barbour-Beast-to-Be-Unveiled-Sept-9-New-Menken-Song-to-Follow |title=Braxton-Taylor-Barbour Beast to Be Unveiled Sept. 9; New Menken Song to Follow |accessdate=June 27, 2010 |work=playbill |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144402/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/40798-Braxton-Taylor-Barbour-Beast-to-Be-Unveiled-Sept-9-New-Menken-Song-to-Follow |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> During her run in the show [[Alan Menken]] wrote and composed a new song for the musical, titled \"A Change in Me\", which he specially wrote and composed for Braxton, and was still being used in the musical as of late July 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/41311-Toni-Braxton-Premieres-Beauty-s-New-Song-Oct-7-On-Rosie |title=Toni Braxton Premieres Beauty's New Song, Oct. 7 On 'Rosie' |website=Playbill.com |date= |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144507/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/41311-Toni-Braxton-Premieres-Beauty-s-New-Song-Oct-7-On-Rosie |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> She left the production on February 28, 1999 and was succeeded by [[Andrea McArdle]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/43273-Bways-Beauty-Turns-2000-Sat-Matinee-Jan-30-McArdle-Arrives-March-3 |title=Bway's Beauty Turns 2,000 Sat. Matinee Jan. 30; McArdle Arrives March 3 |website=Playbill.com |date= |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144741/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/43273-Bways-Beauty-Turns-2000-Sat-Matinee-Jan-30-McArdle-Arrives-March-3 |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> Her role in ''Beauty and the Beast'' marked the first (and only) time a black woman commanded the leading role of Belle on Broadway. (In the UK, [[Michelle Gayle]] played the role in the West End.) It also marked the first time a black woman would star in a Disney musical on Broadway. In 1999, the lawsuit against LaFace Records was settled and Braxton was given back all her possessions, giving her time to record ''The Heat'', her first album in four years.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.lifetimetv.com/shows/ip/portraits/0223/0223_bio.html |title = Toni Braxton |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = Lifetime's intimate portrait |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20051205012041/http://www.lifetimetv.com/shows/ip/portraits/0223/0223_bio.html |archivedate = December 5, 2005 }}</ref>\n\n===2000\u20132001: ''The Heat'' and acting debut===\nAfter Braxton's three-year-long dispute with LaFace and Arista had been settled, Toni signed a new $20 million contract. In March 2000, LaFace Records released \"[[He Wasn't Man Enough]]\", the first single from Braxton's third studio album, ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]''. By June 2000, the song peaked at number two on the Hot 100 chart and No. 1 on the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop chart. ''The Heat'' was released on April 25, 2000, debuting at number two on the ''Billboard'' 200 albums chart with first-week sales of 194,448 copies sold,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitsdailydouble.com/sales/archcht.cgi?cht692|title=Previous Album Sales Chart|publisher=HITS Daily Double|accessdate=November 12, 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120908231013/http://www.hitsdailydouble.com/sales/archcht.cgi?cht692|archivedate=September 8, 2012}}</ref> it remained in the top 20 for fifteen consecutive weeks. Braxton again worked with producers Babyface and Foster; also included in the staple were [[Rodney Jerkins]], and new beau musician [[Keri Lewis]].\n\nBraxton took a more hands-on approach, co-writing and co-producing a handful of the tracks. One selection on ''The Heat'', titled \"Gimme Some\", featured a rap verse from [[TLC (group)|TLC]] star [[Lisa \"Left Eye\" Lopes]]. The album's second single, \"[[Just Be a Man About It]]\", peaked at number 32 on the Hot 100 and number six on the R&B Charts. The third single, \"[[Spanish Guitar (song)|Spanish Guitar]]\", peaked at number 98 on the Hot 100 and number one on the Hot Dance & Club charts. The fourth single, \"Maybe\", peaked at 74 on the R&B charts. ''The Heat'' was certified double platinum in the U.S. and, by 2002, had sold over 4 million copies worldwide.<ref name=\"books.google.com\"/><ref name=vibe2002>{{cite book|title=Vibe Magazine|url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_uyUEAAAAMBAJ|quote=THE HEAT.|work=[[Vibe Magazine]]|publisher=[[Internet Archive]]|accessdate=May 24, 2014}}</ref>\n\n''The Heat'' was nominated for many awards. At the [[43rd Annual Grammy Awards]], the album's lead single, \"He Wasn't Man Enough\", was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Song|Best R&B Song]] and eventually won a [[Grammy Award for Best Female R&B Vocal Performance]], while the album itself was nominated for [[Grammy Award for Best R&B Album|Best R&B Album]].<ref name=rockonthenet>{{cite web|title=Rock on the Net: Toni Braxton|url=http://www.rockonthenet.com/artists-b/tonibraxton_main.htm|work=Rock on the Net|accessdate=May 24, 2014}}</ref> She was also nominated for [[Soul Train Music Award for Best R&B/Soul Album, Female|Best R&B/Soul album, Female]] on the [[Soul Train Music Awards]],<ref name=rockonthenet/> but she lost to \"[[Who Is Jill Scott? Words and Sounds Vol. 1]]\" by [[Jill Scott]]. She won 2 [[American Music Awards]] for [[American Music Award for Favorite Soul/R&B Female Artist|Favorite Soul/R&B Female Artist]] and [[American Music Award for Favorite Soul/R&B Album|Favorite Soul/R&B Album]] (''The Heat'').<ref name=rockonthenet/>\n\nIn 2001, she made her movie acting debut in the feature film ''[[Kingdom Come (2001 film)|Kingdom Come]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imdb.com/title/tt0246002|title=Kingdom Come|accessdate=December 19, 2006|website=IMDb.com}} {{better source|date=November 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== 2002\u20132005: ''More Than a Woman'' and ''Libra'' ===\n\nIn 2002, while gearing up for the release of her fourth studio album, Braxton discovered she was pregnant with her second child. Knowing that she would be unable to promote the album properly, she unsuccessfully lobbied [[Arista Records]] to get the label to postpone its release until after she was to give birth. [[Arista Records]] refused, and the album was released as planned. It received very little promotion from either Arista or Braxton herself, due in Braxton's case to the complicated pregnancy that had confined her to [[bed rest]]. Braxton accused the company of being unwilling to compromise and punishing her for not putting her career over family.{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nIn November 2002, Braxton's fourth studio album ''[[More Than a Woman (album)|More Than a Woman]]'' was released. Opening to an instant commercial disappointment, the album peaked at number 13. The first single, [[The Neptunes]] -produced \"[[Hit the Freeway]]\", failed at radio and peaked at number 86 on the Hot 100. The two singles, that followed (\"A Better Man\", \"Lies, Lies, Lies\") were scrapped, failed to make a dent and missed the Hot 100 completely. ''More Than a Woman'' was certified gold by [[RIAA]] and sold more than 800,000 copies worldwide.<ref name=\"musicmp3.ru\">{{cite web |url = http://musicmp3.ru/artist_toni-braxton.html |title = Toni Braxton mp3 music download |publisher = MusicMp3.Ru |date = |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref> Prior to the release of the album, a dispute erupted between Braxton and [[Irv Gotti]], when he played a rough cut of \"No More Love\", a song that he produced for the album, that was to be the first single. Disapproving of Gotti broadcasting the unfinished track, Braxton withheld it from being released. The same year, Braxton was further annoyed, when [[Jay-Z]] used the same sample of [[Tupac Shakur|2Pac]]'s \"Me and My Girlfriend\", that she had already used on her track \"Me & My Boyfriend\" for his and Beyonc\u00e9's \"[['03 Bonnie & Clyde]]\".{{citation needed|date=January 2018}}\n\nIn April 2003, Braxton abruptly left Arista Records, having been there for 14 years, and immediately signed with [[Blackground Records]], headed by [[Barry Hankerson]], her manager at the time. She then starred in ''[[Aida (musical)|Aida]]'' as Aida beginning June 30, 2003 when she replaced [[Simone (actress)|Simone]]<ref>{{cite web |url = http://music.yahoo.com/read/news/12037443 |title = Toni Braxton Set To Return To Broadway |accessdate = December 19, 2006 |work = Yahoo! Music |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070612053315/http://music.yahoo.com/read/news/12037443 |archivedate = June 12, 2007 }}</ref> and left the cast on November 16, 2003 where she was replaced by [[Michelle Williams (singer)|Michelle Williams]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/82297-Its-Destiny-RB-Singer-Michelle-Williams-to-Replace-Toni-Braxton-in-Aida |title=It's Destiny: R&B Singer Michelle Williams to Replace Toni Braxton in Aida |website=Playbill.com |date= |accessdate=January 16, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016144804/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/82297-Its-Destiny-RB-Singer-Michelle-Williams-to-Replace-Toni-Braxton-in-Aida |archivedate=October 16, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nShe was to star in a half-hour sitcom pilot where she would play a version of herself for [[The WB Television Network]]'s fall 2006\u201307 lineup, though plans to put the show into full-production fell through once The WB announced it would cease to exist in fall 2006.<ref>{{cite web |title = Development Update: September 29\u201330 |url = http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2004/09/30/development-update-september-29-30-17006/6747/ |work = The Futon Critic |accessdate = November 6, 2013 |date = September 30, 2004 }}</ref> She has also starred in the TV sitcom, ''Kevin Hill''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.contactmusic.com/new/xmlfeed.nsf/mndwebpages/toni.s%20tv%20deal |title = Toni's TV Deal |accessdate = January 24, 2007 |work = Contact Music |date = September 20, 2004 }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2005, Braxton's new label, Blackground/Universal, released \"[[Please (Toni Braxton song)|Please]]\", the first single from her fifth album, ''[[Libra (Toni Braxton album)|Libra]]''. The album was originally planned for a June release, but it was pushed back several times and was finally issued on September 27. Unfortunately for Braxton, her troubles with weak album promotion and lack of label commitment were not over. \"Please\" peaked at number 36 on ''Billboard'' Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs, while altogether missing the Hot 100.\n\n''Libra'' still managed to debut at number four on the ''Billboard'' 200 selling 114,593 copies in the first week. ''Libra'' also peaked at number two on the Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums. Although that is strong for an album with little to no promotion, it became yet another commercial disappointment for Braxton. The album's second single, \"[[Trippin' (That's the Way Love Works)]]\", received less airplay and peaked at number 67 on the R&B chart. The failure was ascribed to the non-video presence of the single and lack of label support. The album was certified gold in late 2005 and has since sold 679,000 copies worldwide.<ref name=\"musicmp3.ru\" />\n\n=== 2006\u20132007: ''Toni Braxton: Revealed'' and label conflicts ===\n\nBraxton recorded a song in 2006 with [[Il Divo]], titled \"[[The Time of Our Lives (Il Divo and Toni Braxton song)|The Time of Our Lives]]\". The song was used as the official [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] anthem and was performed at the opening ceremony in [[Berlin]], Germany, on June 9. The song was also performed at the closing ceremonies making Braxton and Il Divo the first artists to be asked to perform for the opening and closing ceremonies.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/tm_objectid=16862049&method=full&siteid=94762&headline=fiona--divo--name_page.html |title = Fiona: divo |accessdate = December 18, 2006 |work = Mirror.co.uk }}</ref>\n\nBraxton made an appearance on the season finale of ''[[American Idol (season 5)|American Idol 5]]'', where she performed [[Elvis Presley]]'s \"[[In the Ghetto]]\" with soon-to-be winner [[Taylor Hicks]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1532468/20060524/hicks__taylor.jhtml |title = Soul Patrol Rides On: Taylor Hicks Wins 'American Idol' |accessdate = December 27, 2006 |work = MTV News |date = May 25, 2006 }}</ref>\n\nOn May 19, 2006, the [[Flamingo Las Vegas|Flamingo Hotel and Casino]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada|Las Vegas]] announced that Braxton would replace [[Wayne Newton]] as the casino's new headlining act from August 3, 2006.<ref>{{cite news |title = Toni Braxton to be headliner at Flamingo Las Vegas to 2007 |url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/travel/hotels/2006-05-19-braxtons-back_x.htm |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[USA Today]] |date = May 19, 2006 |agency = Associated Press }}</ref> The show, entitled [[Toni Braxton: Revealed]], was to be performed six nights a week and was scheduled to run through to March 2007. Braxton later confirmed that she was extending her show through to August 2007. Due to its success, it was reported that Braxton would extend her show through to August 2008. The show was later cancelled in order for Braxton to focus on her health.<ref>{{cite news |last = Mascia |first = Kristen |title = Toni Braxton Cancels Vegas Show |url = http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20203349,00.html |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = People |date = May 30, 2008 }}</ref>\n\nIn an October 2006 concert at the [[Flamingo Las Vegas]], Braxton broke down in tears while announcing to the audience that just before the concert began she had been told that her son, Diezel, had been diagnosed with [[autism]].<ref>{{cite news |last = Walls |first = Jeannette |title = O.J. Simpson to confess \u2013 hypothetically, Plus: Toni Braxton sobs while discussing autistic son |url = http://www.today.com/id/15066202 |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Today.com]] |date = October 30, 2006 }}</ref> Braxton has been outspoken regarding her doctor's failure to diagnose Diezel's condition earlier, contending that if he had been diagnosed earlier he could have received treatment earlier.<ref>{{cite news |title = Braxton Upset With Doctor's Over Son's Autism |url = http://www.contactmusic.com/news/braxton-upset-with-doctors-over-sons-autism_1009575 |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Contactmusic.com]] |date = September 29, 2006 }}</ref> As well as becoming a spokeswoman for [[Autism Speaks]],<ref>{{cite news |title = Toni Braxton Named National Celebrity Spokesperson for Autism Speaks |url = http://www.autismspeaks.org/about-us/press-releases/toni-braxton-named-national-celebrity-spokesperson-autism-speaks |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Autism Speaks]] |date = March 7, 2007 }}</ref> she is also a spokeswoman for the [[American Heart Association]].\n\nOn January 12, 2007, Braxton filed a lawsuit in the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York]] against her former manager Barry Hankerson for $10 million, alleging \"fraud, deception and double dealing\", in addition to mismanaging her relationship with Arista Records.<ref name=tbmgr>{{cite news |last = Neumeister |first = Larry |title = Toni Braxton Sues Her Former Manager |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2007/01/12/AR2007011201814.html |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[The Washington Post]] |date = January 12, 2007 |agency = AP }}</ref> According to Braxton's lawsuit, Hankerson placed his personal financial interests ahead of hers by using 'double-talk' to compromise the relationship between Braxton and her former recording label, [[Arista Records]], with Hankerson allegedly telling Arista that \"Braxton no longer wanted to record for Arista\", and telling Braxton that \"Arista was not interested in working with her anymore\".<ref name=tbmgr />\n\nThe suit was settled with Braxton being forced to return a $375,000 advance to Hankerson, who would also receive a percentage of the sales of her next album, and Hankerson releasing Braxton from her contract with him. The settlement also temporarily limited the companies with which Braxton can sign.<ref>{{cite news |title = Braxton Settles Lawsuit Against Ex-Manager |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1054986/braxton-settles-lawsuit-against-ex-manager |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = Billboard |date = February 14, 2007 |agency = AP }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = https://news.yahoo.com/s/ap/20070113/ap_on_en_mu/braxton_lawsuit_2 |title = Toni Braxton sues her former manager |accessdate = January 12, 2007 |work = Yahoo |date = January 12, 2007 }}{{Dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> Hankerson claimed that the problems initially arose due to a number of disputes with Braxton and her wish to include her husband in her music.<ref>{{cite news |last = Finn |first = Natalie |title = Braxton Settles Up with Ex-Manager |url = http://au.eonline.com/news/54395/braxton-settles-up-with-ex-manager |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[E! Online]] |date = February 13, 2007 }}</ref>\n\n=== 2008\u20132010: ''Pulse'' and television ===\nBraxton appeared on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 7)|seventh season]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''; her partner was [[Alec Mazo]].<ref>{{Cite news |title = Announcing the Stars |url = http://abc.go.com/primetime/dancingwiththestars/index?pn=announcement |work = abc.go.com |year = 2008 |accessdate = September 16, 2008 }}</ref> They were voted off in the fifth week of the competition.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"float:left;\"\n|-  style=\"text-align:Center; background:#ccc;\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Week'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Dance/Song'''\n| colspan=\"3\"|'''Judges' score'''\n| rowspan=\"2\"|'''Result'''\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#ccc;\"\n|  style=\"width:10%; \"|Inaba\n|  style=\"width:10%; \"|Goodman\n|  style=\"width:10%; \"|Tonioli\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|1A\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|[[cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]]/ \"[[Smooth (song)|Smooth]]\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|7\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|7\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|8\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|Safe\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|1B\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|[[Quickstep]]/ \"[[Blue Skies (1926 song)|Blue Skies]]\"\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|8\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|7\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|8\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"|Last to Be Called Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||2\n||[[Rhumba|Rumba]]/ \"[[I Can't Make You Love Me]]\"\n||7\n||8\n||8\n||Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||3\n||[[Viennese Waltz]]/ \"[[F\u00fcr Elise]]\"\n||8\n||7\n||7\n||Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||4\n||[[Samba]]/ \"De Donde Soy\"\n||7\n||7\n||8\n||Safe\n|-  style=\"text-align:center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n||5\n||[[West Coast Swing]]/ \"[[The Way You Make Me Feel]]\"\n||7\n||7\n||8\n||Eliminated\n|}{{Clear}}\n\n[[File:Toni Braxton 2009 VH1 Divas.jpg|thumb|Braxton at the 2009 VH1 Divas Red Carpet]]\n\nIn October 2008 Braxton signed to [[Atlantic Records]]. The DJ Frank E produced song \"[[Yesterday (Toni Braxton song)|Yesterday]]\" premiered on September 11, 2009 and features [[Trey Songz]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.essence.com/news_entertainment/entertainment/articles/listen_to_toni_braxtons_new_single_yesterday |title = Exclusive: Be the First to Listen to Toni Braxton's New Single 'Yesterday' |accessdate = September 12, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090914055322/http://www.essence.com/news_entertainment/entertainment/articles/listen_to_toni_braxtons_new_single_yesterday |archivedate = September 14, 2009 }}</ref> It was released as the lead single from her sixth studio album ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/960751/toni-braxton-pulse-album-preview |title = Toni Braxton \"Pulse\" Album Preview |magazine = Billboard |accessdate = June 29, 2013 }}</ref> \"Yesterday\" peaked at No. 12 on the U.S. ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]] chart making it her highest chart performance since her 2000 single \"[[Just Be a Man About It]]\", which peaked at No. 6. The single has been released worldwide on May 3, 2010.<ref>{{cite web |author=Praxis Media |url=http://www.radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_singles.htm |title=Radio1 Rodos Greece ::: UK Forthcoming Singles ::: Charts, DJ Promos, Dance, Lyrics, Free Mp3 Samples Downloads |website=Radio1.gr |date= |accessdate=November 12, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121122103050/http://radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_singles.htm |archivedate=November 22, 2012 |df=mdy }}</ref> In the UK, \"Yesterday\" became Braxton's first hit single since the release of \"[[Hit the Freeway]]\", peaking at No. 50 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] and at No. 17 on the [[UK R&B Chart|UK R&B Singles Chart]]. The song also became a moderate hit in Europe, peaking at No. 20 on the [[German Singles Chart]], at No. 17 on the [[Swiss Singles Chart]] and charting at No. 50 on the [[European Hot 100]].\n\nBy November 2009 Braxton had separated from Lewis.<ref>{{cite news |title = Toni Braxton Confirms 'Single' and 'Separated' Post Divorce Rumor |url = http://www.singersroom.com/content/2009-11-20/Toni-Braxton-Confirms-Single-and-Separated-Post-Divorce-Rumor/ |accessdate = December 2, 2013 |newspaper = [[Singersroom]] |date = November 20, 2009 }}</ref> Two songs were released from her upcoming album, \"[[Hands Tied]]\" and \"Make My Heart\". The former peaked at No. 29 on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]], the latter was sent to dance/club radio.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tonibraxton.com/news/hands-tied-make-my-heart-are-now-available-to-buy-exclusively-on-tonibraxtoncom/ |title = \"Hands Tied\" & \"Make My Heart\" Are Now Available To Buy Exclusively on ToniBraxton.com! \u2013 Blog Detail |publisher = ToniBraxton.com |date = January 29, 2010 |accessdate = November 12, 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110108182712/http://www.tonibraxton.com/news/hands-tied-make-my-heart-are-now-available-to-buy-exclusively-on-tonibraxtoncom/ |archivedate = January 8, 2011 }}</ref>\nShe performed \"Make My Heart\" on ''[[The Wendy Williams Show]]''.\n\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Toni Braxton Soul Beach.JPG|thumb|left|Soul Beach Music Festival press conference, Braxton with [[Gee Money]], May 2010]] -->\nBraxton released her sixth studio album ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]'' on May 4, 2010 in the US<ref>{{cite web |url = http://thatgrapejuice.net/2010/01/toni-braxtons-pulse-pushed/ |title = Toni Braxton's 'Pulse' Pushed Back&nbsp;\u2013 Again &#124; ..::That Grape Juice // ThatGrapeJuice.net::.. &#124;&#124; Thirsty? |publisher = Thatgrapejuice.net |date = January 21, 2010 |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref> and on May 10, 2010 in the UK.<ref>{{cite web |author = Praxis Media |url = http://www.radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_albums.htm |title = Radio1 Rodos Greece ::: UK Forthcoming Albums ::: Charts, DJ Promos, Dance, Lyrics, Free Mp3 Samples Downloads |publisher = Radio1.gr |date = |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref>\nDespite the fact that 27 songs were leaked, the album consisting of only 11 tracks, debuted at No. 9 on the US Billboard 200 chart and hit No. 1 on Billboard's [[R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]] chart, becoming Braxton's fifth US top-ten album. It also achieved moderate chart success around the world. In Canada, it debuted at No. 72 on the Top 100 Albums chart and in the United Kingdom, it debuted at No. 28 on the Top 40 Albums and at No. 7 on the R&B Albums chart. It entered at No. 18 on the German Album Chart. In Switzerland, the album hit No. 9. ''Pulse'', although a commercial flop, became Toni's first album to chart inside the [[European Top 100 Albums]] since her 2000 album ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]''.\n\nOn June 28, 2010, Braxton posted a video for ''Woman''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tonibraxton.com/ |title = Toni Braxton &#124; Official Website: Photos, Blog, Videos, Interactive and more. |publisher = ToniBraxton.com |date = |accessdate = November 12, 2010 }}</ref>\n\nBraxton was included as part of the \"[[We Are the World 25 for Haiti]]\" remake of the 1985 hit \"[[We Are the World]]\" to help benefit the people of Haiti following the January 12, 2010 magnitude 7.0 MW earthquake in Haiti. The new version of the song was recorded on February 1, 2010. Music legends [[Quincy Jones]] and [[Lionel Richie]] act as Executive Producers as well as [[Wyclef Jean]]. Artists involved included [[Celine Dion]], [[Barbra Streisand]], [[Janet Jackson]], [[Tony Bennett]], [[Wyclef Jean]], [[Josh Groban]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Usher (entertainer)|Usher]], [[Mary J. Blige]], [[Jennifer Hudson]], [[Adam Levine]], [[Justin Bieber]], [[LL Cool J]], among others.\n\nAccording to Braxton, via a lawsuit, [[TMZ]], and [[VH1]]'s [[Behind the Music]], after her ''Toni Braxton: Revealed'' show was abruptly cancelled back in 2008, the insurance agency, [[Lloyd's of London]] refused to honor her policy that she purchased for upwards of $70,000 that included financial compensations for financial losses that occurred as results of concert cancellations.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toni Braxton: My Insurance Co. Has No Heart|url=http://www.tmz.com/2009/04/29/toni-braxton-lawsuit|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=[[TMZ]]|date=April 29, 2009}}</ref> The policy was reported to insure Braxton up to $2.8 million.<ref name=\"hinterlandgazette.com\">{{cite news|last=Shan|first=Janet|title=Legal Briefs: Singer Toni Braxton Sues Lloyd's of London Over Cancelled Shoes|url=http://hinterlandgazette.com/2009/05/legal-briefs-singer-toni-braxton-sues.html|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=The Hinterland Gazette|date=May 3, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"vh1.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vh1.com/shows/behind_the_music/episode.jhtml?episodeID=200331|title=Ep. 238 &#124; Toni Braxton &#124; Behind The Music|website=VH1.com|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref>\n\nLloyd's of London responded with a counter-suit seeking damages against Braxton and remarked that Braxton's policy was null and void because of an unrelated heart condition that the company was not made aware of at the time the application was filed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Insurance Co. Claims Braxton's a Hearty Liar|url=http://www.tmz.com/2009/10/01/lloyds-of-london-toni-braxton-lawsuit-heart-condition|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=TMZ|date=October 1, 2009}}</ref> Braxton responded to the counter-suit by saying that she did disclose her full medical history at the time.<ref name=\"hinterlandgazette.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hellobeautiful.com/509107/lloyds-of-london-sues-toni-braxton|title=Lloyds of London Sues Toni Braxton|website=Hellobeautiful.com|date=October 1, 2009|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://newsok.com/toni-braxton-sues-her-insurance-company/article/3816464|title=Toni Braxton sues her insurance company|website=Newsok.com|date=April 29, 2009|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref> As a result of the insurance company nullifying Braxton's contract, Braxton has said that she was on the hook for all damages because of the cancelled shows, being sued by multiple companies, and had to once again file for bankruptcy.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toni Braxton: My Vegas Show Broke Me|url=http://www.tmz.com/2010/10/07/toni-braxton-files-chapter-7-bankruptcy-las-vegas-show-broke-debt|accessdate=December 2, 2013|newspaper=TMZ|date=October 7, 2010}}</ref> As of 2013, Braxton has completed required financial management courses and most of her debt has been discharged.<ref name=\"vh1.com\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2013/07/06/toni-braxton-bankruptcy-case-settled|title=Toni Braxton \u2013 Bankruptcy Case finally settled|website=Tmz.com|date=June 7, 2013}}</ref>\n\nLater that year rumors began circulating that Braxton was in talks to star in her own reality show with [[Bravo (U.S. TV network)|Bravo]]. Braxton would later confirm the rumors during an appearance on Ellen after a performance of her single \"Make My Heart\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/02/bravo-snags-singer-toni-braxton-for-new-reality-series.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100214093552/http://blog.zap2it.com/frominsidethebox/2010/02/bravo-snags-singer-toni-braxton-for-new-reality-series.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 14, 2010|title=Bravo snags singer Toni Braxton for new reality series|website=Blog.zap2it.com|accessdate=February 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===2011\u20132012: Television success and initial retirement===\n[[File:Toni Braxton Romania.jpg|thumb|left|Braxton performing in [[Romania]] during New Year's Eve 2011]]\nBraxton signed with [[WE tv]] for a [[reality series]], ''[[Braxton Family Values]]'', and the series debuted April 12, 2011, with Braxton, her mother, and her four sisters; Trina, [[Tamar Braxton|Tamar]], Traci and Towanda.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/01/04/wetv-toni-braxton-staten-island-cakes-tagline/ |title = WEtv unveils new details on Toni Braxton series, new cake series, and announces new tagline |author = James Hibberd |date = January 4, 2011 |accessdate = April 16, 2011 }}</ref> Toni parted ways with her long-time manager Vincent Herbert, who is also husband of sister Tamar Braxton, and signed a new management deal with Los Angeles -based entertainment/production company 'The Collective'.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://thatgrapejuice.net/2011/09/toni-braxton-signs-management/ |title = Toni Braxton Signs New Management Deal &#124; ..::That Grape Juice // ThatGrapeJuice.net::.. &#124;&#124; Thirsty? |publisher = Thatgrapejuice.net |date = September 6, 2011 |accessdate = May 5, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nBraxton completed filming of ''[[The Oogieloves in the Big Balloon Adventure]]'' alongside [[Jaime Pressly]] and [[Cloris Leachman]] which was released in 2012. Her character&nbsp;\u2013 Rosalie Rosebud&nbsp;\u2013 is a singer, whose over-the-top personality was apparently inspired by [[Mariah Carey]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.bluesandsoul.com/feature/538/ms_impulsive/ |title = Toni Braxton interview by Pete Lewis, 'Blues & Soul' May 2010 |publisher = Bluesandsoul.com |date = |accessdate = January 16, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last = Moss |first = Ricki |url = http://www.bet.com/news/celebrities/2012/08/24/watch-toni-braxton-stars-in-childrens-film.html |title = Watch: Toni Braxton Stars in Children's Film &#124; News |publisher = BET |date =  |accessdate = November 25, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nLater that year Braxton confirmed work on her eighth studio album.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://welovetoni.com/forum/topics/breaking-news-toni-is-working-with-l-a-reid-on-new-album|title=BREAKING NEWS: Toni is working with L.A. Reid on new album|website=WeLoveToni.com|date=October 28, 2011|accessdate=January 16, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120405123535/http://welovetoni.com/forum/topics/breaking-news-toni-is-working-with-l-a-reid-on-new-album |archivedate=April 5, 2012}}</ref> Braxton announced at Mercedes-Benz 2012 Fall/Winter Fashion Week in an interview with Rocco Leo Gaglioti as a part of \"Fashion News Live\", that she would be releasing a new single titled \"[[I Heart You (Toni Braxton song)|I Heart You]]\" in March 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toyazworld.com/2012/02/10/toni-braxton-confirms-new-single-i-heart-you/#more-14993|title=Toni Braxton confirms new single 'I Heart You'...|website=ToyazWorld.com}}</ref> Braxton premiered \"I Heart You\" on March 9, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|author=Pro Motion|url=http://blog.promotion-us.com/exclusive-mp3-toni-braxton-i-heart-you|title=Exclusive: Toni Braxton 'I Heart You'|website=Blog.promotion-us.com|date=March 9, 2012|accessdate=April 9, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311172728/http://blog.promotion-us.com/exclusive-mp3-toni-braxton-i-heart-you|archivedate=March 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe song has peaked at number 1 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Dance/Club play chart.<ref>{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=toni braxton|chart=all}}</ref> The music video for \"I Heart You\" was directed by [[Bille Woodruff]]. Shortly after the release of [[I Heart You (Toni Braxton song)|I Heart You]] rumors began circulating that Braxton would soon retire. These rumors would later be confirmed by Braxton herself on February 7, 2013. Braxton flew to Canada to begin shooting for her lead role in ''Twist of Faith'' later that year. Braxton appeared on Good Morning America to promote her new movie when she also confirmed the rumors of her retirement revealing that she is retiring from music and stated that she would like to focus on acting: \"I have to do shows here and there, but I'm not gonna do any albums, I'm falling out of love with it, it's weird. I don't know what to say when I hear songs. They don't impact me. I've been trying to listen to songs, record companies have been calling me, so it's a good situation to be in, but I'm not really interested at all\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/387118/toni-braxton-retiring-from-music-to-focus-on-film-career|title=Toni Braxton Retiring From Music to Focus on Film Career|website=Eonline.com|date=February 11, 2013|accessdate=February 17, 2013}}</ref> ''Twist of Faith'' premiered on the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] February 9, 2013.\n\n===2013\u20132014: ''Love, Marriage and Divorce,'' Broadway return, and memoir===\n''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' was released on February 4, 2014, under [[Motown Records]]. The lead single from ''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' was titled \"[[Hurt You (song)|Hurt You]];\" it premiered on August 17, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2013/08/17/new-music-toni-braxton-babyface-hurt-you|title=New Music: Toni Braxton & Babyface \u2013 'Hurt You'|publisher = Rap-Up.com|date=August 17, 2013|accessdate=February 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://singersroom.com/content/2013-06-11/Toni-Braxton-Babyface-Unite-For-Duet-Album-Can-The-Duo-Make-A-Hit-Again|title=News &#124; Toni Braxton & Babyface Unite For Duet Album, Can The Duo Make A Hit Again?|publisher=[[Singersroom]]|date=June 11, 2013|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref> The song attained success, claiming the No. 1 spot on two charts: the Billboard Adult R&B Songs chart for four weeks, and the Urban Adult Contemporary (Urban AC) for the week ending December 14, 2013. This marked Braxton's seventh No. 1 hit on the Adult R&B Songs chart and first since her 2000 release \"Just Be a Man About It.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2013-12-11/Toni-Braxton-and-Babyfaces-Hurt-You-Hits-No1-On-Two-Charts-Fantasia-Soars|title=Toni Braxton and Babyface's 'Hurt You' Hits No.1 on Two Charts|publisher=[[Singersroom]]|date=December 11, 2013}}</ref> The song also hit number 16 on ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Hot R&B/ Hip Hop Airplay chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/430180/toni-braxton/chart?f=364|title=Toni Braxton: Chart History|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=February 1, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=Toni Braxton \u2013 Chart history|magazine=Billboard}}</ref> The second single from the album was called \"Where Did We Go Wrong?\" It peaked at No. 11 on the Adult R&B Songs chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://singersroom.com/content/2014-01-21/Toni-Braxton-Babyface-and-Ledisi-Soar-With-Thicke-on-Adult-RB-Songs-Charts|title=Toni Braxton, Babyface and Ledisi Soar with Thicke on Adult R&B Songs Chart|publisher=[[Singersroom]]|date=December 11, 2013}}</ref> The album was nominated for World's Best Album at the [[2014 World Music Awards]]. The album won for [[Best R&B Album]] at the 57th Annual Grammy Awards in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees|title=The Official Site of Music's Biggest Night|website=Grammy.com|accessdate=July 8, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120201120225/http://www.grammy.com/nominees|archivedate=February 1, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2013, it was announced that Braxton would make her return to Broadway alongside collaborator [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]] in Broadway's ''[[After Midnight (musical)|After Midnight]].'' They were scheduled to perform from March 18 to March 31, 2014, at the Brooks Atkinson Theatre. In succession, they would be third in rotation in the role of \"Special Guest Star\" following [[Fantasia Barrino]] and [[KD Lang]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/toni-braxton-kenny-babyface-edmonds-636524|title=Toni Braxton and Kenny 'Babyface' Edmonds Join Broadway's 'After Midnight' Lineup|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=September 25, 2013|accessdate=February 1, 2014|first=David|last=Rooney}}</ref>\n\nOn January 20, 2014, Braxton announced that she would publish a memoir, titled ''Unbreak My Heart: A Memoir,'' through [[Harper Collins Publishers]]. In it, Braxton said, she would discuss her career success and struggles and the self-healing she took charge of after her own diagnosis with the auto-immune disease [[lupus]] and her son's diagnosis with autism. ''Unbreak My Heart: A Memoir'' was published on May 20, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/music/240653651.html |title=Toni Braxton memoir, 'Unbreak My Heart,' coming in May; to cover her hit songs, lupus |newspaper=[[Star Tribune]] |date=January 16, 2014 |accessdate=February 1, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202115248/http://www.startribune.com/entertainment/music/240653651.html |archivedate=February 2, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===2015\u20132016: ''Braxton Family Christmas'', biographical film, and The Hits Tour===\nOn May 14, 2015, Braxton said she was headed back to the studio for an upcoming eighth album. She promised that a new single would be released before the end of the year.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://thatgrapejuice.net/2015/05/watch-toni-braxton-announces-new-single-album-due-this-year|title=Watch: Toni Braxton Announces New Single & Album Due This Year|website=Thatgrapejuice.net|date=May 14, 2015|accessdate=July 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, Lifetime greenlighted a biographical film on Braxton's life, ''[[Toni Braxton: Unbreak My Heart]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/toni-braxton-life-story-lifetime-movie-unbreak-my-heart-1201528565|website=Deadline.com|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]|date=September 15, 2015|accessdate=September 15, 2015|title=Toni Braxton's Life Story Heading To Lifetime As Original Movie|first=Denise|last=Petski}}</ref> The film's premiere generated 3.6 million viewers, earning the highest rating for an original movie with adults ages 25\u201354, women 25-54 and women 18-49 since \"Whitney,\" the January 2015 biopic on Whitney Houston.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toni Braxton biopic earns high ratings|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/entertainment/music/midnight-sun-blog/bal-toni-braxton-biopic-earns-high-ratings-story.html|newspaper=[[Baltimore Sun]]|accessdate=January 25, 2016}}</ref> The film has an [[IMDb]] rating of a 6.5 out of 10 stars.<ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton: Unbreak my Heart (2016) IMDb|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5037902/|website=IMDb.com|accessdate=15 November 2016}}</ref> In October 2015, [[The Braxtons]] released ''[[Braxton Family Christmas]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.essence.com/2015/10/09/braxtons-are-releasing-christmas-album|title=Braxton Family Christmas|website=Essence.com|accessdate=October 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.target.com/p/the-braxtons-braxton-family-christmas/-/A-50059014#prodSlot=medium_1_1&term=Braxton+Family+Christmas|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Braxton Family Christmas|website=Target.com|accessdate=October 11, 2015}}</ref> ''Braxton Family Christmas'' debuted at number 27 on the US [[Billboard R&B/Hip-Hop Albums chart|''Billboard'' R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=333|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Chart history|website=Billboard.com|date=October 5, 1996|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref> number 10 on the [[US R&B]] Chart and number 12 on US Top Holiday Albums on November 21, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=1235|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Chart history|website=Billboard.com|date=October 5, 1996|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=325|title=The Braxtons \u2013 Chart history|website=Billboard.com|date=October 5, 1996|accessdate=December 7, 2015}}</ref> The album charted at number 1 on the US [[Top Heatseekers|Heatseekers Albums]] on December 12, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.billboard.com/artist/388935/braxtons/chart?f=324 |title = The Braxtons \u2013 Chart History |work = The Braxtons |publisher = Billboard |accessdate = December 17, 2015 }}</ref> Braxton announced in an interview with Sway in the Morning on January 22, 2016 that she and Babyface will collaborate again with ''Love, Marriage & Divorce Pt. II''.<ref name=\"soultracks\">{{cite web |url = http://www.soultracks.com/story-toni-braxton-babyface-recording |title = Toni Braxton and Babyface to team for 2nd album of duets |work = Toni Braxton Babyface |publisher = soultracks |accessdate = January 27, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nOn July 25, 2016, Braxton announced that she would be embarking on a tour in late 2016 titled \"[[The Hits Tour (Toni Braxton)|The Hits Tour]]\" in North America.<ref>{{cite web|title=So excited to announce my new tour starting in October! Get your tickets now! Can't wait to see you all \u2764\ufe0f \u2022The Hits Tour\u2022|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BITLo4GgvTu/|website=Instagram|publisher=Toni Braxton|accessdate=July 25, 2016}}</ref> On October 3, five days before the first date of the tour Braxton was hospitalized due to complications with [[Lupus]] resulting in canceling the first two dates of the tour. The dates canceled were rescheduled for January 28 and 29, 2017 and kicked off the tour on in Detroit at the [[MotorCity Casino Hotel]] on October 12, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=TONI BRAXTON HOSPITALIZED Birdman Rushes to Her Side|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/10/03/toni-braxton-hospitalized-birdman/|website=Tmz.com|accessdate=October 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Singer Toni Braxton hospitalized with lupus complications|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/video/tvshowbiz/video-1336092/Singer-Toni-Braxton-hospitalized-lupus-complications.html|website=Dailymail.co.uk|accessdate=October 4, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton (Rescheduled from 10/8) Oakland Tickets - 1/28/17|url=http://www.vividseats.com/concerts/toni-braxton-tickets/toni-braxton-paramount-theatre-oakland-10-8-2109718.html|website=Vividseats.com|accessdate=October 12, 2016}}</ref> On October 15, 2016, Braxton was admitted once again to hospital with complications with Lupus resulting to cancel another tour date October 15, 2016, which was later scheduled to November 14, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=TONI BRAXTON BACK IN HOSPITAL ... Postpones Show|url=http://www.tmz.com/2016/10/16/toni-braxton-hospital-postpones-show/|website=Tmz.com|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton Hospitalized Again With Lupus, Postpones Concert|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7542066/toni-braxton-hospitalized-lupus-postpones-concert|website=Billboard|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref> On October 16, 2016, Braxton posted a photo of herself leaving the hospital on her Instagram, announcing that she was on her way to that night's performance in Chicago.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hey guys, thanks for all of your well wishes and understanding. I am out of the hospital, and en route to CHICAGO! I can not wait to see you all TONIGHT at the Arie Crown Theater!! #TheHitsTour \u2764\ufe0f|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BLoeUDkDWH5/|website=Instagram|publisher=Toni Braxton|accessdate=October 16, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn December 1, 2016, Braxton announced a short statement via [[Twitter]] that the dates for The Hits Tour in January 2017 were canceled, a new album would be coming soon and back touring in the summer, \"Hey Guys, Unfortunately, Under doctor\u2019s recommendation, I'm going to have to cancel my shows in Oakland on January 28th and Los Angeles on January 29th, 2017. I'm feeling better and better every day and I want to be at my best when performing for you all. I\u2019m excited to say that I will be completing my new record this spring/summer of 2017 and can't wait to share it with you. Stay tuned for more details. I look forward to seeing everyone back on tour in the summer of 2017!!!\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Hey Guys, Unfortunately, Under doctor's recommendation, I'm going to have to cancel my shows in Oakland on January 28th and|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483723957850112|website=Twitter|accessdate=December 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Los Angeles on January 29th, 2017. I'm feeling better and better every day and I want to be at my best when performing for you all.|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483509410791424|website=Twitter|accessdate=December 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=I\u2019m excited to say that I will be completing my new record this spring/summer of 2017 and can\u2019t wait to share it with you.|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483598283898884|website=Twitter|date=December 5, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stay tuned for more details.  I look forward to seeing everyone back on tour in the summer of 2017!!!|url=https://twitter.com/tonibraxton/status/804483723957850112|website=Twitter|accessdate=December 5, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u20132019: ''Sex & Cigarettes'', touring, and other ventures ===\nOn September 14, 2017, Braxton released the lead single \"[[Deadwood (Toni Braxton song)|Deadwood]]\"<ref name=\"iTunes\">{{cite web|title=Deadwood \u2013 Single by Toni Braxton on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/deadwood-single/id1280577966|website=Apple Music (U.S. Store)|accessdate=September 14, 2017}}</ref> from her eighth studio album ''[[Sex & Cigarettes]]''. The single reached #7 on the Adult R&B Charts.<ref>{{cite web|title=Toni Braxton Is Back On The Music Scene With \u2018Sex & Cigarettes\u2019|url=https://hellobeautiful.com/2957549/toni-braxton-announces-new-album|accessdate=September 8, 2017|date=September 7, 2017}}</ref> A remix EP for the song \"Coping\" was released on November 10, 2017. The single reached #1 on the Billboard Dance Charts, marking Braxton's 6th single to reach #1 on that chart.<ref>{{cite web|title=Coping (Remixes) \u2013 EP by Toni Braxton|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/coping-remixes-ep/1306316861|website=Apple Music|accessdate=November 10, 2017}}</ref> The album was nominated for three [[Grammy Awards]]: [[Best R&B Performance]], [[Best R&B Song]] for \"[[Long as I Live (Toni Braxton song)|Long as I Live]]\", and for [[Best R&B Album]] at the [[61st Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/61st-annual-grammy-awards|title=61st Annual GRAMMY Awards|date=December 6, 2018|website=Grammy.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Faith Under Fire'' premiered on the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] January 22, 2018.<ref name=\"mylifetime\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mylifetime.com/movies/faith-under-fire/about|title=About Faith Under Fire: The Antoinette Tuff Story - Lifetime|website=Mylifetime.com}}</ref> The second single \"[[Long as I Live (Toni Braxton song)|Long as I Live]]\" was released on February 9, 2018. The single reached #1 on the Adult R&B Charts, giving Braxton her eighth #1 on the chart. Braxton also broke a tie with Maxwell and R. Kelly to give her sole possession of the second-most No. 1s in the chart's 24-year history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Long As I Live \u2013 by Toni Braxton|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/long-as-i-live-single/1342585144?l=en|accessdate=February 9, 2018}}</ref> On April 20, 2018, Trina, Towanda and Toni appears as featuring on their sister Traci's single \"Broken Things\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tracibraxton.com/news|title=TraciBraxton - NEWS|website=Traci Braxton Reality Tv Celebrity|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thatgrapejuice.net/2018/04/new-single-traci-braxton-broken-things-featuring-toni-braxton-towanda-braxton-trina-braxton/|title=New Single: Traci Braxton - 'Broken Things' (Featuring Toni Braxton, Towanda Braxton, & Trina Braxton) - That Grape Juice|website=Thatgrapejuice.net|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thisisrnb.com/2018/04/new-music-traci-braxton-feat-toni-braxton-towanda-braxton-trina-braxton-broken-things/|title=New Music: Traci Braxton feat. Toni Braxton, Towanda Braxton & Trina Braxton - Broken Things|date=April 20, 2018|website=Thisisrnb.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref> On October 23, 2018, Braxton announced a joint tour with [[SWV]], As Long As I Live Tour for 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.essence.com/entertainment/toni-braxton-and-swv-are-going-on-tour-next-year/|title=Yassss! Toni Braxton And SWV Are Going On Tour Next Year|first=Keyaira|last=Boone|website=Essence.com}}</ref> Toni and her sister Towanda are the stars on the Christmas TV movie ''Every Day is Christmas'' which premiered on the [[Lifetime Movie Network]] November 24, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt9102152/|title=Every Day is Christmas|accessdate=December 15, 2018|website=IMDb.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/03/15/lifetime-doubling-holiday-movies-2018/|title=Lifetime to double number of original holiday movies in 2018|website=Ew.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/lifetime-decks-its-halls-with-23-holiday-themed-movies-more-cheer-1202469310/|title=Lifetime Decks Its Halls With 23 Holiday-Themed Movies & More Cheer|first1=Erik|last1=Pedersen|first2=Erik|last2=Pedersen|date=September 24, 2018|website=Deadline.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/971199/all-the-lifetime-and-hallmark-holiday-movies-you-need-to-watch-this-year|title=Every Holiday Movie Coming to Lifetime and Hallmark This Fall|date=November 1, 2018|website=Eonline.com|accessdate=December 15, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Braxton and Uncle Bud's Hemp products created a joint marketing campaign for the latter's products.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/toni-braxton-and-uncle-buds-natural-hemp-products-join-forces-300710241.html|title=Toni Braxton and Uncle Bud's Natural Hemp Products Join Forces|website=Prnewswire.com|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref> The campaign included multiple videos and pictures online as well as a billboard in New York's Time Square. Braxton is quoted as saying how these products have helped her with her battle against lupus,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unclebudshemp.com/|title=Natural CBD & Hemp Products &#124; Organic Topical Lotions|website=Uncle Bud\u2019s Hemp}}</ref> \"Lupus is a part of who I am, but I am not going to let it define me. I still want to perform & love what I do. Using safe natural products like Uncle Bud's Hemp & CBD makes it possible\".\n\nIn April 2019, it was announced that Braxton would be headlining the 2019 Pittsburgh Pride festival on Saturday, June 8. This is a first for Braxton to perform in a Pride festival.<ref>{{cite news |url = https://www.post-gazette.com/ae/music/2019/04/09/Toni-Braxton-Walk-the-Moon-will-headline-Pittsburgh-Pride-2019/stories/201904090096 |title = Toni Braxton, Walk the Moon will headline Pittsburgh Pride |last = Mervis |first = Scott |date = April 9, 2019 |newspaper=[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]]|accessdate = May 8, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nIn August 2019, it was announced Braxton would take her As Long As I Live Tour for 2019 international, to South Africa for two dates in November; Johannesburg on the 9th and Cape Town on the 12th. The two shows in South Africa will be followed by a one-off special show in the capital of the United Kingdom, London at the Eventim Apollo in Hammersmith on November 16, 2019; this  will be the first time in 22 years that she has performed a concert in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tonibraxton.com/tour|title=Tour|website=Tonibraxton.com|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2020: Island Records and new music ===\nIn April 2020, it was announced that Braxton had signed with [[Island Records]]. She released the single, \"Do It\", the first song under the new deal on April 5, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/9351807/toni-braxton-signs-island-records-new-single-do-it-exclusive|title=Toni Braxton Signs with Island Records, Releases New Single \u2018Do It\u2019: Exclusive|website=Billboard.com|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Artistry ==\nBraxton has been recognized for her distinctive [[contralto]] voice.<ref>{{cite news |url = http://articles.courant.com/2012-03-24/entertainment/hc-toni-braxtons-concert-at-foxwoods-20120324_1_toni-braxton-angel-break-concert-review |title = Concert Review: Toni Braxton's Sultry Delivery Scores At Foxwoods |last = Kintner |first = Thomas |date = March 24, 2012 |publisher = courant.com |accessdate = August 11, 2012 }}</ref><ref name=\"books.google.ca\">{{Cite book |title = Rock-N-Roll Gold Rush |last = Dean |first = Maury |authorlink = |year = 2003 |publisher = Algora Publishing |location = |isbn = 0-87586-207-1 |page = 34 |url = https://books.google.com/?id=lJS4EArRBwoC&dq=Rock-N-Roll+Gold+Rush+mariah+carey&pg=PA87&lpg=PA87&q=whitney+houston#PPA34,M1 |accessdate = June 24, 2016 }}</ref> Her voice has been called \"husky, sultry, elegant and sexy.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://myplay.com/artists/toni-braxton |title=My Play: Toni Braxton |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015194514/http://myplay.com/artists/toni-braxton |archivedate=October 15, 2012 }}</ref> Due to the huskiness of her voice, Braxton often used male singers such as [[Michael McDonald (singer)|Michael McDonald]], [[Luther Vandross]] and [[Stevie Wonder]] as vocal style models.<ref name=stevehuey>{{cite web |last = Huey |first = Steve |url = http://www.allmusic.com/artist/toni-braxton-mn0000935330 |title = Toni Braxton&nbsp;\u2013 Music Biography, Credits and Discography |website = AllMusic |accessdate = July 29, 2012 }}</ref> [[Chaka Khan]] and [[Anita Baker]] were two of the few female singers that she could stylize. Steve Huey of [[AllMusic]] cites a key to Braxton's success is the versatility of her voice, which he states as being \"soulful enough for [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] audiences, but smooth enough for adult contemporary; sophisticated enough for adults, but sultry enough for younger listeners; strong enough in the face of heartbreak to appeal to women, but ravishing enough to nab the fellas.\"<ref name=stevehuey/>\n\nBraxton began her career singing traditional R&B and soft rock ballads and love songs on her debut and second albums. However, [[hip-hop soul]] and [[dance music]] elements begun to get spun into her sound on ''The Heat'',<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/the-heat-mw0000256509 |title = The Heat Review |website = [[AllMusic]] |accessdate = July 8, 2015 }}</ref> ''More Than a Woman'',<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.allmusic.com/album/more-than-a-woman-mw0000224666 |title = More Than A Woman |website = [[AllMusic]] |accessdate = July 8, 2015 }}</ref> and ''Pulse''. She also showcased her classical training while performing in Broadway plays ''[[Beauty and the Beast (musical)|Beauty and the Beast]]'' and ''[[Aida]]'' as well as her duet with [[Il Divo]], \"The Time of Our Lives\".\n\n== Legacy ==\n\nToni Braxton became an immediate R&B superstar after the release of her first album. LA Reid stated during an interview with [[VH1]]: \"We called her the first lady of LaFace. She was our Diva. [[Clive Davis|Clive]] had [[Whitney Houston|Whitney]], [[Tommy Mottola|Tommy]] had [[Mariah Carey|Mariah]] and we had Toni.\" BBC called the album \"spiritedly, mature soul at its best \u2013 and just urban enough to make it the bedroom album for the hip hop generation.\"<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/j4fd |title = Music \u2013 Review of Toni Braxton \u2013 Toni Braxton |publisher = BBC |date = July 13, 1993 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> Braxton had the sound of R&B greats like [[Anita Baker]] and the sex appeal to compete with fellow superstars [[Mariah Carey]] and [[Whitney Houston]]. Over the span of her career Braxton has sold over 66 million records,{{citation needed|date=October 2014}} including 40 million albums,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tonibraxton.com/bio/ |title=Toni Braxton Bio |publisher=Toni Braxton Official Website |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140727061235/http://www.tonibraxton.com/bio/ |archivedate=July 27, 2014 }}</ref> worldwide. Braxton's musical catalog contains many classics that have won her many accolades. Her greatest is \"[[Un-Break My Heart]]\", the [[Diane Warren]]-penned ballad that spent 11-weeks at number 1. Bob McCann, author of ''Encyclopedia of African American Actresses in Film and Television'' (2010), considered it \"simply one of the most haunting R&B records ever made.\" Reviewer Mark Edward Nero named it one of the best R&B break-up songs and considered it Braxton's \"finest moment\". He further commented, \"damn, this song is so sad it can make people cry for hours at a time.\" It's Braxton's ability to capture her audience that plays a factor in her continuous success.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}} Braxton is a recipient of seven [[Grammy Award]]s, seven [[American Music Awards]], and nine [[Billboard Music Awards]].{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n\nThroughout Braxton's career, she made several impacts on fashion mostly for her legendary high splits in her dresses. Her now-famous [[Richard Tyler (designer)|Richard Tyler]] white satin gown has gone down in history as one of the most revealing and sexiest dresses. In 2011, Braxton topped the list for the [[Grammy Award]]'s best dressed of the decade.<ref>{{cite news |author = |url = http://www.cbsnews.com/news/grammy-fashion-the-best-and-worst-of-the-decade/ |title = Grammy Fashion: The Best and Worst of the Decade |publisher = CBS News |date = February 10, 2011 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> \"I've always gone a little risque with all my other award show outfits.\"<ref>{{cite magazine |url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/gallery/racy-grammy-dresses-419267#2-toni-braxton |title = Racy Grammy Dresses |magazine = Hollywood Reporter |date = February 8, 2013 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 |first = Emily |last = Helwig }}</ref> In 2012, Braxton made the list for [[VH1]]'s 50 Greatest Women in Music. Braxton's 2000 performance at [[Super Bowl XXXIV]] is ranked as one of the most memorable Super Bowl performances.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/02/the-super-bowl-top-5-memorable-halftime-shows/ |title = The Super Bowl: Top 5 Memorable Halftime Shows \u2013 ABC News |publisher = Abcnews.go.com |date = February 3, 2012 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> Braxton is featured alongside other R&B and pop divas as a primary character on the popular [[web series|web]] [[parody]] ''[[Got 2B Real: The Diva Variety Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Glazer|first=Eliot|url=https://www.vulture.com/2012/01/got-2-b-real.html|title=Behold the Newest Installment of \u2018Got 2 B Real,\u2019 a Web Series That Dubs Over the Voices of R&B Goddesses|website=Vulture.com}}</ref> Braxton cemented her diva status in the music industry in 2006, with her Las Vegas residency ''Toni Braxton: Revealed'', by becoming the first African American performer in Las Vegas to have her act enter the top ten Vegas shows charting.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}} Braxton also made headlines for her signature and legendary Giantto Million Dollar Microphone that she performed every show with. Braxton said: \"I think it's a great element to the show. You have to have a little sprinkle of [[Liberace]] and this is my little sprinkle of that.\" Braxton's famous prop was made up of white gold and encrusted with 650 karats of diamonds.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.tmz.com/2006/09/01/braxtons-million-dollar-baby/ |title = Braxton's Million Dollar Baby |website=Tmz.com |date = January 9, 2006 |accessdate = February 1, 2014 }}</ref> The microphone reportedly cost $1 million.{{citation needed|date=May 2014}}\n\n== Personal life ==\n===Relationships===\nBraxton met musician [[Keri Lewis]] when his group, [[Mint Condition]], opened for her on tour; they married on April 21, 2001. In 2001, she gave birth to their first child, a son named Denim Cole Braxton-Lewis. In 2002, while gearing up for the release of her fourth studio album, Braxton discovered she was pregnant with her second child; the complicated pregnancy confined her to [[bed rest]]. The couple's second son, Diezel Ky Braxton-Lewis, was born in March 2003. As Diezel has been diagnosed with [[autism]], Braxton has become involved with [[Autism Speaks]], serving as their International Spokesperson. In November 2009 Braxton announced that she and her husband had separated. The couple later divorced in July 2013.<ref>{{cite web |author = Zach Johnson |url = http://m.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/toni-braxton-finalizes-divorce-from-keri-lewis-2013257/ |title = Toni Braxton Finalizes Divorce From Keri Lewis |publisher = usmagazine.com |date = July 25, 2013 |accessdate = July 10, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nIn her early 30s, Braxton had an abortion after discovering she was pregnant with then-boyfriend Keri Lewis. In her memoir ''Unbreak my Heart'', Braxton discusses her abortion and guilt, saying that her son Diezel's autism was \"God's payback.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2014/05/toni-braxton-thinks-god-punished-her-for-getting-an-abortion-by-giving-her-son-autism/371518/|title=Toni Braxton Thinks God Punished Her for Getting an Abortion by Giving Her Son Autism|last=Jones|first=Allie|date=2014-05-23|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-28}}</ref>\n\nBraxton was dating rapper [[Birdman (rapper)|Birdman]] in May 2016, and the couple announced their engagement in February 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uk/news/914842/toni-braxton-confirms-engagement-to-birdman-see-her-massive-ring|title=Toni Braxton Confirms Engagement to Birdman: See Her Massive Ring|website=Eonline.com|accessdate=October 16, 2019}}</ref> In January 2019, the couple have called off the engagement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-01-02-toni-braxton-birdman-call-of-engagement-its-over/|title=Toni Braxton & Birdman Call Off Engagement: 'It's Over'|last=Blakemore|first=Peyton|work=[[iHeartRadio]]|date=January 2, 2019|accessdate=January 9, 2019}}</ref> However, in April 2019, both Braxton and Birdman confirmed that they were still together.<ref>{{cite web |author = Danilo Castro |url = https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/04/toni-braxton-fiance-birdman-still-together/ |title = Are Toni Braxton & Fiance Birdman Still Together? |date= April 11, 2019 }}</ref>\n\nOn July 8, 2015, Braxton's attorney, Antavius Weems, announced that Braxton had settled her contentious child support case with her former husband, Keri Lewis.<ref>{{cite web |author = Ny Magee |url = http://www.eurweb.com/2015/07/toni-braxton-settles-child-support-battle-with-ex-husband/ |title = Toni Braxton Settles Child Support Battle with Ex-husband |publisher = eurweb.com |date = July 8, 2015 |accessdate = July 10, 2015 }}</ref> On June 2, 2016, the city and county officials of [[Atlanta, Georgia]], named June 2 as Toni Braxton Day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://raycornelius.com/2016/06/toni-braxton-honored-with-atls-phoenix-award-and-more-photos/|title=Toni Braxton honored with ATL\u2019s Phoenix Award and more! [PHOTOS]|website=Raycornelius.com|language=en-US|access-date=December 17, 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Health problems ===\nAs of August 2007, rumors surfaced that she had been diagnosed with breast cancer. Braxton stated to ''[[Access Hollywood]]'', that the breast cancer rumors were false and that her health is in great condition. However, in 2008, she had a [[Benign tumor|benign]] lump removed from her breast. On April 8, 2008, near the end of her two-year run at the [[Flamingo Hotel]], Braxton was briefly hospitalized and the remaining dates on the show, which was scheduled to end on August 23, 2008, were cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.huliq.com/57437/toni-braxton-cancels-more-shows-due-unidentified-illness |accessdate = January 23, 2016 |work = Huliq |title = Toni Braxton Cancels More Shows Due to Unidentified Illness }}</ref> Later, while appearing on Season 7 of ''Dancing with the Stars'', she stated, that she has been diagnosed with [[Microangiopathy|microvascular angina]] (small vessel disease).<ref>{{cite web |url = http://abcnews.go.com/Health/HeartDiseaseNews/story?id=5870125 |accessdate = January 23, 2016 |date = September 24, 2008 |work = [[ABC News]] |publisher = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |first = Radha |last = Chitale |title = Dancing Won't Un-Break Toni Braxton's Heart }}</ref>\n\nOn November 18, 2010, Braxton admitted to [[CBS News]] that she had been diagnosed with [[systemic lupus erythematosus]] (SLE), a potentially life-threatening autoimmune disease.<ref name=\"Lupus\">{{cite web|url=http://heal-good.blogspot.com/2014/02/toni-braxton-is-fighter-of-lupus.html|accessdate=January 23, 2016|work=Heal Good|title=Toni Braxton is a fighter of Lupus}}</ref>\n\nBraxton's uncle died of complications from lupus.<ref name=\"Lupus\"/> While taping her reality series ''[[Braxton Family Values]]'', she went in for surgery. Braxton was hospitalized in Los Angeles in December 2012 because of \"minor health issues\" related to [[lupus]].<ref>{{cite news |url = http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1481514/toni-braxton-hospitalized-for-lupus-related-health-issues|accessdate=January 23, 2016|date=December 8, 2012|agency=Associated Press|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|title=Toni Braxton Hospitalized for Lupus-Related Health Issues}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Toni Braxton discography}} {{see also|The Braxtons discography}}\n\n;Studio albums \n* ''[[Toni Braxton (album)|Toni Braxton]]'' (1993)\n* ''[[Secrets (Toni Braxton album)|Secrets]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[The Heat (Toni Braxton album)|The Heat]]'' (2000)\n* ''[[Snowflakes (album)|Snowflakes]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[More Than a Woman (album)|More Than a Woman]]'' (2002)\n* ''[[Libra (Toni Braxton album)|Libra]]'' (2005)\n* ''[[Pulse (Toni Braxton album)|Pulse]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Sex & Cigarettes]]'' (2018)\n\n;Collaboration albums \n* ''[[Love, Marriage & Divorce]]'' <small>(with [[Babyface (musician)|Babyface]])</small> (2014)\n\n==Tours==\n'''Headlining'''\n* [[Secrets Tour]] (1996)\n* [[Libra Tour]] (2006)\n* [[2013 Summer Tour (Toni Braxton)|2013 Summer Tour]] (2013)\n* [[The Hits Tour]] (2016)\n* [[As Long As I Live Tour]] (2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Toni-Braxton-Announces-New-Studio-Album-SEX-AND-CIGARETTES-Out-March-23-20180212|title=Toni Braxton Announces New Studio Album SEX AND CIGARETTES Out March 23|website=Broadwayworld.com}}</ref>\n\n'''Residencies'''\n* ''[[Toni Braxton: Revealed]]'' (2006\u20132008)\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Toni Braxton}}\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Kingdom Come (2001 film)|Kingdom Come]]''\n| Juanita Slocumb\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Play'd: A Hip Hop Story]]''\n| Shonda\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Oogieloves in the Big Balloon Adventure]]''\n| Rosalie Rosebud\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Twist of Faith''\n| Nina Jones\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Toni Braxton: Unbreak My Heart]]''\n| Herself\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Faith Under Fire: The Antoinette Tuff Story''\n| [[Antoinette Tuff]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Every Day Is Christmas''\n| Alexis Taylor\n| Television film\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Roc (TV series)|Roc]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Concert\"\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[Mad TV]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"6.10\"\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Blue's Clues]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"Bluestock\"\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Kevin Hill]]''\n| Terry Knox\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\u2013present\n| ''[[Braxton Family Values]]''\n| Herself\n| Main role; 142 episodes\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:left;\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Year\n! Artist\n! Notes\n|-\n| \"[[Miss You (Aaliyah song)|Miss You]]\"\n| 2002\n| [[Aaliyah]]\n|\n|-\n| \"Last Call\"\n| 2014\n| [[Traci Braxton]]\n|\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n\n{{Portal|Biography|Film|Music|Television}}\n\n* [[Honorific nicknames in popular music]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one in the United States]]\n* [[List of artists who reached number one on the U.S. dance chart]]\n* [[List of best-selling music artists]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Toni Braxton}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p37576|label=Toni Braxton}}\n* {{IMDb name|4772}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{Amg name|285038}}\n\n{{Toni Braxton}}\n{{Toni Braxton singles}}\n{{The Braxtons}}\n{{Grammy Award for Best New Artist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Braxton, Toni}}\n[[Category:Toni Braxton| ]]\n[[Category:1967 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Activists from California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Maryland]]\n[[Category:African-American activists]]\n[[Category:African-American actresses]]\n[[Category:African-American female singers]]\n[[Category:African-American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American pianists]]\n[[Category:African-American record producers]]\n[[Category:African-American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:African-American television personalities]]\n[[Category:American women television personalities]]\n[[Category:American contemporary R&B singers]]\n[[Category:American contraltos]]\n[[Category:American female pop singers]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American female singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American health activists]]\n[[Category:American hip hop dancers]]\n[[Category:American hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:American hip hop singers]]\n[[Category:American women record producers]]\n[[Category:American Methodists]]\n[[Category:American singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American soul singers]]\n[[Category:American women activists]]\n[[Category:Arista Records artists]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records artists]]\n[[Category:Autism activists]]\n[[Category:Ballad musicians]]\n[[Category:Bowie State University alumni]]\n[[Category:The Braxtons members]]\n[[Category:Female dancers]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:New jack swing musicians]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Severn, Maryland]]\n[[Category:People from the Las Vegas Valley]]\n[[Category:People with lupus]]\n[[Category:Singers from Maryland]]\n[[Category:Women hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:American female hip hop musicians]]\n", "name_user": "149.167.143.193", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed typo)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toni_Braxton"}
{"title_page": "Taxation in Turkey", "text_new": "Taxation has an important part in Turkish economy. Turkey has 25.5% tax-GDP ration (in 2016).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=2017|title=Revenue Statistics 2017 - Turkey|url=https://www.oecd.org/tax/revenue-statistics-turkey.pdf|journal=OECD Revenue Statistics 2017|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> Most of the taxes are levied by central government. However some specific taxes are levied by municipalities.\n\n== Tax Procedure Law ==\nTaxation system in Turkey is regulated by the Tax Procedure (TP) Law. It regulates the rights, burdens, carrying out duties along with principals of accrual. This Law consist of procedural and official provisions of all tax laws. The TP has five main sections: taxation, taxpayer duties, valuation, penalty provisions, tax cases.<ref name=ministry>{{Cite web |date=2016 |title=Turkish Taxation System |url=http://www.gib.gov.tr/sites/default/files/fileadmin/taxation_system2016.pdf |publisher=The Republic of Turkey Ministry of Finance Revenue Administration}}</ref>\n\n== Taxes ==\nThe Turkish tax legislation can be divided into three main categories:\n\n# Income taxes\n# Taxes on expenditure\n# Taxes on wealth\n\n=== Income taxes ===\nThe Turkish tax legislation has two main income taxes, they are individual income tax and corporate income tax. Many rules and provisions are the same for individual income tax and corporations, especially in terms of income elements and the determination of net income. However individual income tax and corporate income tax are regulated by different laws.<ref name=invest>{{Cite web|url=http://www.invest.gov.tr/en-US/investmentguide/investorsguide/Pages/Taxes.aspx|title=Taxes - Invest in Turkey|website=www.invest.gov.tr|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref>\n\n==== Individual income tax ====\nThe subject of individual income tax is the real people. The meaning of income is the net amount of revenues derived by a person within a year. According to Income Tax Law, incomes may be listed such as:\n\n* Business profits\n* Agricultural profits\n* Salaries and wages\n* Income from independent personal services\n* Income from immovable property and rights (rental income)\n* Income from movable property (income from capital investment)\n* Other income and earnings\n\n<nowiki>#</nowiki>Variety of individual income tax rate is between 15% and 35%.<ref name=invest/>\n\nResidency criterion is the key point for the taxes. Residents in Turkey are liable at tax on their worldwide income and they are considered as \"full tax liable\". Non-residents are only subject to taxes on their revenues gained in Turkey and they are considered as \"limited tax liable\". Residents are individuals with legal permanent residence and those who reside in Turkey for more than six months during one year.<ref>[http://www.gep.gov.tr/tmp/_Gep1.pdf Turkish Tax System in General]</ref>\n\n==== Corporate income taxes ====\nIf the income elements listed in the Income Tax Law are derived by corporations, taxation is enforceable on the legal entities of these corporations. Corporate taxpayers has been described as:\n\n* Capital companies\n* Cooperatives\n* Public economic enterprises\n* Economic enterprises owned by associations and foundations\n* Joint ventures<ref name=invest/>\n\nIf the legal headquarters or effective management of corporations are located in Turkey, they are subject to taxes derived from world-wide business. They are also called as resident companies.\n\n=== Taxes on expenditure ===\n\n==== Value Added Tax (VAT) ====\nGenerally, the VAT rate varies from 1%, 8% to 18%. There is a huge range of subject subject to VAT such as industrial, commercial, agricultural, independent professional goods and services.<ref name=invest/>\n\nPeople who has to pay VAT are described as:\n\n* Those supplying goods and services,\n* Those importing goods or services,\n* Those required to complete customs formalities in case of transit of goods through Turkey,\n* General Directorates of Postal Services (PT and Telecom) and radio and television corporations,\n* Organizers of any kind of chance and gambling,\n* Organizers of shows, concerts and sporting events with the participation of professional artists and professional sportsmen,\n* Lessors of goods and rights stated in Article 70 of the PIT Law,\n* Applicants for optional tax liability<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Special Consumption Tax (SCT) ====\nThe goods which are subject to SCT is in the list. For these products, the Special Consumption Tax is collected only once. Generally 4 product group are subject to SCT at different rates:\n\n* Petroleum products\n* Automobiles and other vehicles\n* Tobacco and tobacco products, alcoholic beverages\n* Luxury products<ref name=invest/>\n\n==== Banking and Insurance Transaction Tax ====\nThe transactions and services performed by banks and insurance companies are subject to the tax. Taxpayers consist of banks, bankers and insurance companies. Regardless of the nature of the transaction, they are all subject to BITT. Taxes will be levied on the money they collect as interest, commission and expenditure Bankers' certain transactions and services defined in the Law No. 6802 are the subject of the Tax. These transactions and services . Bankers' other transactions are subject to VAT.<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Stamp duty ====\nThere are many documents that are subject to stamp duty such as contracts, letter of credit, letter of guarantee, financial statements, payrolls. The stamp tax is collected at a rate of 0.89% and 0.948% as a percentage of the value of the document and is collected at a fixed price (a predetermined price) for some documents.<ref name=invest/>\n\n=== Taxes on wealth ===\n\n==== Inheritance and gift tax ====\nThe subject of this tax is Turkish citizens who have worldwide assets. Foreigners who has a permanent residency are liable to inheritance and gift tax on assets located in Turkey and assets received from Turkish citizens. Foreigners who hasn't a permanent residency are liable to this tax on assets located in Turkey. There is a progressive tax rate varies from 10% to 30% and 1% to 10% on the items received as gift or inherited.<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Property tax ====\nProperty tax levied on buildings and lands in Turkey. Per annum, property tax is calculated at rates ranging from 0.1% to 0.3% by the concerned municipality. Within the metropolitan cities, these rates have increased by 100%.\n\nOwner of the building/land is the taxpayer and has any usufruct right on the building/land or if neither of these exists anyone that uses the building/land is regarded as its owner.<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Motor vehicle tax ====\nThe subjects of the tax are vehicles registered to traffic bureaus or offices such as land motors also helicopters and airplanes registered to the Directorate General of Civil Aviation.\n\nTaxpayers are civil and legal persons who own motor vehicles registered in their own names in the traffic register and civil aviation records kept by the Ministry of Transport, Maritime Affairs and Communications.\n\nIn every year, at the beginning of January, MVT is assessed and accrued. There are two equal installments in January and July each year.\n\nThere are three categories for motor vehicles according to motor vehicle tax:\n\n# cars, motorcycles and terrain vehicles etc.\n# minibuses, panel vans, motorized caravans, busses, trucks etc.\n# planes and helicopters<ref name=ministry/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Europe in topic|Taxation in}}\n\n[[Category:Taxation in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Turkish law]]\n", "text_old": "Taxation has an important part in Turkish economy. Turkey has 25.5% tax-GDP ration (in 2016).<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|date=2017|title=Revenue Statistics 2017 - Turkey|url=https://www.oecd.org/tax/revenue-statistics-turkey.pdf|journal=OECD Revenue Statistics 2017|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref> Most of the taxes are levied by central government. However some speficic taxes are levied by municipalities. \n\n== Tax Procedure Law ==\nTaxation system in Turkey is regulated by the Tax Procedure (TP) Law. It regulates the rights, burdens, carrying out duties along with principals of accrual. This Law consist of procedural and official provisions of all tax laws. The TP has five main sections: taxation, taxpayer duties, valuation, penalty provisions, tax cases.<ref name=ministry>{{Cite web |date=2016 |title=Turkish Taxation System |url=http://www.gib.gov.tr/sites/default/files/fileadmin/taxation_system2016.pdf |publisher=The Republic of Turkey Ministry of Finance Revenue Administration}}</ref>\n\n== Taxes ==\nThe Turkish tax legislation can be divided into three main categories:\n\n# Income taxes\n# Taxes on expenditure\n# Taxes on wealth\n\n=== Income taxes ===\nThe Turkish tax legislation has two main income taxes, they are individual income tax and corporate income tax. Many rules and provisions are the same for individual income tax and corporations, especially in terms of income elements and the determination of net income. However individual income tax and corporate income tax are regulated by different laws.<ref name=invest>{{Cite web|url=http://www.invest.gov.tr/en-US/investmentguide/investorsguide/Pages/Taxes.aspx|title=Taxes - Invest in Turkey|website=www.invest.gov.tr|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref>\n\n==== Individual income tax ====\nThe subject of individual income tax is the real people. The meaning of income is the net amount of revenues derived by a person within a year. According to Income Tax Law, incomes may be listed such as:\n\n* Business profits\n* Agricultural profits\n* Salaries and wages\n* Income from independent personal services\n* Income from immovable property and rights (rental income)\n* Income from movable property (income from capital investment)\n* Other income and earnings\n\n<nowiki>#</nowiki>Variety of individual income tax rate is between 15% and 35%.<ref name=invest/>\n\nResidency criterion is the key point for the taxes. Residents in Turkey are liable at tax on their worldwide income and they are considered as \"full tax liable\". Non-residents are only subject to taxes on their revenues gained in Turkey and they are considered as \"limited tax liable\". Residents are individuals with legal permanent residence and those who reside in Turkey for more than six months during one year.<ref>[http://www.gep.gov.tr/tmp/_Gep1.pdf Turkish Tax System in General]</ref>\n\n==== Corporate income taxes ====\nIf the income elements listed in the Income Tax Law are derived by corporations, taxation is enforceable on the legal entities of these corporations. Corporate taxpayers has been described as:\n\n* Capital companies\n* Cooperatives\n* Public economic enterprises\n* Economic enterprises owned by associations and foundations\n* Joint ventures<ref name=invest/>\n\nIf the legal headquarters or effective management of corporations are located in Turkey, they are subject to taxes derived from world-wide business. They are also called as resident companies.\n\n=== Taxes on expenditure ===\n\n==== Value Added Tax (VAT) ====\nGenerally, the VAT rate varies from 1%, 8% to 18%. There is a huge range of subject subject to VAT such as industrial, commercial, agricultural, independent professional goods and services.<ref name=invest/> \n\nPeople who has to pay VAT are described as:\n\n* Those supplying goods and services,\n* Those importing goods or services,\n* Those required to complete customs formalities in case of transit of goods through Turkey,\n* General Directorates of Postal Services (PT and Telecom) and radio and television corporations,\n* Organizers of any kind of chance and gambling,\n* Organizers of shows, concerts and sporting events with the participation of professional artists and professional sportsmen,\n* Lessors of goods and rights stated in Article 70 of the PIT Law,\n* Applicants for optional tax liability<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Special Consumption Tax (SCT) ====\nThe goods which are subject to SCT is in the list. For these products, the Special Consumption Tax is collected only once. Generally 4 product group are subject to SCT at different rates:\n\n* Petroleum products\n* Automobiles and other vehicles\n* Tobacco and tobacco products, alcoholic beverages\n* Luxury products<ref name=invest/>\n\n==== Banking and Insurance Transaction Tax ====\nThe transactions and services performed by banks and insurance companies are subject to the tax. Taxpayers consist of banks, bankers and insurance companies. Regardless of the nature of the transaction, they are all subject to BITT. Taxes will be levied on the money they collect as interest, commission and expenditure Bankers' certain transactions and services defined in the Law No. 6802 are the subject of the Tax. These transactions and services . Bankers' other transactions are subject to VAT.<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Stamp duty ====\nThere are many documents that are subject to stamp duty such as contracts, letter of credit, letter of guarantee, financial statements, payrolls. The stamp tax is collected at a rate of 0.89% and 0.948% as a percentage of the value of the document and is collected at a fixed price (a predetermined price) for some documents.<ref name=invest/>\n\n=== Taxes on wealth ===\n\n==== Inheritance and gift tax ====\nThe subject of this tax is Turkish citizens who have worldwide assets. Foreigners who has a permanent residency are liable to inheritance and gift tax on assets located in Turkey and assets received from Turkish citizens. Foreigners who hasn't a permanent residency are liable to this tax on assets located in Turkey. There is a progressive tax rate varies from 10% to 30% and 1% to 10% on the items received as gift or inherited.<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Property tax ====\nProperty tax levied on buildings and lands in Turkey. Per annum, property tax is calculated at rates ranging from 0.1% to 0.3% by the concerned municipality. Within the metropolitan cities, these rates have increased by 100%. \n\nOwner of the building/land is the taxpayer and has any usufruct right on the building/land or if neither of these exists anyone that uses the building/land is regarded as its owner.<ref name=ministry/>\n\n==== Motor vehicle tax ====\nThe subjects of the tax are vehicles registered to traffic bureaus or offices such as land motors also helicopters and airplanes registered to the Directorate General of Civil Aviation.\n\nTaxpayers are civil and legal persons who own motor vehicles registered in their own names in the traffic register and civil aviation records kept by the Ministry of Transport, Maritime Affairs and Communications.\n\nIn every year, at the beginning of January, MVT is assessed and accrued. There are two equal installments in January and July each year.\n\nThere are three categories for motor vehicles according to motor vehicle tax:\n\n# cars, motorcycles and terrain vehicles etc.\n# minibuses, panel vans, motorized caravans, busses, trucks etc.\n# planes and helicopters<ref name=ministry/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Europe in topic|Taxation in}}\n\n[[Category:Taxation in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Turkish law]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo/generalfixes, replaced: speficic \u2192 specific", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxation_in_Turkey"}
{"title_page": "N\u00e9stor Espenilla", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Nestor A. Espenilla Jr.\n|image       = File:Nestor Espenilla Jr. (cropped).jpg\n|office      = 4th [[Governor of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]] \n|term_start  = 3 July 2017\n|term_end    = 23 February 2019\n|president   = [[Rodrigo Duterte]]\n|deputy       = Diwa Guinigundo <br/> Ma. Almasara Tua\u00f1o-Amador <br/> Chuchi Fonacier\n|predecessor = [[Amando Tetangco Jr.]]\n|successor   = [[Benjamin Diokno]]\n|birth_name = Nestor Aldave Espenilla Jr.\n|birth_date   = 12 October 1958\n|birth_place  = [[San Jacinto, Masbate|San Jacinto]], [[Masbate]], [[Philippines]]\n|death_date   = {{Death date and age|2019|02|23|1958|10|12|df=yes}}\n|death_place  = [[Manila, Philippines|Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n|death_cause = [[Tongue Cancer]]\n|profession  = Banker, Economist\n|spouse       = \n|alma_mater   = [[University of the Philippines]] <br> [[National Graduate Institute for Policy Studies]]\n|signature   = \n}}\n\n'''Nestor Aldave Espenilla Jr.''' (12 October 1958 \u2013 23 February 2019) was the fourth [[Governor of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas|Governor]] of the [[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]. He was appointed by [[Philippine President]] [[Rodrigo Duterte]] on 8 May 2017 and assumed office on 3 July 2017. He previously served as the bank's deputy governor under his predecessor [[Amando Tetangco Jr.]]<ref name=BSP>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=4402|title=Turnover of the BSP Governorship|publisher=[[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]|date=3 July 2017|accessdate=3 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Doris>{{cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/229144/selection-insider-head-bsp-hailed|title=Selection of \u2018insider\u2019 to head BSP hailed|last=Dumlao-Abadilla|first=Doris|date=9 May 2017|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nEspenilla was born in [[San Jacinto, Masbate]], to Nestor Espenilla, Sr. and Arminda Aldave-Espenilla, the only son in a family of five. When he was 10 years old, his mother established a small rural bank, the Rural Bank of San Jacinto (Masbate), Inc., which grew and now has several branches in the province and in neighboring [[Sorsogon|Sorsogon Province]]. The bank is now managed by his three sisters.<ref name=Rimando>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/business/169235-who-is-new-bsp-governor-nestor-espenilla-jr|title=Who is new BSP governor Nestor Espenilla?|first=Lala|last=Rimando|work=[[Rappler]]|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=BSP2>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=2005|title=Statement of Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas Governor Amando M. Tetangco Jr. Re: Legacy Banks|publisher=[[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]|date=8 February 2009|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Ferriols>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/business/438274/tetangco-defends-espenilla|title=Tetangco defends Espenilla|first=Des|last=Ferriols|newspaper=[[The Philippine STAR]]|date=9 February 2009|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nEspenilla graduated from the Ateneo De Manila High School in 1977.  He then graduated with a [[Bachelor of Science]] degree in [[Business Economics]] ([[magna cum laude]]) from the [[University of the Philippines]] in 1981. He also earned his [[Master of Business Administration]] honors degree from the University of the Philippines in 1982 and obtained his [[Master of Science]] degree in [[Policy Studies|Policy Science]] from the [[National Graduate Institute for Policy Studies]] in [[Tokyo, Japan|Tokyo]], [[Japan]] in 1988.<ref name=Doris/><ref name=AsianBanker>{{cite web|url=http://www.theasianbanker.com/press-releases/deputy-governor-nestor-espenilla-jr.-appointed-next-bangko-sentral-ng-pilipinas-chief|title=Deputy Governor Nestor Espenilla Jr. appointed next Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas chief|date=9 May 2017|publisher=[[The Asian Banker]]|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAfter graduating from the University of the Philippines in 1981, Espenilla was hired by the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas as a debt analyst.<ref name=AsianBanker/> Known to his co-workers as \"Nesting\",<ref name=Padin>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2017/05/09/1698115/espenilla-named-bangko-sentral-chief|title=Espenilla named Bangko Sentral chief|first=Mary Grace|last=Padin|newspaper=[[The Philippine STAR]]|date=9 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> Espenilla steadily rose through the ranks, earning his stripes in economic research and international operations, before he was appointed by [[President of the Philippines|Philippine president]] [[Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo]] in 2005 as deputy governor for supervision and examination sector<ref name=Remo>{{cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/21353/philippine-central-bank%E2%80%99s-top-guns|title=Philippine central bank\u2019s top guns|first=Michelle|last=Remo|date=26 September 2011|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> under the administration of his predecessor Amando Tetangco Jr.<ref name=BSP/><ref name=Doris/><ref name=Rimando/> When Philippine president [[Benigno S. Aquino III]] took office in 2010, Tetangco's term would have expired, but Aquino reappointed him and his deputies\u2014including Espenilla\u2014to their positions.<ref name=Fojas>{{cite news|url=http://lifestyle.mb.com.ph/2017/06/04/governor-signing-off/|title=Governor, Signing Off|first=Sarah Grace|last=Fojas|newspaper=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=4 June 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===As BSP deputy governor===\nAs deputy governor, Espenilla was responsible for the BSP's regulatory policies with regards to the entire banking system, playing the \"[[Good cop/bad cop|bad cop]]\" whenever it deals with banks that were revealed to have violated regulations.<ref name=Rimando/> Among his accomplishments as deputy governor include the closure of [[Banco Filipino]], a major savings and loan bank owned by the Aguirre family, on 17 March 2011 after an investigation by Espenilla's team revealed that depositors' money had been diverted to entities controlled by the bank's owners and officers.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro>{{cite web|url=https://www.euromoney.com/article/b13c957bpkcwbq/philippines-espenilla-publicly-positive-appointment-but-behind-closed-doors|title=Philippines' Espenilla: publicly positive appointment, but behind closed doors\u2026|date=9 June 2017|publisher=[[Euromoney]]|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref> Espenilla also ordered the investigation into and closure of LBC Development Bank, owned by the [[Araneta family]] that established courier firm [[LBC Express]]. It was revealed in the investigation that the bank incurred P6.09 billion in deposit liabilities after a build-up of cash advances to its affiliate businesses.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/><ref name=Rosero>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/money/content/232398/advances-insufficient-assets-led-to-lbc-bank-closure-bsp/story/|title=Advances, insufficient assets led to LBC bank closure \u2013 BSP|first=Earl Victor|last=Rosero|publisher=GMA News Online|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nEspenilla also sat as the BSP's representative to the [[Anti-Money Laundering Council (Philippines)|Anti-Money Laundering Council]], the Philippines' financial intelligence, financial counter-terrorism and anti-money laundering agency. He sat as chairperson of the council on behalf of Tetangco.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/> One of his key accomplishments as head of the council was the filing of a petition in the [[Court of Appeals of the Philippines|Court of Appeals]] to freeze the bank accounts of former [[Ferdinand Marcos|Marcos administration]] [[Department of Trade and Industry (Philippines)|Trade and Industry]] [[Secretary of Trade and Industry (Philippines)|minister]] [[Roberto Ongpin]] after it was revealed that he allegedly made two behest loans with the [[Development Bank of the Philippines]] totaling P660 million to buy the government-owned bank's shares in [[Manuel V. Pangilinan|Philex Mining Corporation]]. The Appellate Court froze 100 of Ongpin's bank accounts on 6 December 2012 but lifted the freeze order on 7 May 2013.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/><ref name=Reformina>{{cite web|url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/business/05/08/13/freeze-order-bank-accounts-ongpin-lifted|title=Freeze order on bank accounts of Ongpin lifted|first=Ina|last=Reformina|date=8 May 2013|publisher=[[ABS-CBNnews.com]]|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Lucas>{{cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/120935/ca-lifts-freeze-order-on-ongpin-bank-accounts|title=CA lifts freeze order on Ongpin bank accounts|first=Daxim|last=Lucas|date=8 May 2013|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2016, Espenilla ordered the P1 billion-fine against [[Rizal Commercial Banking Corporation]], which is owned by the [[Alfonso Yuchengco|Yuchengco family]]. The bank was involved in the 2016 [[Bangladesh Bank robbery]], having been used by hackers to launder and withdraw $81 million which was stolen from [[Bangladesh Bank]]'s account in the [[Federal Reserve Bank of New York]].<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/>\n\nEspenilla also led the establishment of the National Retail Payment System (NRPS), a framework which will be used for the Philippines' gradual shift from [[cash]] and [[cheque|check-based payments]] to [[Electronic funds transfer|electronic means]]. The shift is expected to improve efficiency in transactions among and between banks and other financial institutions involved in [[financial technology]].<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Agcaoili>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com:8080/business/2017/03/10/1679555/bsp-banks-pursue-e-payment-system|title=BSP, banks pursue e-payment system|first=Lawrence|last=Agcaoili|newspaper=[[The Philippine STAR]]|date=10 March 2017|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Appointment as BSP governor===\nPhilippine President Rodrigo Duterte appointed Espenilla as BSP governor on 8 May 2017 and assumed office on 3 July 2017. He bested other contenders for the position, including former Philippine President Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo, fellow BSP deputy governor Diwa Gunigundo, [[EastWest Bank]] vice chairman and CEO Antonio Moncupa Jr. and former Trade and Industry Secretary Peter Favila. His selection was hailed as a wise decision by several key personalities in the government and the banking sector, including Tetangco, [[Department of Finance (Philippines)|Finance]] [[Secretary of Finance (Philippines)|Secretary]] [[Carlos Dominguez III]], [[Security Bank]] president and CEO Alfonso Salcedo Jr. and [[ING Group|ING Bank Manila]] senior economist Joey Cuyegkeng.<ref name=Doris/><ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Padin/><ref name=Lema>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-phlippines-cenbank-governor-idUSKBN18415O|title=Philippines picks central bank insider Espenilla as next governor|first=Karen|last=Lema|work=[[Reuters]]|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Cabuenas>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/money/companies/609956/central-banker-espenilla-succeeds-tetangco-as-bsp-governor/story/|title=Central banker Espenilla succeeds Tetangco as BSP governor|first=Jon Viktor|last=Cabuenas|publisher=GMA News Online|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref> Under his leadership, the BSP continued to push reforms under the \"Continuity Plus Plus\" theme. Digitalization of the country's retail payment system was also spearheaded under his term. In 2018, under his tenure, Congress passed an act amending the BSP Charter. On February 16, 2019, almost a week before his death, President Duterte signed the act into law effectively \"strengthening BSP's capacity to foster price and financial stability\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=4942|title=President Duterte Signs BSP's Charter Amendments Into Law|publisher=Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas|date=16 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nEspenilla was married to Maria Teresita Festin-Espenilla, a [[microfinance]] specialist for the [[United States Agency for International Development]] (USAID), and had a daughter and two sons with her. They met at the University of the Philippines while studying for their [[master's degree]]s.<ref name=Arnaldo>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/bsps-gentle-giant-gets-ready-for-his-close-up/|title=BSP\u2019s gentle giant gets ready for his close-up|first=Ma. Stella|last=Arnaldo|newspaper=[[BusinessMirror]]|date=11 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> Espenilla enjoyed his free time either playing [[golf]], [[bowling]], [[badminton]] or going to the [[gym]]. He also liked going on long walks with his dog (potentially on the beach), watching TV or movies and cooking for his family on Sundays.<ref name=Remo/>\n\n==Death==\nEspenilla died on 23 February 2019 at the age of 60 due to complications brought about by tongue cancer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bworldonline.com/central-bank-chief-espenilla-passes-away/|title=Central bank chief Espenilla passes away|first=Melissa Luz|last=Lopez|newspaper=[[BusinessWorld]]|date=February 23, 2019|accessdate=February 24, 2019}}</ref> He had been undergoing cancer treatment for more than a year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=4952|title=BSP Statement on the passing of Governor Nestor A. Espenilla, Jr.|publisher=Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas|date=24 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-gov}}\n{{succession box\n|title=[[Governor of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]\n|years=2017\u20132019\n|before = [[Amando Tetangco Jr.]]\n|after = [[Benjamin Diokno]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Espenilla, Nestor Jr.}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Governors of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]\n[[Category:Benigno Aquino III Administration personnel]]\n[[Category:Duterte Administration personnel]]\n[[Category:University of the Philippines alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Masbate]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in the Philippines]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Nestor A. Espenilla Jr.\n|image       = File:Nestor Espenilla Jr. (cropped).jpg\n|office      = 4th [[Governor of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]] \n|term_start  = 3 July 2017\n|term_end    = 23 February 2019\n|president   = [[Rodrigo Duterte]]\n|deputy       = Diwa Guinigundo <br/> Ma. Almasara Tua\u00f1o-Amador <br/> Chuchi Fonacier\n|predecessor = [[Amando Tetangco Jr.]]\n|successor   = [[Benjamin Diokno]]\n|birth_name = Nestor Aldave Espenilla Jr.\n|birth_date   = 12 October 1958\n|birth_place  = [[San Jacinto, Masbate|San Jacinto]], [[Masbate]], [[Philippines]]\n|death_date   = {{Death date and age|2019|02|23|1958|10|12|df=yes}}\n|death_place  = [[Manila, Philippines|Manila]], [[Philippines]]\n|death_cause = [[Tongue Cancer]]\n|profession  = Banker, Economist\n|spouse       = \n|alma_mater   = [[University of the Philippines]] <br> [[National Graduate Institute for Policy Studies]]\n|signature   = \n}}\n\n'''Nestor Aldave Espenilla Jr.''' (12 October 1958 \u2013 23 February 2019) was the fourth [[Governor of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas|Governor]] of the [[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]. He was appointed by [[Philippine President]] [[Rodrigo Duterte]] on 8 May 2017 and assumed office on 3 July 2017. He previously served as the bank's deputy governor under his predecessor [[Amando Tetangco Jr.]]<ref name=BSP>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=4402|title=Turnover of the BSP Governorship|publisher=[[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]|date=3 July 2017|accessdate=3 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Doris>{{cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/229144/selection-insider-head-bsp-hailed|title=Selection of \u2018insider\u2019 to head BSP hailed|last=Dumlao-Abadilla|first=Doris|date=9 May 2017|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nEspenilla was born in [[San Jacinto, Masbate]], to Nestor Espenilla, Sr. and Arminda Aldave-Espenilla, the only son in a family of five. When he was 10 years old, his mother established a small rural bank, the Rural Bank of San Jacinto (Masbate), Inc., which grew and now has several branches in the province and in neighboring [[Sorsogon|Sorsogon Province]]. The bank is now managed by his three sisters.<ref name=Rimando>{{cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/business/169235-who-is-new-bsp-governor-nestor-espenilla-jr|title=Who is new BSP governor Nestor Espenilla?|first=Lala|last=Rimando|work=[[Rappler]]|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=BSP2>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=2005|title=Statement of Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas Governor Amando M. Tetangco Jr. Re: Legacy Banks|publisher=[[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]|date=8 February 2009|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Ferriols>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/business/438274/tetangco-defends-espenilla|title=Tetangco defends Espenilla|first=Des|last=Ferriols|newspaper=[[The Philippine STAR]]|date=9 February 2009|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\nEspenilla graduated from the Ateneo De Manila High School in 1977.  He then graduated with a [[Bachelor of Science]] degree in [[Business Economics]] ([[magna cum laude]]) from the [[University of the Philippines]] in 1981. He also earned his [[Master of Business Administration]] honors degree from the University of the Philippines in 1982 and obtained his [[Master of Science]] degree in [[Policy Studies|Policy Science]] from the [[National Graduate Institute for Policy Studies]] in [[Tokyo, Japan|Tokyo]], [[Japan]] in 1988.<ref name=Doris/><ref name=AsianBanker>{{cite web|url=http://www.theasianbanker.com/press-releases/deputy-governor-nestor-espenilla-jr.-appointed-next-bangko-sentral-ng-pilipinas-chief|title=Deputy Governor Nestor Espenilla Jr. appointed next Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas chief|date=9 May 2017|publisher=[[The Asian Banker]]|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nAfter graduating from the University of the Philippines in 1981, Espenilla was hired by the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas as a debt analyst.<ref name=AsianBanker/> Known to his co-workers as \"Nesting\",<ref name=Padin>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com/headlines/2017/05/09/1698115/espenilla-named-bangko-sentral-chief|title=Espenilla named Bangko Sentral chief|first=Mary Grace|last=Padin|newspaper=[[The Philippine STAR]]|date=9 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> Espenilla steadily rose through the ranks, earning his stripes in economic research and international operations, before he was appointed by [[President of the Philippines|Philippine president]] [[Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo]] in 2005 as deputy governor for supervision and examination sector<ref name=Remo>{{cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/21353/philippine-central-bank%E2%80%99s-top-guns|title=Philippine central bank\u2019s top guns|first=Michelle|last=Remo|date=26 September 2011|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> under the administration of his predecessor Amando Tetangco Jr.<ref name=BSP/><ref name=Doris/><ref name=Rimando/> When Philippine president [[Benigno S. Aquino III]] took office in 2010, Tetangco's term would have expired, but Aquino reappointed him and his deputies\u2014including Espenilla\u2014to their positions.<ref name=Fojas>{{cite news|url=http://lifestyle.mb.com.ph/2017/06/04/governor-signing-off/|title=Governor, Signing Off|first=Sarah Grace|last=Fojas|newspaper=[[Manila Bulletin]]|date=4 June 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===As BSP deputy governor===\nAs deputy governor, Espenilla was responsible for the BSP's regulatory policies with regards to the entire banking system, playing the \"[[Good cop/bad cop|bad cop]]\" whenever it deals with banks that were revealed to have violated regulations.<ref name=Rimando/> Among his accomplishments as deputy governor include the closure of [[Banco Filipino]], a major savings and loan bank owned by the Aguirre family, on 17 March 2011 after an investigation by Espenilla's team revealed that depositors' money had been diverted to entities controlled by the bank's owners and officers.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro>{{cite web|url=https://www.euromoney.com/article/b13c957bpkcwbq/philippines-espenilla-publicly-positive-appointment-but-behind-closed-doors|title=Philippines' Espenilla: publicly positive appointment, but behind closed doors\u2026|date=9 June 2017|publisher=[[Euromoney]]|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref> Espenilla also ordered the investigation into and closure of LBC Development Bank, owned by the [[Araneta family]] that established courier firm [[LBC Express]]. It was revealed in the investigation that the bank incurred P6.09 billion in deposit liabilities after a build-up of cash advances to its affiliate businesses.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/><ref name=Rosero>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/money/content/232398/advances-insufficient-assets-led-to-lbc-bank-closure-bsp/story/|title=Advances, insufficient assets led to LBC bank closure \u2013 BSP|first=Earl Victor|last=Rosero|publisher=GMA News Online|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nEspenilla also sat as the BSP's representative to the [[Anti-Money Laundering Council (Philippines)|Anti-Money Laundering Council]], the Philippines' financial intelligence, financial counter-terrorism and anti-money laundering agency. He sat as chairperson of the council on behalf of Tetangco.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/> One of his key accomplishments as head of the council was the filing of a petition in the [[Court of Appeals of the Philippines|Court of Appeals]] to freeze the bank accounts of former [[Ferdinand Marcos|Marcos administration]] [[Department of Trade and Industry (Philippines)|Trade and Industry]] [[Secretary of Trade and Industry (Philippines)|minister]] [[Roberto Ongpin]] after it was revealed that he allegedly made two behest loans with the [[Development Bank of the Philippines]] totaling P660 million to buy the government-owned bank's shares in [[Manuel V. Pangilinan|Philex Mining Corporation]]. The Appelate Court froze 100 of Ongpin's bank accounts on 6 December 2012 but lifted the freeze order on 7 May 2013.<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/><ref name=Reformina>{{cite web|url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/business/05/08/13/freeze-order-bank-accounts-ongpin-lifted|title=Freeze order on bank accounts of Ongpin lifted|first=Ina|last=Reformina|date=8 May 2013|publisher=[[ABS-CBNnews.com]]|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Lucas>{{cite news|url=http://business.inquirer.net/120935/ca-lifts-freeze-order-on-ongpin-bank-accounts|title=CA lifts freeze order on Ongpin bank accounts|first=Daxim|last=Lucas|date=8 May 2013|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2016, Espenilla ordered the P1 billion-fine against [[Rizal Commercial Banking Corporation]], which is owned by the [[Alfonso Yuchengco|Yuchengco family]]. The bank was involved in the 2016 [[Bangladesh Bank robbery]], having been used by hackers to launder and withdraw $81 million which was stolen from [[Bangladesh Bank]]'s account in the [[Federal Reserve Bank of New York]].<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Euro/>\n\nEspenilla also led the establishment of the National Retail Payment System (NRPS), a framework which will be used for the Philippines' gradual shift from [[cash]] and [[cheque|check-based payments]] to [[Electronic funds transfer|electronic means]]. The shift is expected to improve efficiency in transactions among and between banks and other financial institutions involved in [[financial technology]].<ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Agcaoili>{{cite news|url=http://www.philstar.com:8080/business/2017/03/10/1679555/bsp-banks-pursue-e-payment-system|title=BSP, banks pursue e-payment system|first=Lawrence|last=Agcaoili|newspaper=[[The Philippine STAR]]|date=10 March 2017|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Appointment as BSP governor===\nPhilippine President Rodrigo Duterte appointed Espenilla as BSP governor on 8 May 2017 and assumed office on 3 July 2017. He bested other contenders for the position, including former Philippine President Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo, fellow BSP deputy governor Diwa Gunigundo, [[EastWest Bank]] vice chairman and CEO Antonio Moncupa Jr. and former Trade and Industry Secretary Peter Favila. His selection was hailed as a wise decision by several key personalities in the government and the banking sector, including Tetangco, [[Department of Finance (Philippines)|Finance]] [[Secretary of Finance (Philippines)|Secretary]] [[Carlos Dominguez III]], [[Security Bank]] president and CEO Alfonso Salcedo Jr. and [[ING Group|ING Bank Manila]] senior economist Joey Cuyegkeng.<ref name=Doris/><ref name=Rimando/><ref name=Padin/><ref name=Lema>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-phlippines-cenbank-governor-idUSKBN18415O|title=Philippines picks central bank insider Espenilla as next governor|first=Karen|last=Lema|work=[[Reuters]]|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Cabuenas>{{cite web|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/money/companies/609956/central-banker-espenilla-succeeds-tetangco-as-bsp-governor/story/|title=Central banker Espenilla succeeds Tetangco as BSP governor|first=Jon Viktor|last=Cabuenas|publisher=GMA News Online|date=8 May 2017|accessdate=28 July 2017}}</ref> Under his leadership, the BSP continued to push reforms under the \"Continuity Plus Plus\" theme. Digitalization of the country's retail payment system was also spearheaded under his term. In 2018, under his tenure, Congress passed an act amending the BSP Charter. On February 16, 2019, almost a week before his death, President Duterte signed the act into law effectively \"strengthening BSP's capacity to foster price and financial stability\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=4942|title=President Duterte Signs BSP's Charter Amendments Into Law|publisher=Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas|date=16 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nEspenilla was married to Maria Teresita Festin-Espenilla, a [[microfinance]] specialist for the [[United States Agency for International Development]] (USAID), and had a daughter and two sons with her. They met at the University of the Philippines while studying for their [[master's degree]]s.<ref name=Arnaldo>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessmirror.com.ph/bsps-gentle-giant-gets-ready-for-his-close-up/|title=BSP\u2019s gentle giant gets ready for his close-up|first=Ma. Stella|last=Arnaldo|newspaper=[[BusinessMirror]]|date=11 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> Espenilla enjoyed his free time either playing [[golf]], [[bowling]], [[badminton]] or going to the [[gym]]. He also liked going on long walks with his dog (potentially on the beach), watching TV or movies and cooking for his family on Sundays.<ref name=Remo/>\n\n==Death==\nEspenilla died on 23 February 2019 at the age of 60 due to complications brought about by tongue cancer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bworldonline.com/central-bank-chief-espenilla-passes-away/|title=Central bank chief Espenilla passes away|first=Melissa Luz|last=Lopez|newspaper=[[BusinessWorld]]|date=February 23, 2019|accessdate=February 24, 2019}}</ref> He had been undergoing cancer treatment for more than a year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/media.asp?id=4952|title=BSP Statement on the passing of Governor Nestor A. Espenilla, Jr.|publisher=Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas|date=24 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-gov}}\n{{succession box\n|title=[[Governor of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]\n|years=2017\u20132019\n|before = [[Amando Tetangco Jr.]]\n|after = [[Benjamin Diokno]]\n}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Espenilla, Nestor Jr.}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:Governors of the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]]\n[[Category:Benigno Aquino III Administration personnel]]\n[[Category:Duterte Administration personnel]]\n[[Category:University of the Philippines alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Masbate]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in the Philippines]]\n", "name_user": "Will Sandberg", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%A9stor_Espenilla"}
{"title_page": "Taxation in Italy", "text_new": "{{Taxation}}\n'''Taxation in Italy''' is levied by the central and regional governments and is collected by the [[Italian Agency of Revenue]] (Agenzia delle Entrate). Total tax revenue in 2018 was 42,4% of GDP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oecd.org/tax/revenue-statistics-italy.pdf|title=Revenue Statistics 2018 - Italy|last=|first=|date=2018|website=OECD}}</ref>  Most important earnings are: [[income tax]], [[social security]], [[corporate tax]] and [[value added tax]].  All of those are collected at national level, but some of those differs across regions. Personal income taxation in Italy is [[Progressive tax|progressive]].\n\n==Income tax==\nEmployment income is subject to a progressive income tax, IRPEF (''Imposta sul reddito delle persone fisiche'') applying to all workers. By government is set tax rate according to income, but the regions can add an additional 0.7% to 3.33%. Each region not only has a regional income tax, a municipal income tax can be levied which ranges from 0.1% to 0.9%. Municipalities can also establish progressive tax rates applicable to the national income bracket.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://taxsummaries.pwc.com/uk/taxsummaries/wwts.nsf/ID/Italy-Individual-Taxes-on-personal-income|title=Italy - Taxes on personal income|website=taxsummaries.pwc.com|access-date=2019-04-28}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, the personal income tax rates were as follows:\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Income range\n! Tax rate<ref>{{cite web|url=https://taxing.it/personal-income-tax-irpef-rates/|title=Personal income tax (IRPEF) rates|author=|first=|date=2018|website=taxing.it|publisher=IRPEF - Imposta sul reddito delle persone fisiche|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n| \u20ac0 \u2014 \u20ac15,000\n| 23%\n|-\n| \u20ac15,000 \u2014 \u20ac28,000\n| 27%\n|-\n| \u20ac28,000 \u2014 \u20ac55,000\n| 38% \n|-\n| \u20ac55,000 \u2014 \u20ac75,000\n| 41% \n|-\n| over \u20ac75,000\n| 43%\n|}\n\nIndividuals are considered [[resident for tax purposes]] if for the greater part of the tax year they satisfy any of the following conditions:\n\n* their habitual abode is in Italy,\n* the centre of their vital interests is located in Italy, or\n* they are registered at the Office of Records of the Resident Population in Italy.\n\n===Exemption Area===\nDue to the different types of income, exemption from IRPEF is determined at:\n\n*8,000 euros, for subordinate workers, if their employment period coincides with the entire year;\n*7,500 euros, for pensioners under 75 years of age, if the pension is cashed in for the entire year, and for those receiving palimony from ex spouses;\n*7,750 euros, for pensioners aged 75 or older, with a pension period that coincides with the whole year;\n*4,800 euros, no matter how many days they work a year, for taxpayers with other types of income.\nThe area exempt from IRPEF increases further if there are dependent family members.\n\n==Corporate tax==\nItalian corporate entities are subject to Corporate Income Tax, IRES (''Imposta sul reddito delle societ\u00e0'') and to Regional Production Tax, IRAP (''Imposta regionale sulle attivit\u00e0 produttive''). Italy has one of the highest corporate tax - currently at 24% - across EU28, average tax in EU is 21.3% (2018) and is still decreasing, however, Italy has after elections in March 2018 stop depreciation. [https://d3fy651gv2fhd3.cloudfront.net/charts/italy-corporate-tax-rate@2x.png?s=itacorptax&v=201804031046a1&d1=20000428&d2=20190428&mean=1&url2=/european-union/corporate-tax-rate]\n\n*The rate of corporate income tax (IRES) since 1 January 2017 is 24% (previously it was 27.5%, maximum 53.2% in 1981). Some corporations are exempted from corporate tax, such as charitable foundations, church institutions and sports clubs.\n*The standard rate of regional tax (IRAP) is 3.9%, however, [[Regions of Italy|regional authorities]] may increase or decrease rate of standart tax by up to 0.92%. In addition, different IRAP rates are used to differ sectors of the economy in each region. For example, the rate for banks and other financial institutions is 5.57% in [[Abruzzo]], [[Apulia]], [[Lazio]], [[Lombardy]], [[Piedmont]] and [[Veneto]], but only 4.65% in [[Emilia-Romagna]]).<ref>https://www.guidafisco.it/calcolo-irap-aliquote-851 guidafisco.it</ref> The tax is calculated differently from IRES, adding the cost of fixed-term workers (before 2016 the cost of every employee was counted). Up to 10% of regional tax (IRAP) is deductible in calculating the tax base for corporate income tax (IRES) purposes.\n\n==Value added tax==\nValue added tax or shortcut [[Value-added tax|VAT]], (in Italian ''Imposta sul valore aggiunto'', shortcut IVA) is a consumption tax charged at a standard rate of 22%, which haven't changed for years. Italian government reduced VAT rates at 10% for some listed pharmaceuticals and listed power supplies, passenger transport that is not specifically exempted, admissions to cultural and entertainment events, hotels, restaurants and  reduced only to 4% to listed food, drinks and agricultural products. The Italian [[Value-added tax|VAT]] regime is part of the [[European Union value added tax]] system. Specific supplied goods on a market, such as education, healthcare, hospitals, public postal services are by law excluded out of VAT, same fore specially listed financial transactions, such as transfers of money and transfers of  business parts. In the case of a taxable person (VAT number holders), input VAT on purchases of goods and services related to business activity generally is allowed for recovery. Special limitations apply in relation to specific items (e.g. cars, entertainment expenses).\n\nThe filing deadline for VAT returns is 30 April of the next year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://taxsummaries.pwc.com/ID/Italy-Individual-Other-taxes|title=Italy - Value-added tax (VAT)|last=|first=|date=2018|website=TaxSummaries|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Social security==\n\n=== Employment relationship (staff) ===\nSocial security contributions apply to everyone in the workforce, divided into contributions by the employer and those by the employee; both sides are obliged to participate. Employers must register with the Italian Social Security Administration (''Istituto Nazionale Previdenza Sociale'' or INPS). The total contribution rate fluctuates around 40% of the employee's wage, depending on their position in the company, on the number of employees in the company, and on the industrial sector of the company. Usually the contibutions are apportioned as follows:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://taxsummaries.pwc.com/uk/taxsummaries/wwts.nsf/ID/Italy-Individual-Other-taxes|title=Italy - Other taxes impacting individuals|website=taxsummaries.pwc.com|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\n* around 30% is charged to the employer\n* around 10% is charged to the employee\n\nHowever, only 33% out of this 40% is used for INPS purposes; the rest is distributed into several other funds:\n\n* Unemployment fund\n* Sickness fund - usage of this fund is not applicable for executives\n* Maternity fund\n* Temporary unemployment compensation fund - separates into ordinary and extraordinary compensation fund, usage of this fund is not applicable for executives\n* Social mobility fund - usage of this fund is not applicable for executives\n* Other minor funds\n\nThe social security contribution, for employees who registered with INPS after 1 January 1996 without a previous social security position in Italy, is calculated and paid up to a maximum amount of EUR 101,427 for the year 2018.\n\n=== Employment relationship (executive) ===\nSocial contributions due from executives:\n\n==== commercial executive has to contribute following ====\n\n* For INPS tax level is 9.19% of income up to income ceiling of amount \u20ac46,630. For higher income tax level is set to be 10.19% of income.\n* For ''Fondo Mario Negri'' - complementary pension fund tax level is 1% on a national annual income, tax ceiling is \u20ac59,224.54 and maximally \u20ac129.12 yearly as training charges.\n* For ''Fondo Mario Busesso'' - also known as FASDAC<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fasdac.it/|title=Fasdac|website=www.fasdac.it|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref> (''Fondo Assistenza Sanitaria Dirigenti Aziende Commerciali'') - national medical fund, tax level is 1.87% of annual income with yearly maximum \u20ac45,940. \n* For ''Fondo Pastore'' - complementary pension fund - it's required to contribute at least \u20ac464.81. This fund consist of insurance and investment (not compulsory).\n\n==== industrial executive has to contribute following ====\n\n* For INPS tax level is 9.19% of income up to income ceiling of amount \u20ac46,630. For higher income tax level is set to be 10.19% of income.\n* For ''Fondo Assistenza Sanitaria Industria'' or FASI - medical care fund - is set flat rate at level of \u20ac960.\n* For ''Fondo Previdenza Dirienti Aziende industriali'' or PREVINDAI - additional pension fund - is set tax level 4% of income only for those with maximum annual income \u20ac150,000.\n\n=== Self-employment relationship ===\nFor self-employed individuals who are not VAT number holders and are not covered by compulsory private pension fund is instituted law 335/95, according to this individuals must register with INPS in a \"separate social security regime\". This system is provided for three different rates.\n\n* For individuals enrolled in other mandatory security regime is tax level 24% of annual income.\n* For individuals with VAT number enrolled in exclusive way into ''Gestione separata INPS'' (separate social security regime) is tax level 25.72%.\n*All others individuals enrolled in the exclusive way into the separate social security regime (''Gestione separata INPS'') differs on providing DIS-COLL. If DIS-COLL is not provided, tax rate is 33.72% of income, if DIS-COLL is provided, tax rate is 34.23%.\n\nAll percentages equals to maximal limit of \u20ac101,427 established by law in 2017.\n\n*\n\n== Other taxes ==\n\n=== Wealth tax on real estate properties owned outside of Italy ===\nThe Italian wealth tax on real estate properties (''Imposta sul valore degli immobile situati all\u2019estero'' or IVIE) owned outside of Italy by an individual who qualifies as a resident for Italian tax purposes has been introduced in Italy. The wealth tax due is proportionate to the percentage owned and the size of the property. The applicable tax rate is equal to 0.76%.No IVIE is due if the tax is lower than EUR 200; otherwise, the entire IVIE amount is due.\n\n=== Wealth tax on financial investments owned outside of Italy ===\nThe Italian wealth tax on financial investments (''Imposta sul valore delle Attivita` Finanziarie detenute all` Estero'' or IVAFE) owned outside of Italy by an individual who qualifies as a resident for Italian tax purposes has been introduced in Italy. The wealth tax due is proportionate to the percentage owned and the size of the property. The applicable tax rate is equal to 0.2% for FY 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://transferwise.com/gb/blog/italy-inheritance-tax|title=Your guide to paying inheritance tax in Italy|date=2018-02-06|website=TransferWise|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref> Only for bank accounts, the above-mentioned tax is a flat amount equal to EUR 34.20 for each bank account. This flat amount is not due if the average saving amount is lower than EUR 5,000, taking into consideration all the bank accounts owned by the taxpayer.\n\n=== Inheritance, estate, and gift taxes ===\nA tax on inheritance and donations was reintroduced in October 2006 after a five year period during which this tax was abolished. The percentage and exemption limits applicable to transfers of money or assets depend on the beneficiary's relation with the deceased person or donor.\n\n* the spouse or relatives in a direct line, the inheritance or donations tax will be imposed at 4% on the value of the assets exceeding the tax-free threshold of EUR 1 million (per heir)\n* a sister and brother, the inheritance or donations tax will be imposed at 6% on the value of the transfer exceeding EUR 100,000 (per heir)\n* other family members up to the fourth generation, the inheritance or donations tax will be imposed at a 6% tax rate on the entire value of the transfer, and\n* all other beneficiaries not previously mentioned will be subject to an 8% tax rate to be applied on the entire value of the transfer.\n\nSpecific provisions apply to a handicapped person.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.icalculator.info/italy/inheritance-tax-calculator.html|title=Inheritance Tax Rates and Online Calculator|date=2020-02-13|website=iCalculator|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Regional tax on productivity ===\nThe regional tax on productivity (IRAP) is applied at a flat rate up to 3.9%. This flat rate is applicable to the productive activity exercised. The taxable base is the difference between the compensation received and the direct business expenses, excluding any cost of personnel and interest.\n\n=== Municipal taxes on real estate owned in Italy ===\nThe Italian Financial Bill for FY 2014 has introduced relevant changes to the municipal tax on real estate owned in Italy. Indeed, the tax law has introduced a 'unique municipal tax' (''Imposta municipale unica'' or IUC).\n\nIUC is composed of three different taxes:\n\n* Municipal tax (''Imposta municipale propria'' or IMU).\n* Garbage tax (''Imposta sui rifiuti'' or TARI).\n* Indivisible service tax (''Imposta sui servizi indivisibili'' or TASI).\n\n== Tax evasion and lack of guarantees ==\nItaly has the largest number of \"major tax evaders\" in Europe, counting, according to the estimated figures,<ref>https://www.forexinfo.it/Evasione-Fiscale-Italia-I-numeri-da-conoscere</ref> tax evasion for over \u20ac180 billion. On the other hand, evasion is sometimes seen by evaders as the best way to ensure the right of defense from the alleged excessive tax claim of the State.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Buonomo|first1=Giampiero|title = Codice del processo tributario, un convegno fa chiarezza|journal= L'Ago e Il Filo|date=2015| url= https://www.questia.com/projects#!/project/89427378}} {{Subscription required |via=[[Questia]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Eight per thousand]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://attorneyitaly.com/how-to-register-vat-number-italy How to: Register the VAT number in Italy]\n*[http://www.tjtaylor.net/english/teaching-taxation How to calculate your net salary in Italy]\n\n{{Italy topics}}\n{{Taxation in Europe}}\n\n[[Category:Taxation in Italy| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Taxation}}\n'''Taxation in Italy''' is levied by the central and regional governments and is collected by the [[Italian Agency of Revenue]] (Agenzia delle Entrate). Total tax revenue in 2018 was 42,4% of GDP.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.oecd.org/tax/revenue-statistics-italy.pdf|title=Revenue Statistics 2018 - Italy|last=|first=|date=2018|website=OECD}}</ref>  Most important earnings are: [[income tax]], [[social security]], [[corporate tax]] and [[value added tax]].  All of those are collected at national level, but some of those differs across regions. Personal income taxation in Italy is [[Progressive tax|progressive]].\n\n==Income tax==\nEmployment income is subject to a progressive income tax, IRPEF (''Imposta sul reddito delle persone fisiche'') applying to all workers. By government is set tax rate according to income, but the regions can add an additional 0.7% to 3.33%. Each region not only has a regional income tax, a municipal income tax can be levied which ranges from 0.1% to 0.9%. Municipalities can also establish progressive tax rates applicable to the national income bracket.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://taxsummaries.pwc.com/uk/taxsummaries/wwts.nsf/ID/Italy-Individual-Taxes-on-personal-income|title=Italy - Taxes on personal income|website=taxsummaries.pwc.com|access-date=2019-04-28}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, the personal income tax rates were as follows:\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Income range\n! Tax rate<ref>{{cite web|url=https://taxing.it/personal-income-tax-irpef-rates/|title=Personal income tax (IRPEF) rates|author=|first=|date=2018|website=taxing.it|publisher=IRPEF - Imposta sul reddito delle persone fisiche|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n| \u20ac0 \u2014 \u20ac15,000\n| 23%\n|-\n| \u20ac15,000 \u2014 \u20ac28,000\n| 27%\n|-\n| \u20ac28,000 \u2014 \u20ac55,000\n| 38% \n|-\n| \u20ac55,000 \u2014 \u20ac75,000\n| 41% \n|-\n| over \u20ac75,000\n| 43%\n|}\n\nIndividuals are considered [[resident for tax purposes]] if for the greater part of the tax year they satisfy any of the following conditions:\n\n* their habitual abode is in Italy,\n* the centre of their vital interests is located in Italy, or\n* they are registered at the Office of Records of the Resident Population in Italy.\n\n===Exemption Area===\nDue to the different types of income, exemption from IRPEF is determined at:\n\n*8,000 euros, for subordinate workers, if their employment period coincides with the entire year;\n*7,500 euros, for pensioners under 75 years of age, if the pension is cashed in for the entire year, and for those receiving palimony from ex spouses;\n*7,750 euros, for pensioners aged 75 or older, with a pension period that coincides with the whole year;\n*4,800 euros, no matter how many days they work a year, for taxpayers with other types of income.\nThe area exempt from IRPEF increases further if there are dependent family members.\n\n==Corporate tax==\nItalian corporate entities are subject to Corporate Income Tax, IRES (''Imposta sul reddito delle societ\u00e0'') and to Regional Production Tax, IRAP (''Imposta regionale sulle attivit\u00e0 produttive''). Italy has one of the highest corporate tax - currently at 24% - across EU28, average tax in EU is 21.3% (2018) and is still decreasing, however, Italy has after elections in March 2018 stop depreciation. [https://d3fy651gv2fhd3.cloudfront.net/charts/italy-corporate-tax-rate@2x.png?s=itacorptax&v=201804031046a1&d1=20000428&d2=20190428&mean=1&url2=/european-union/corporate-tax-rate]\n\n*The rate of corporate income tax (IRES) since 1 January 2017 is 24% (previously it was 27.5%, maximum 53.2% in 1981). Some corporations are exempted from corporate tax, such as charitable foundations, church institutions and sports clubs.\n*The standard rate of regional tax (IRAP) is 3.9%, however, [[Regions of Italy|regional authorities]] may increase or decrease rate of standart tax by up to 0.92%. In addition, different IRAP rates are used to differ sectors of the economy in each region. For example, the rate for banks and other financial institutions is 5.57% in [[Abruzzo]], [[Apulia]], [[Lazio]], [[Lombardy]], [[Piedmont]] and [[Veneto]], but only 4.65% in [[Emilia-Romagna]]).<ref>https://www.guidafisco.it/calcolo-irap-aliquote-851 guidafisco.it</ref> The tax is calculated differently from IRES, adding the cost of fixed-term workers (before 2016 the cost of every employee was counted). Up to 10% of regional tax (IRAP) is deductible in calculating the tax base for corporate income tax (IRES) purposes.\n\n==Value added tax==\nValue added tax or shortcut [[Value-added tax|VAT]], (in Italian ''Imposta sul valore aggiunto'', shortcut IVA) is a consumption tax charged at a standard rate of 22%, which haven't changed for years. Italian government reduced VAT rates at 10% for some listed pharmaceuticals and listed power supplies, passenger transport that is not specifically exempted, admissions to cultural and entertainment events, hotels, restaurants and  reduced only to 4% to listed food, drinks and agricultural products. The Italian [[Value-added tax|VAT]] regime is part of the [[European Union value added tax]] system. Specififc supplied goods on a market, such as education, healthcare, hospitals, public postal services are by law excluded out of VAT, same fore specially listed financial transactions, such as transfers of money and transfers of  business parts. In the case of a taxable person (VAT number holders), input VAT on purchases of goods and services related to business activity generally is allowed for recovery. Special limitations apply in relation to specific items (e.g. cars, entertainment expenses).\n\nThe filing deadline for VAT returns is 30 April of the next year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://taxsummaries.pwc.com/ID/Italy-Individual-Other-taxes|title=Italy - Value-added tax (VAT)|last=|first=|date=2018|website=TaxSummaries|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Social security==\n\n=== Employment relationship (staff) ===\nSocial security contributions apply to everyone in the workforce, divided into contributions by the employer and those by the employee; both sides are obliged to participate. Employers must register with the Italian Social Security Administration (''Istituto Nazionale Previdenza Sociale'' or INPS). The total contribution rate fluctuates around 40% of the employee's wage, depending on their position in the company, on the number of employees in the company, and on the industrial sector of the company. Usually the contibutions are apportioned as follows:<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://taxsummaries.pwc.com/uk/taxsummaries/wwts.nsf/ID/Italy-Individual-Other-taxes|title=Italy - Other taxes impacting individuals|website=taxsummaries.pwc.com|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref>\n\n* around 30% is charged to the employer\n* around 10% is charged to the employee\n\nHowever, only 33% out of this 40% is used for INPS purposes; the rest is distributed into several other funds:\n\n* Unemployment fund\n* Sickness fund - usage of this fund is not applicable for executives\n* Maternity fund\n* Temporary unemployment compensation fund - separates into ordinary and extraordinary compensation fund, usage of this fund is not applicable for executives\n* Social mobility fund - usage of this fund is not applicable for executives\n* Other minor funds\n\nThe social security contribution, for employees who registered with INPS after 1 January 1996 without a previous social security position in Italy, is calculated and paid up to a maximum amount of EUR 101,427 for the year 2018.\n\n=== Employment relationship (executive) ===\nSocial contributions due from executives:\n\n==== commercial executive has to contribute following ====\n\n* For INPS tax level is 9.19% of income up to income ceiling of amount \u20ac46,630. For higher income tax level is set to be 10.19% of income.\n* For ''Fondo Mario Negri'' - complementary pension fund tax level is 1% on a national annual income, tax ceiling is \u20ac59,224.54 and maximally \u20ac129.12 yearly as training charges.\n* For ''Fondo Mario Busesso'' - also known as FASDAC<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fasdac.it/|title=Fasdac|website=www.fasdac.it|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref> (''Fondo Assistenza Sanitaria Dirigenti Aziende Commerciali'') - national medical fund, tax level is 1.87% of annual income with yearly maximum \u20ac45,940. \n* For ''Fondo Pastore'' - complementary pension fund - it's required to contribute at least \u20ac464.81. This fund consist of insurance and investment (not compulsory).\n\n==== industrial executive has to contribute following ====\n\n* For INPS tax level is 9.19% of income up to income ceiling of amount \u20ac46,630. For higher income tax level is set to be 10.19% of income.\n* For ''Fondo Assistenza Sanitaria Industria'' or FASI - medical care fund - is set flat rate at level of \u20ac960.\n* For ''Fondo Previdenza Dirienti Aziende industriali'' or PREVINDAI - additional pension fund - is set tax level 4% of income only for those with maximum annual income \u20ac150,000.\n\n=== Self-employment relationship ===\nFor self-employed individuals who are not VAT number holders and are not covered by compulsory private pension fund is instituted law 335/95, according to this individuals must register with INPS in a \"separate social security regime\". This system is provided for three different rates.\n\n* For individuals enrolled in other mandatory security regime is tax level 24% of annual income.\n* For individuals with VAT number enrolled in exclusive way into ''Gestione separata INPS'' (separate social security regime) is tax level 25.72%.\n*All others individuals enrolled in the exclusive way into the separate social security regime (''Gestione separata INPS'') differs on providing DIS-COLL. If DIS-COLL is not provided, tax rate is 33.72% of income, if DIS-COLL is provided, tax rate is 34.23%.\n\nAll percentages equals to maximal limit of \u20ac101,427 established by law in 2017.\n\n*\n\n== Other taxes ==\n\n=== Wealth tax on real estate properties owned outside of Italy ===\nThe Italian wealth tax on real estate properties (''Imposta sul valore degli immobile situati all\u2019estero'' or IVIE) owned outside of Italy by an individual who qualifies as a resident for Italian tax purposes has been introduced in Italy. The wealth tax due is proportionate to the percentage owned and the size of the property. The applicable tax rate is equal to 0.76%.No IVIE is due if the tax is lower than EUR 200; otherwise, the entire IVIE amount is due.\n\n=== Wealth tax on financial investments owned outside of Italy ===\nThe Italian wealth tax on financial investments (''Imposta sul valore delle Attivita` Finanziarie detenute all` Estero'' or IVAFE) owned outside of Italy by an individual who qualifies as a resident for Italian tax purposes has been introduced in Italy. The wealth tax due is proportionate to the percentage owned and the size of the property. The applicable tax rate is equal to 0.2% for FY 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://transferwise.com/gb/blog/italy-inheritance-tax|title=Your guide to paying inheritance tax in Italy|date=2018-02-06|website=TransferWise|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-04-30}}</ref> Only for bank accounts, the above-mentioned tax is a flat amount equal to EUR 34.20 for each bank account. This flat amount is not due if the average saving amount is lower than EUR 5,000, taking into consideration all the bank accounts owned by the taxpayer.\n\n=== Inheritance, estate, and gift taxes ===\nA tax on inheritance and donations was reintroduced in October 2006 after a five year period during which this tax was abolished. The percentage and exemption limits applicable to transfers of money or assets depend on the beneficiary's relation with the deceased person or donor.\n\n* the spouse or relatives in a direct line, the inheritance or donations tax will be imposed at 4% on the value of the assets exceeding the tax-free threshold of EUR 1 million (per heir)\n* a sister and brother, the inheritance or donations tax will be imposed at 6% on the value of the transfer exceeding EUR 100,000 (per heir)\n* other family members up to the fourth generation, the inheritance or donations tax will be imposed at a 6% tax rate on the entire value of the transfer, and\n* all other beneficiaries not previously mentioned will be subject to an 8% tax rate to be applied on the entire value of the transfer.\n\nSpecific provisions apply to a handicapped person.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.icalculator.info/italy/inheritance-tax-calculator.html|title=Inheritance Tax Rates and Online Calculator|date=2020-02-13|website=iCalculator|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n\n=== Regional tax on productivity ===\nThe regional tax on productivity (IRAP) is applied at a flat rate up to 3.9%. This flat rate is applicable to the productive activity exercised. The taxable base is the difference between the compensation received and the direct business expenses, excluding any cost of personnel and interest.\n\n=== Municipal taxes on real estate owned in Italy ===\nThe Italian Financial Bill for FY 2014 has introduced relevant changes to the municipal tax on real estate owned in Italy. Indeed, the tax law has introduced a 'unique municipal tax' (''Imposta municipale unica'' or IUC).\n\nIUC is composed of three different taxes:\n\n* Municipal tax (''Imposta municipale propria'' or IMU).\n* Garbage tax (''Imposta sui rifiuti'' or TARI).\n* Indivisible service tax (''Imposta sui servizi indivisibili'' or TASI).\n\n== Tax evasion and lack of guarantees ==\nItaly has the largest number of \"major tax evaders\" in Europe, counting, according to the estimated figures,<ref>https://www.forexinfo.it/Evasione-Fiscale-Italia-I-numeri-da-conoscere</ref> tax evasion for over \u20ac180 billion. On the other hand, evasion is sometimes seen by evaders as the best way to ensure the right of defense from the alleged excessive tax claim of the State.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Buonomo|first1=Giampiero|title = Codice del processo tributario, un convegno fa chiarezza|journal= L'Ago e Il Filo|date=2015| url= https://www.questia.com/projects#!/project/89427378}} {{Subscription required |via=[[Questia]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Eight per thousand]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://attorneyitaly.com/how-to-register-vat-number-italy How to: Register the VAT number in Italy]\n*[http://www.tjtaylor.net/english/teaching-taxation How to calculate your net salary in Italy]\n\n{{Italy topics}}\n{{Taxation in Europe}}\n\n[[Category:Taxation in Italy| ]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eValue added tax:Typo fixing, replaced: Specififc \u2192 Specific", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxation_in_Italy"}
{"title_page": "Tancredi Pozzi", "text_new": "'''Tancredi Pozzi''' ([[Milan]], 1864- [[Turin]], 1924) was an [[Italy|Italian]] sculptor.\n\n==Biography==\nPozzi studied at the [[Accademia Albertina]], under [[Giuseppe Dini]].<ref>[http://www.museotorino.it/resources/pdf/books/25/files/assets/downloads/page0254.pdf Turin Museum] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219022759/http://www.museotorino.it/resources/pdf/books/25/files/assets/downloads/page0254.pdf |date=2013-12-19 }} biography from ''Augusta Taurinorum; Torino Illustrata nelle sue Cose e nei suoi Cittadini'' Editore proprietario Erneseto Marini, page 254-255.</ref> He completed many bas reliefs, funereal monuments, and monumental commemorations. He also completed a number of portrait busts. At the 1884 Turin exhibition, he exhibited a life-size stucco statue titled: ''Sar\u00e0 tempesta?''. At the 1887 National Exhibition of Fine Arts in Venice, he exhibited ''Regata vinta''. Other works include ''Rematore'', ''Popolano'', and ''Figurina muliebre''.  In 1888 at Bologna, he exhibited a stucco statue of a horse titled ''Tafani molesti'' and a small bronze equestrian group titled ''Tancredi in Love''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Zz0bAAAAYAAJ ''Dizionario degli Artisti Italiani Viventi: pittori, scultori, e Architetti.''], by [[Angelo de Gubernatis]]. Tipe dei Successori Le Monnier, 1889, page 388.</ref> He was knighted by the King. These works underscore his predilection for statues of vigorous and active horses and equestrian groups, also including ''Ettore Fieramosca'', ''Kamir'', ''Arduino d'Ivrea'', ''Clelia Romana'', ''Rez'', ''Populus'', ''Fetontesul Po, and ''Autari''. Among his funereal monuments are that to his family in the Camposanto of Turin.<ref>''Augusta Taurinorum'', page 255.</ref>\n\nAmong his major monumental works are: his ''Monument to King Umberto I'' (1902) standing in the piazza in front of the [[Basilica of Superga]]<ref>[http://www.comune.torino.it/english/itiner/frames/cur/basilica.htm Monument to King Umberto I] at Superga.</ref> and his bronze ''Monument to Giuseppe Garibaldi'' (1904), leaning on a rock, located in Porto Maurizio ([[Imperia]]) in [[Liguria]]<ref>[http://www.liguriamia.it/IMPERIA/UTILI/MONUMENTI/MONUMENTIDIIMPERIA.html Garibaldi Monument in Imperia].</ref> Finally, he sculpted the ''Monument to [[Angelo Beccaria]]'', in the Garden of what was the Istituto dei Rachitici. He also completed a monumental fountain in Turin.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pozzi, Tancredi}}\n[[Category:1864 births]]\n[[Category:1924 deaths]]\n[[Category:Accademia Albertina alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Italian sculptors]]\n[[Category:19th-century Italian sculptors]]\n[[Category:Italian male sculptors]]\n\n\n{{Italy-sculptor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Tancredi Pozzi''' ([[Milan]], 1864- [[Turin]], 1924) was an [[Italy|Italian]] sculptor.\n\n==Biography==\nPozzi studied at the [[Accademia Albertina]], under [[Giuseppe Dini]].<ref>[http://www.museotorino.it/resources/pdf/books/25/files/assets/downloads/page0254.pdf Turin Museum] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131219022759/http://www.museotorino.it/resources/pdf/books/25/files/assets/downloads/page0254.pdf |date=2013-12-19 }} biography from ''Augusta Taurinorum; Torino Illustrata nelle sue Cose e nei suoi Cittadini'' Editore proprietario Erneseto Marini, page 254-255.</ref> He completed many bas reliefs, funereal monuments, and monumental conmemoratons. He also completed a number of portrait busts. At the 1884 Turin exhibition, he exhibited a life-size stucco statue titled: ''Sar\u00e0 tempesta?''. At the 1887 National Exhibition of Fine Arts in Venice, he exhibited ''Regata vinta''. Other works include ''Rematore'', ''Popolano'', and ''Figurina muliebre''.  In 1888 at Bologna, he exhibited a stucco statue of a horse titled ''Tafani molesti'' and a small bronze equestrian group titled ''Tancredi in Love''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Zz0bAAAAYAAJ ''Dizionario degli Artisti Italiani Viventi: pittori, scultori, e Architetti.''], by [[Angelo de Gubernatis]]. Tipe dei Successori Le Monnier, 1889, page 388.</ref> He was knighted by the King. These works underscore his predilection for statues of vigorous and active horses and equestrian groups, also including ''Ettore Fieramosca'', ''Kamir'', ''Arduino d'Ivrea'', ''Clelia Romana'', ''Rez'', ''Populus'', ''Fetontesul Po, and ''Autari''. Among his funereal monuments are that to his family in the Camposanto of Turin.<ref>''Augusta Taurinorum'', page 255.</ref>\n\nAmong his major monumental works are: his ''Monument to King Umberto I'' (1902) standing in the piazza in front of the [[Basilica of Superga]]<ref>[http://www.comune.torino.it/english/itiner/frames/cur/basilica.htm Monument to King Umberto I] at Superga.</ref> and his bronze ''Monument to Giuseppe Garibaldi'' (1904), leaning on a rock, located in Porto Maurizio ([[Imperia]]) in [[Liguria]]<ref>[http://www.liguriamia.it/IMPERIA/UTILI/MONUMENTI/MONUMENTIDIIMPERIA.html Garibaldi Monument in Imperia].</ref> Finally, he sculpted the ''Monument to [[Angelo Beccaria]]'', in the Garden of what was the Istituto dei Rachitici. He also completed a monumental fountain in Turin.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pozzi, Tancredi}}\n[[Category:1864 births]]\n[[Category:1924 deaths]]\n[[Category:Accademia Albertina alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century Italian sculptors]]\n[[Category:19th-century Italian sculptors]]\n[[Category:Italian male sculptors]]\n\n\n{{Italy-sculptor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing, replaced: conmemoratons \u2192 commemorations", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tancredi_Pozzi"}
{"title_page": "Sharia in the Philippines", "text_new": "[[Sharia]] or Islamic law is partially implemented in the legal system of the [[Philippines]] and is applicable only to [[Muslims]]. Sharia courts in the country are under supervision of the [[Supreme Court of the Philippines]].\n\nSharia courts in the Philippines has jurisdiction over Muslim-majority [[Bangsamoro]] as well as other parts of [[Mindanao]] outside the autonomous region.\n\n==Background==\nThe sharia court system in the Philippines was a result of the Presidential Decree 1083 issued by then-President [[Ferdinand Marcos]] in February 7, 1977, which is also known as the Code of Muslim Personal Laws on the advice of the now-defunct Commission on National Integration.<ref name=\"equality\">{{cite web |last1=Maulana |first1=Nash |title=Sharia equality pushed |url=http://www.manilastandard.net/lgu/mindanao/255260/sharia-equality-pushed.html |publisher=Manila Standard |accessdate=29 April 2019}}</ref>\nSharia courts are under the administrative supervision of the [[Supreme Court of the Philippines]].<ref name=\"primer\">{{cite web |title=Courts for Muslims: A Primer on Philippine Shari'a Courts |url=http://www.muslimmindanao.ph/shari'a/code_muslim.pdf |publisher=Asian Institute of Journalism and Communication |accessdate=29 April 2019}}</ref> Sharia in the country only deals with Muslim customary and personal laws<ref>{{cite news |last1=Banagudos |first1=Rey-Luis |title=Shariah courts render \u2018quick action\u2019 on Muslims\u2019 disputes |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1054885 |accessdate=29 April 2019 |agency=Philippine News Agency |date=25 November 2018}}</ref> and exclude criminal law.\n\nRepublic Act 6734, which was the Organic Law of the [[Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao]] recognized the two district courts under the now defunct autonomous region and also provided for the establishment of a Sharia Appellate Court,<ref name=\"thenandnow\">{{cite news |last1=San Juan |first1=Joel |title=Sharia courts: Then and now |url=https://businessmirror.com.ph/2017/06/11/sharia-courts-then-and-now/ |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=BusinessMirror}}</ref> however such court was never established.\n\nThe Organic Law which served as the foundation of the [[Bangsamoro Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao]] provides for the formation of a Sharia High Court for the region.<ref name=\"highcourt\">{{cite news |last1=Cepeda |first1=Maria |title=Bicam approves creation of Shari'ah High Court in Bangsamoro |url=https://www.rappler.com/nation/207171-bicameral-conference-committee-approval-shariah-high-court-bangsamoro |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=Rappler |date=12 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Organization==\n===Sharia District Courts===\nThere are five Sharia District Courts in the Philippines, all of which has territorial jurisdiction over areas in Mindanao.<ref name=\"primer\"/> The Sharia District Court is roughly equivalent to the Regional Trial Court in the regular and secular Philippine court system.<ref name=\"shariadc\">{{cite news |last1=Balane |first1=Walter |title=Legislators want Shari\u2019ah courts in DC |url=https://www.mindanews.com/c3-news/2007/10/legislators-want-shariah-courts-in-dc/ |work=MindaNews |date=16 October 2007}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\" width=80%\n|-\n!Court!!Location!!Jurisdiction\n|-\n|align=left|First Sharia District Court || [[Jolo, Sulu|Jolo]], [[Sulu]] || [[Sulu]]\n|-\n|align=left|Second Sharia District Court || [[Bongao, Tawi-Tawi|Bongao]], [[Tawi-Tawi]] || [[Tawi-Tawi]]\n|-\n|align=left|Third Sharia District Court || [[Zamboanga City]] || [[Basilan]]<br>[[Zamboanga del Norte]]<br>[[Zamboanga del Sur]]<br>[[Dipolog]]<br>[[Pagadian]]<br>[[Zamboanga City]]\n|-\n|align=left|Fourth Sharia District Court || [[Marawi]] || [[Lanao del Norte]]<br>[[Lanao del Sur]]<br>[[Iligan]]<br>[[Marawi]]\n|-\n|align=left|Second Sharia District Court || [[Cotabato City]] || [[Maguindanao]]<br>[[North Cotabato]]<br>[[Sultan Kudarat]]<br>[[Cotabato City]]<br>[[Kidapawan]]\n|-\n|}\n===Sharia Circuit Courts===\nThere are 51 circuit courts in Mindanao. Their scope is comparable to that of the regular court system's city and municipal courts.<ref name=\"shariadc\"/>\n\n===Bangsamoro Sharia High Court===\nThe [[Bangsamoro Organic Law]] has provisions for the creation of a Sharia High Court for the [[Bangsamoro]] region. The high court shall have exclusive appellate jurisdiction over sharia districts within the autonomous region.<ref name=\"highcourt\"/>\n\n==Application==\n===Personal status laws===\n====Marriage====\nThe Code of Muslim Personal Laws covers marriage done under Islamic rites. The same also recognizes divorce contrary to the [[Family Code of the Philippines]] which does not recognize divorce, baring most non-Muslim Filipinos from legally ending their marriage. Divorce between a non-Muslim and a Muslim is also recognized such as the divorce case of a Christian woman and a Muslim man who were married under Islamic rites which was upheld in 2016 by the Supreme Court.<ref name=muslimchristian>{{cite news |last1=Quismundo |first1=Tarra |title=Muslim-Christian couple\u2019s divorce upheld |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/761714/muslim-christian-couples-divorce-upheld |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nUnder the Muslim code a husband may seek for a \"perpetual divorce\" from his wife or invoke ''li'an'' to end his marriage if his spouse commits adultery. The wife may seek the termination of her marriage with her husband by invoking ''faskh'' if certain conditions are met including if her spouse commits \"unusual cruelty\", suffers from insanity or affliction of an incurable disease, or for six consecutive months neglects family support for six consecutive months. ''Talaq'' divorce may be invoked \"may be effected by the husband in a single repudiation of his wife\" after totally abstaining from sexual relations with his spouse.<ref name=muslimchristian/>\n\n===Financial laws===\n[[File:Al-Amanah Islamic Bank San Juan, Metro Manila branch.jpg|thumb|[[Al-Amanah Islamic Bank]] outlet in [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]], [[Metro Manila]]]]\nUntil 2019, there were no current framework legislation in effect that would allow the establishments of [[Islamic banking|Islamic banks]] or banks compliant with sharia. In August 22, 2019, Republic Act  11439 which is also known as \"An Act Providing for the Regulation and Organization of Islamic Banks\" was signed into law. Said legislation became effectivee on September 15, 2019 and introductory regulations for Islamic banks were released by the [[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]], the country's central bank on December 31, 2019.<ref name=bpiapproves>{{cite news |last1=Cuaresma |first1=Bianca |title=BSP approves rules on Islamic banking |url=https://businessmirror.com.ph/2020/01/01/bsp-approves-rules-on-islamic-banking/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=BusinessMirror |date=1 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nPrior to 2019, the only Islamic bank which was allowed to operate is the [[Al-Amanah Islamic Bank]] which was founded in 1973.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tetangco |first1=Amando Jr. |title=Speeches: Islamic Banking and Finance in the Philippines: Opportunities and Challenges |url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/speeches.asp?id=456 |publisher=[[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]] |accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref> Legislation introduced in 2019 allowed foreign-based and domestic firms to establish full-fledged Islamic banks in the Philippines as well as the setting up of Islamic bank units or subsidiaries under secular banks.<ref name=bpiapproves/>\n\n==Sharia legal practice==\nTo become a lawyer under the Sharia court system of the Philippines, one must pass the Sharia Bar Exam which consists of the following subject matter: Code Muslim Personal Laws; Special Rules of Procedures; Jurisprudence (''[[Fiqh]]''), and the Muslim Law on Inheritance and Succession. A sharia lawyer according to Bar Matter No. 681, a Supreme Court decision made en banc in August 5, 1993, is a \"special member\" of the [[Integrated Bar of the Philippines]] and not a fully pledged member. Members of the Sharia Bar are eligible to become circuit court judges but only those who are members of both the Sharia Bar and Regular Bar could be district court judges.<ref name=\"equality\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Sharia by country|Philippines]]\n[[Category:Islam in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Philippine law]]\n", "text_old": "[[Sharia]] or Islamic law is partially implemented in the legal system of the [[Philippines]] and is applicable only to [[Muslims]]. Sharia courts in the country are under supervision of the [[Supreme Court of the Philippines]].\n\nSharia courts in the Philippines has jurisdiction over Muslim-majority [[Bangsamoro]] as well as other parts of [[Mindanao]] outside the autonomous region.\n\n==Background==\nThe sharia court system in the Philippines was a result of the Presidential Decree 1083 issued by then-President [[Ferdinand Marcos]] in February 7, 1977, which is also known as the Code of Muslim Personal Laws on the advice of the now-defunct Commission on National Integration.<ref name=\"equality\">{{cite web |last1=Maulana |first1=Nash |title=Sharia equality pushed |url=http://www.manilastandard.net/lgu/mindanao/255260/sharia-equality-pushed.html |publisher=Manila Standard |accessdate=29 April 2019}}</ref>\nSharia courts are under the administrative supervision of the [[Supreme Court of the Philippines]].<ref name=\"primer\">{{cite web |title=Courts for Muslims: A Primer on Philippine Shari'a Courts |url=http://www.muslimmindanao.ph/shari'a/code_muslim.pdf |publisher=Asian Institute of Journalism and Communication |accessdate=29 April 2019}}</ref> Sharia in the country only deals with Muslim customary and personal laws<ref>{{cite news |last1=Banagudos |first1=Rey-Luis |title=Shariah courts render \u2018quick action\u2019 on Muslims\u2019 disputes |url=https://www.pna.gov.ph/articles/1054885 |accessdate=29 April 2019 |agency=Philippine News Agency |date=25 November 2018}}</ref> and exclude criminal law.\n\nRepublic Act 6734, which was the Organic Law of the [[Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao]] recognized the two district courts under the now defunct autonomous region and also provided for the establishment of a Sharia Appellate Court,<ref name=\"thenandnow\">{{cite news |last1=San Juan |first1=Joel |title=Sharia courts: Then and now |url=https://businessmirror.com.ph/2017/06/11/sharia-courts-then-and-now/ |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=BusinessMirror}}</ref> however such court was never established.\n\nThe Organic Law which served as the foundation of the [[Bangsamoro Autonomous Region in Muslim Mindanao]] provides for the formation of a Sharia High Court for the region.<ref name=\"highcourt\">{{cite news |last1=Cepeda |first1=Maria |title=Bicam approves creation of Shari'ah High Court in Bangsamoro |url=https://www.rappler.com/nation/207171-bicameral-conference-committee-approval-shariah-high-court-bangsamoro |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=Rappler |date=12 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Organization==\n===Sharia District Courts===\nThere are five Sharia District Courts in the Philippines, all of which has territorial jurisdiction over areas in Mindanao.<ref name=\"primer\"/> The Sharia District Court is roughly equivalent to the Regional Trial Court in the regular and secular Philippine court system.<ref name=\"shariadc\">{{cite news |last1=Balane |first1=Walter |title=Legislators want Shari\u2019ah courts in DC |url=https://www.mindanews.com/c3-news/2007/10/legislators-want-shariah-courts-in-dc/ |work=MindaNews |date=16 October 2007}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\" width=80%\n|-\n!Court!!Location!!Jurisdiction\n|-\n|align=left|First Sharia District Court || [[Jolo, Sulu|Jolo]], [[Sulu]] || [[Sulu]]\n|-\n|align=left|Second Sharia District Court || [[Bongao, Tawi-Tawi|Bongao]], [[Tawi-Tawi]] || [[Tawi-Tawi]]\n|-\n|align=left|Third Sharia District Court || [[Zamboanga City]] || [[Basilan]]<br>[[Zamboanga del Norte]]<br>[[Zamboanga del Sur]]<br>[[Dipolog]]<br>[[Pagadian]]<br>[[Zamboanga City]]\n|-\n|align=left|Fourth Sharia District Court || [[Marawi]] || [[Lanao del Norte]]<br>[[Lanao del Sur]]<br>[[Iligan]]<br>[[Marawi]]\n|-\n|align=left|Second Sharia District Court || [[Cotabato City]] || [[Maguindanao]]<br>[[North Cotabato]]<br>[[Sultan Kudarat]]<br>[[Cotabato City]]<br>[[Kidapawan]]\n|-\n|}\n===Sharia Circuit Courts===\nThere are 51 circuit courts in Mindanao. Their scope is comparable to that of the regular court system's city and municipal courts.<ref name=\"shariadc\"/>\n\n===Bangsamoro Sharia High Court===\nThe [[Bangsamoro Organic Law]] has provisions for the creation of a Sharia High Court for the [[Bangsamoro]] region. The high court shall have exclusive appelate jurisdiction over sharia districts within the autonomous region.<ref name=\"highcourt\"/>\n\n==Application==\n===Personal status laws===\n====Marriage====\nThe Code of Muslim Personal Laws covers marriage done under Islamic rites. The same also recognizes divorce contrary to the [[Family Code of the Philippines]] which does not recognize divorce, baring most non-Muslim Filipinos from legally ending their marriage. Divorce between a non-Muslim and a Muslim is also recognized such as the divorce case of a Christian woman and a Muslim man who were married under Islamic rites which was upheld in 2016 by the Supreme Court.<ref name=muslimchristian>{{cite news |last1=Quismundo |first1=Tarra |title=Muslim-Christian couple\u2019s divorce upheld |url=https://newsinfo.inquirer.net/761714/muslim-christian-couples-divorce-upheld |accessdate=29 April 2019 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=6 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nUnder the Muslim code a husband may seek for a \"perpetual divorce\" from his wife or invoke ''li'an'' to end his marriage if his spouse commits adultery. The wife may seek the termination of her marriage with her husband by invoking ''faskh'' if certain conditions are met including if her spouse commits \"unusual cruelty\", suffers from insanity or affliction of an incurable disease, or for six consecutive months neglects family support for six consecutive months. ''Talaq'' divorce may be invoked \"may be effected by the husband in a single repudiation of his wife\" after totally abstaining from sexual relations with his spouse.<ref name=muslimchristian/>\n\n===Financial laws===\n[[File:Al-Amanah Islamic Bank San Juan, Metro Manila branch.jpg|thumb|[[Al-Amanah Islamic Bank]] outlet in [[San Juan, Metro Manila|San Juan]], [[Metro Manila]]]]\nUntil 2019, there were no current framework legislation in effect that would allow the establishments of [[Islamic banking|Islamic banks]] or banks compliant with sharia. In August 22, 2019, Republic Act  11439 which is also known as \"An Act Providing for the Regulation and Organization of Islamic Banks\" was signed into law. Said legislation became effectivee on September 15, 2019 and introductory regulations for Islamic banks were released by the [[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]], the country's central bank on December 31, 2019.<ref name=bpiapproves>{{cite news |last1=Cuaresma |first1=Bianca |title=BSP approves rules on Islamic banking |url=https://businessmirror.com.ph/2020/01/01/bsp-approves-rules-on-islamic-banking/ |accessdate=13 January 2020 |work=BusinessMirror |date=1 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nPrior to 2019, the only Islamic bank which was allowed to operate is the [[Al-Amanah Islamic Bank]] which was founded in 1973.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tetangco |first1=Amando Jr. |title=Speeches: Islamic Banking and Finance in the Philippines: Opportunities and Challenges |url=http://www.bsp.gov.ph/publications/speeches.asp?id=456 |publisher=[[Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas]] |accessdate=31 May 2019}}</ref> Legislation introduced in 2019 allowed foreign-based and domestic firms to establish full-fledged Islamic banks in the Philippines as well as the setting up of Islamic bank units or subsidiaries under secular banks.<ref name=bpiapproves/>\n\n==Sharia legal practice==\nTo become a lawyer under the Sharia court system of the Philippines, one must pass the Sharia Bar Exam which consists of the following subject matter: Code Muslim Personal Laws; Special Rules of Procedures; Jurisprudence (''[[Fiqh]]''), and the Muslim Law on Inheritance and Succession. A sharia lawyer according to Bar Matter No. 681, a Supreme Court decision made en banc in August 5, 1993, is a \"special member\" of the [[Integrated Bar of the Philippines]] and not a fully pledged member. Members of the Sharia Bar are eligible to become circuit court judges but only those who are members of both the Sharia Bar and Regular Bar could be district court judges.<ref name=\"equality\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Sharia by country|Philippines]]\n[[Category:Islam in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Philippine law]]\n", "name_user": "Will Sandberg", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBangsamoro Sharia High Court", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sharia_in_the_Philippines"}
{"title_page": "Proposed second Scottish independence referendum", "text_new": "{{PoliticsScotland}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Update|documentation|date=December 2019}}\n[[File:Scottish independence protest.jpg|thumb|Pro-independence protest in [[Edinburgh]], 2019]]\nThe [[Scottish Government]] has proposed holding a second referendum on Scottish independence from the [[United Kingdom]] (UK). A [[2014 Scottish independence referendum|referendum on Scottish independence]] was held in 2014, with 55% voting against the proposal. After this, the UK voted to leave the [[European Union]] (EU) in a [[Brexit referendum|2016 referendum]]. One of the reasons cited by those opposed to [[Scottish independence]] during the 2014 campaign was that it would endanger [[Scotland]] being part of the EU. \n\nThe SNP majority [[Scottish Government]] stated in its 2013 white paper on independence that the 2014 referendum would be a \"once in a generation opportunity to follow a different path, and choose a new and better direction for our nation\".<ref name=\"White Paper\">{{cite web|url=https://www2.gov.scot/resource/0043/00439021.pdf|title=SCOTLAND\u02bcS FUTURE YOUR GUIDE TO AN INDEPENDENT SCOTLAND|date=1 November 2013|website=gov.scot|publisher=gov.scot|accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref> Following the election of a Conservative UK government in [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015]], a referendum on UK membership of the EU was scheduled for June 2016. The SNP stated in its manifesto for the [[2016 Scottish Parliament election|May 2016 Scottish Parliament election]] that a second independence referendum should be held if there was a material change of circumstances, such as the [[Brexit|UK leaving the EU]].\n\nThe SNP formed a minority government in 2016 with the [[Scottish Parliament]] having a pro-independence majority with the [[Scottish Greens]]. The \"leave\" side won the EU referendum with 52% of the vote across the UK. In Scotland, 62% of votes were to \"remain\" in the EU, with a majority of voters in every local authority area voting \"remain\".\n\nIn March 2017 [[First Minister of Scotland|First Minister]] [[Nicola Sturgeon]] gained the approval of the Scottish Parliament to request a [[Section 30 of the Scotland Act|Section 30 order]] to enable a second independence referendum \"when the shape of the UK's Brexit deal will become clear\", within 18\u201324 months.<ref name=13marchscotgov>{{cite web|url=http://news.gov.scot/news/scotland-must-have-choice-over-future|date=2017-03-13|accessdate=2017-03-13|website=[[Scottish Government]]|title=Scotland must have choice over future}}</ref><ref name=\"2017 request\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-39449459|title=Sturgeon signs independence vote request|date=2017-03-30|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-03-30|language=en-GB}}</ref> Earlier the same month, the UK Prime Minister [[Theresa May]] stated that \"now is not the time\" to discuss another referendum, because the focus should be on \"working together, not pulling apart\" for Brexit negotiations.<ref name=\"Rejected BBC 16Mar2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-39293513|title=Scottish independence: Referendum demand 'will be rejected'|date=16 March 2017|website=bbc.com|publisher=BBC|accessdate=17 March 2017}}</ref> The [[Brexit]] process also met a 10-month delay due to lack of ratification of the exit deal by the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/10/28/brexit-delayed-many-brexit-extensions-10996922/|title=Is Brexit delayed and how many Brexit extensions have there been?|last=Martin|first=Rachael|date=2019-10-28|work=The Metro|access-date=2020-01-01|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, Sturgeon sent an official request to hold an independence referendum to May's successor as prime minister, [[Boris Johnson]]. Sturgeon advocated holding a referendum in 2020 and published a document presenting the democratic case for a referendum alongside proposed amendments to the [[Scotland Act 1998]], including to give the Scottish parliament permanent powers to hold referendums and for UK law to make provisions for self-determination.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/dec/19/nicola-sturgeon-requests-independence-referendum-powers|title=Sturgeon demands independence referendum powers be devolved|last=correspondent|first=Libby Brooks Scotland|date=2019-12-19|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-12-27|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gov.scot/publications/scotlands-right-choose-putting-scotlands-future-scotlands-hands/|title=Scotland's right to choose: putting Scotland's future in Scotland's hands\n|last=Scottish Government|first=|date=2019-12-19|work=The Scottish Government|access-date=2019-12-27|language=en-GB|isbn=9781839604454}}</ref><ref name=\"for 2020\">{{cite news |first= Libby |last=Brooks |url= https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/15/nicola-sturgeon-to-demand-powers-for-2020-referendum |title= Nicola Sturgeon to demand powers for 2020 referendum |work= The Guardian |date= 15 October 2019 |accessdate= 31 December 2019}}</ref> In January 2020, the request was rejected by the UK government, which pointed out that Sturgeon had promised that the 2014 referendum would not be repeated for at least a generation, and that both the Scottish and UK governments had pledged to abide by its outcome.\n\n==History==\n===2014 Scottish independence referendum===\n{{Main|2014 Scottish independence referendum}}\n[[File:Scottish independence referendum results.svg|150px|thumb|Results by council area of the 2014 Scottish independence referendum:<br />{{legend|#24B14C|Yes}}{{legend|#DF0A24|No}}]]\nThe referendum on Scottish independence held on 18 September 2014 saw Scotland vote to remain part of the United Kingdom (UK), with 55% voting against the proposal for Scotland to become an independent country and 45% voting in favour. Uncertainty over Scotland's European Union (EU) membership was a topic in the run-up to the referendum vote.<ref name=\"Clegg 2014\">{{cite web | last= Clegg | first=David | title= Independence referendum: Euro bigwig Jose Manuel Barroso delivers fresh blow to Yes campaign | website= Daily record | date=17 February 2014 | url= http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/politics/independence-referendum-ec-president-jose-3154114 | accessdate= 25 June 2016 | quote=EU membership is another central plank in Salmond's blueprint for independence outlined in the SNP's White Paper last year.}}</ref> The British government and some mainstream political parties argued that remaining in the UK was the only way for Scotland to remain part of the EU.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/jun/24/nicola-sturgeon-keep-scotland-eu-independence |title=Nicola Sturgeon needs to keep Scotland in the EU. But how? |first=Lesley|last=Riddoch|authorlink= Lesley Riddoch|date=24 June 2016|work=The Guardian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://apnews.com/cace8f31f50245b093e26cdd434d236e |title=Pro-EU Scots, Northern Irish eye UK escape after Brexit vote|date= 24 June 2016|agency= Associated Press}}</ref> The proposed UK referendum on EU membership had already been announced, and was a topic of discussion in the independence debate.<ref name=\"salmond eu\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-28980041 |title=Scottish independence: Alex Salmond says Eurosceptics 'damaging Scotland' |work=BBC News |date=29 August 2014 |accessdate=29 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nOther issues, such as the economy, played a large part in the debate. Financial groups, such as the [[Royal Bank of Scotland]] and [[Lloyds Banking Group]], were reported to be considering moving their registered offices to London, as a result of a European law stating that banks should have their head offices in the same member state as its registered office, as well as implying that these offices should be in the location where they conduct most of their activity \u2013 which would be the remainder of the United Kingdom in the event of Scottish independence.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-26455655|title=EU law may force RBS and Lloyds to become English |work= BBC News|date=5 March 2014 |accessdate= 21 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://eur-lex.europa.eu/LexUriServ/LexUriServ.do?uri=CELEX:31995L0026:EN:HTML |title=Council Directive 95/26/EC |work= Eur-lex | publisher = Europa |date= 18 July 1995 |accessdate= 21 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe Scottish Government's official publication on the independence referendum stated that \"It is the view of the current Scottish Government that a referendum is a once-in-a-generation opportunity\",<ref>Scottish Government (November 2013) [http://www.gov.scot/Resource/0043/00439021.pdf  \"Scotland's Future\"]. p. 556.</ref> a point reiterated a few days before the vote by the SNP's then-leader, [[Alex Salmond]], noting the eighteen-year gap between the devolution referenda held in [[1979 Scottish devolution referendum|1979]] and in [[1997 Scottish devolution referendum |1997]] as an example of the generational opportunity.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-29196661|title=Salmond: 'Referendum is once in a generation opportunity'|date=14 September 2014|work=BBC}}</ref> Three months later, Salmond reversed the position, highlighting the UK's EU referendum as a factor.<ref>Kinder, Tabatha (20 December 2014) [http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/second-scottish-independence-referendum-horizon-says-alex-salmond-1480417 \"'A second Scottish independence referendum is on the horizon', says Alex Salmond\"]. ''International Business Times''.</ref> The UK government had also portrayed the independence referendum as once-in-a-generation.<ref>Aitken, Keith (15 October 2012) [http://www.publicfinance.co.uk/news/2012/10/terms-%E2%80%98once-generation%E2%80%99-scottish-independence-referendum-agreed \"Terms of 'once in a generation' Scottish independence referendum agreed\"]. Public Finance. CIPFA.</ref>\n\nThough the proposal for Scotland to become an independent country was voted down in 2014, the referendum resulted in the Scottish Parliament gaining additional powers through the  [[Scotland Act 2016]], which increased the devolved powers in areas such as taxation and some aspects of welfare provision.<ref>{{Cite journal|last= McGarvey |first=Neil|year= 2015 |title= The 2014 Scottish Independence Referendum and Its Aftermath |journal= Social Alternatives |volume= 34 |pages= 34\u201340|via= EBSCOHost}}</ref>\n\n===United Kingdom general election, 2015===\n{{see also|United Kingdom general election, 2015 (Scotland)}}\n[[File:2015UKelectionMapScotland.svg|right|300px|thumb|Results of the 2015 United Kingdom general election]]\nThe [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015 UK general election]] was held on 7 May almost eight months after the independence referendum was held. In their manifesto, the SNP said the following in response to the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]]' manifesto pledge promising a referendum on EU membership by the end of 2017 if elected:<ref>/http://votesnp.com/docs/manifesto.pdf}</ref>\n\n<blockquote>The European Union is far from perfect, however, we believe that it is overwhelmingly in Scotland\u2019s interests for us to remain a member, engaging with the institutions as fully as we can, and to argue for reform from within. We will oppose UK withdrawal from the EU and will propose that, in any future referendum, there should be a double majority requirement. Each of the four constituent nations of the UK would have to vote for withdrawal before the UK as a whole could leave the European Union.</blockquote>\n\nThe SNP went on to win 56 of the 59 Scottish seats that were contested in an unprecedented landslide winning 50% of the national vote and left just three unionist MPs in Scotland; [[Scottish Labour Party|Labour]] saw their worst result in Scotland since [[1918 United Kingdom general election|1918]], the [[Scottish Liberal Democrats|Liberal Democrats]] fell to their lowest level since [[1970 United Kingdom general election|1970]] and the [[Scottish Conservative Party|Conservatives]] received their lowest vote share in Scotland since [[1865 United Kingdom general election|1865]].\n\nAcross the United Kingdom, the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] led by [[David Cameron]] won an unexpected overall majority, their first since 1992 and following their victory passed the [[European Union Referendum Act 2015]] which legislated for the holding of a national UK-wide referendum on EU membership which would be held following the conclusion of a [[United Kingdom renegotiation of European Union membership, 2015\u201316|renegotiation of the UK's membership to the EU]].\n\n===Scottish Parliament election, 2016===\n{{Main|Scottish Parliament election, 2016}}\n[[File:Scottish Election Results 2016.svg|thumb|300px|Results of the 2016 Scottish Parliament election]]\nThe elections to the Scottish Parliament took place on 5 May 2016, seven weeks before the holding of the EU Referendum. In their manifesto for the [[2016 Scottish Parliament election|2016 Scottish elections]], the SNP stipulated conditions under which they would seek a second independence referendum:<ref>[https://www.snp.org/manifesto SNP 2016 manifesto], p. 23</ref>\n\n<blockquote>We believe that the Scottish Parliament should have the right to hold another referendum if there is clear and sustained evidence that independence has become the preferred option of a majority of the Scottish people \u2013 or if there is a significant and material change in the circumstances that prevailed in 2014, such as Scotland being taken out of the EU against our will.</blockquote>\nThe SNP were re-elected in the 2016 election, winning 63 seats in the 129-seat chamber, although the result meant that they no longer held an overall majority.<ref name = \"2016 result\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2016-scotland-36205187 |title=Holyrood 2016: SNP claims 'historic' win but no majority |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=6 May 2016 |accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>  The pro-independence [[Scottish Green Party]] won 6 seats,<ref name = \"2016 result\"/> meaning that pro-independence MSPs maintained a majority.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.newstatesman.com/politics/staggers/2017/03/scottish-greens-will-back-snp-over-indyref-2 |title=Scottish Greens will back SNP over Indyref 2 |first=Julia |last=Rampen |work=New Statesman |publisher= |date=13 March 2017 |accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Scottish Green Party|Green]] manifesto stipulated that a second referendum should be held if there was public demand for one, rather than as a result of \"calculations of party political advantage\". The party specified that their preferred method of showing support for a referendum was via a public petition, although their manifesto didn't clarify how many signatories there would have to be to receive their support:<ref>[https://greens.scot/sites/default/files/Campaigns/Holyrood%202016/Holyrood%20Manifesto%202016%20%E2%80%93%20RNIB.pdf Scottish Green 2016 manifesto], p. 36</ref>\n\n<blockquote>Citizens should be able to play a direct role in the legislative process: on presenting a petition signed by an appropriate number of voters, citizens should be able to trigger a vote on important issues of devolved responsibility. As we proposed on the first anniversary of the Independence Referendum, this is the Scottish Greens\u2019 preferred way of deciding to hold a second referendum on Independence. If a new referendum is to happen, it should come about by the will of the people, and not be driven by calculations of party political advantage. In such a referendum the Scottish Greens will campaign for independence.</blockquote>\n\n===United Kingdom European Union membership referendum, 2016===\n{{Main|2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum}}\n[[File:United Kingdom European Union referendum 2016 voting area results (Scotland).svg|150px|thumb|Every council area in Scotland returned majority votes in favour of remaining in the [[European Union|EU]], contrasting with other parts of the UK, who ultimately carried the overall [[United Kingdom withdrawal from the European Union|UK leave vote]].<br />{{legend|#ffc010|Remain}}]]\nIn the EU membership referendum held on 23 June 2016, all thirty-two council areas in Scotland voted by a majority for the UK to remain a member of the EU. 62% of Scottish voters voted to remain a member of the EU, with 38% voting to leave. However, 52% of voters across the whole UK voted to leave the European Union, with 48% voting to remain; majorities in England and Wales were in favour of leaving the EU, with majorities in Scotland, Northern Ireland and Gibraltar to remain a member of the EU.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/politics/eu_referendum/results|title=EU Referendum Results|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n\nBefore the referendum, leading figures with a range of opinions regarding [[Scottish independence]] suggested that in the event the UK as a whole voted to leave the EU but Scotland as a whole voted to remain, a second independence referendum might be precipitated.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2016/01/24/nicola-sturgeon-denies-she-has-machiavellian-wish-for-brexit_n_9063372.html|title=Nicola Sturgeon Denies She Has 'Machiavellian' Wish For Brexit|last=Simons|first=Ned|date=24 January 2016|website=The Huffington Post UK|accessdate=3 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2016/01/26/scotland-will-quit-britain-if-uk-leaves-eu-warns-tony-blair_n_9077274.html|title=Scotland Will Quit Britain If UK Leaves EU, Warns Tony Blair|last=Simons|first=Ned|date=26 January 2016|website=The Huffington Post UK|accessdate=3 February 2016}}</ref> Former Labour Scottish First Minister [[Henry McLeish]] asserted that he would support Scottish independence under such circumstances.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/14194315.Henry_McLeish__I_will_back_Scottish_independence_if_UK_leave_EU_against_Scotland_s_wishes/?ref=rss|title=Henry McLeish: I will back Scottish independence if UK leave EU against Scotland's wishes|date=10 January 2016|website=The Herald|location=Glasgow|accessdate=3 February 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Scotland exported around three and a half times more to the rest of the UK than to the rest of the EU,<ref name=\"SiU\">{{cite web|title=Scotland, 'Brexit' and the UK|url=https://d3n8a8pro7vhmx.cloudfront.net/scotlandinunion/pages/377/attachments/original/1453372484/Brexit_PDF.pdf?1453372484|publisher=Scotland in Union|accessdate=5 July 2016|date=January 2016}}</ref> while in 2015, that had increased to around four times more to the rest of the UK than to the rest of the EU.<ref>{{cite report |author=The Scottish Government|author-link= |authors= |date=25 January 2017|title=Export Statistics Scotland 2015|url=http://www.gov.scot/Resource/0051/00513335.pdf|publisher= |pages=1\u20132|docket= |access-date=5 February 2017|quote= }}</ref> The pro-union organisation Scotland in Union has suggested that an independent Scotland within the EU would face trade barriers with a post-Brexit UK and face additional costs for re-entry to the EU.<ref name=\"SiU\"/>\n\nA report for the [[European Parliament]] regarding the impact on the United Kingdom's exit from the EU on devolution suggested that \"there now seems to be a consensus that, were Scotland to become independent by legal means, it could join the [European] Union\", something which had been questioned before the 2014 referendum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/RegData/etudes/IDAN/2017/583118/IPOL_IDA(2017)583118_EN.pdf|title=The Impact of the United Kingdom's withdrawal from the European Union on Scotland, Wales and Gibraltar|work=Directorate General for Internal Policies|date=September 2017|accessdate=26 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn response to the result, on 24 June 2016, the [[Scottish Government]] said officials would begin planning for a second referendum on independence.<ref name=\"nbcnews\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/25/world/europe/brexit-scotland-independence-referendum.html|title=Scotland Says New Vote on Independence Is 'Highly Likely'|date=25 June 2016|work=The New York Times}}</ref> [[Scottish First Minister]] [[Nicola Sturgeon]] said it was \"clear that the people of Scotland see their future as part of the European Union\" and that Scotland had \"spoken decisively\" with a \"strong, unequivocal\" vote to remain in the European Union.<ref name=\"ft2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/06a90f8c-39c0-11e6-a780-b48ed7b6126f.html#axzz4CRXecPen|title=Scots' backing for Remain raises threat of union's demise|first=Mure|last=Dickie|date=24 June 2016|newspaper=Financial Times}}</ref> Sturgeon said it was \"democratically unacceptable\" that Scotland could be taken out of the EU \"against its will\".<ref name=\"nbcnews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/brexit-referendum/scotland-could-seek-independence-again-after-u-k-brexit-vote-n598166|title='Brexit' Triggers New Bid for Scottish Independence|website=[[NBC News]]|last=Jamieson|first=Alastair|date=24 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC 24 June 2016 Sturgeon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36621030|title=Brexit: Nicola Sturgeon says second Scottish independence vote 'highly likely'|work=BBC News|date=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2017, the Scottish Parliament voted 90 to 34 to oppose the UK leaving the EU and to oppose [[United Kingdom invocation of Article 50 of the Treaty on European Union|invoking Article 50]] in a non-binding vote.<ref name=\"dw17\">[http://www.dw.com/en/scottish-parliament-rejects-brexit-in-non-binding-vote/a-37448650 Scottish parliament rejects Brexit in non-binding vote], ''DW'', 07 February 2017</ref>\n\n===United Kingdom general election, 2017===\n{{Main|United Kingdom general election, 2017 (Scotland)}}\n[[File:2017UKelectionMapScotland.svg|right|300px|thumb|Results of the 2017 United Kingdom general election in Scotland.]]\n\nThe [[2017 United Kingdom general election|2017 UK general election]] returned a [[hung parliament]] resulting in Theresa May's [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservatives]] returning as a minority government through a [[Arrangement between the Conservative Party and the Democratic Unionist Party|pact]] with the [[Democratic Unionist Party]].\n\nThe SNP remained as the third-largest party in the UK [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]] with its representation reduced to 35 of the total 59 Scottish MPs. The SNP had 21 fewer seats than they won in the [[2015 United Kingdom general election|2015 general election]] and its popular vote in Scotland reduced from 50% in 2015 to 37% in 2017 with a lower voter turnout. The Conservatives, who oppose independence, saw their best election in Scotland since 1983, winning 29% of the vote and increasing their seat total to thirteen, compared to one in the previous parliament.\n\nSturgeon stated: \"Undoubtedly the issue of an independence referendum was a factor in this election result, but I think there were other factors in this election result as well\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-40216748|title=General election 2017: Sturgeon says Indyref2 'a factor' in SNP losses|date=9 June 2017|work=BBC}}</ref> Opposition to a second referendum is one of the issues that former SNP MP [[Angus Robertson]] and [[Scottish Conservatives|Scottish Conservative]] leader [[Ruth Davidson]] have attributed to reduced support for the SNP.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/06/08/europe/snp-uk-general-election/index.html|title=Scottish referendum in doubt after steep losses for SNP in UK vote|work=CNN|date=9 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe SNP lost seats that voted for independence. [[Glasgow North East]] was gained by [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] despite consisting mostly of the two Scottish Parliamentary constituencies with the largest support for independence within the [[Glasgow City Council|Glasgow City council area]] \u2013 [[Glasgow Maryhill and Springburn (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Maryhill and Springburn]] and [[Glasgow Provan (Scottish Parliament constituency)|Glasgow Provan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.glasgow.gov.uk/CHttpHandler.ashx?id=22501&p=0|title=Scottish Independence Referendum 2014 \u2013 Glasgow Partial Total|work=Glasgow City Council|date=18 September 2014|accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nA [[Survation]] poll the day prior to the election found that 71% of 2014 independence voters planned to vote for the SNP,<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2017\">{{cite web|url=http://survation.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Final-Daily-Record-Scotland-Poll-070617DCCH-1c0d0h1.pdf|title=Scotland Poll|work=Survation|date=7 June 2017|accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref> significantly lower than the 87% of 'Yes' voters who were planning to vote SNP at a comparable time in 2015.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2015\">{{cite web|url=http://survation.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/Final-Daily-Record-May-Tables-1c6d6h0.pdf|title=Scottish Attitudes Poll May|work=Survation|date=6 May 2015|accessdate=21 March 2018}}</ref> A large amount of support from independence voters had moved to the Labour Party, with the party increasing their vote share among independence supporters from 6% to 21%.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2017\"/><ref name=\"Survation final poll 2015\"/> The Conservatives had a smaller rise among independence supporters, gaining 7% of their votes in 2017, compared to 2% in 2015.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2017\"/><ref name=\"Survation final poll 2015\"/>\n\nA realignment also occurred among those who opposed independence in the 2014 referendum. In 2015, Labour had the highest vote share among unionist voters at 42%.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2015\"/> This dropped to 33% in 2017.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2017\"/> The Conservatives became the largest anti-independence party increasing their votes from 27% to 46% of unionist voters.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2017\"/><ref name=\"Survation final poll 2015\"/> Elsewhere, 11% backed the SNP and the Liberal Democrats in 2017, compared to 15% and 10% respectively in 2015.<ref name=\"Survation final poll 2017\"/><ref name=\"Survation final poll 2015\"/>\n\n=== United Kingdom general election, 2019 ===\n{{Main|2019 United Kingdom general election in Scotland}}\n[[File:2019UKelectionMapScotland.svg|thumb|266x266px|Results of the 2019 UK general election in Scotland]]\nThe [[2019 United Kingdom general election|2019 UK general election]] resulted in a large victory for the Conservatives led by Boris Johnson. The SNP held the position of third largest party in the House of Commons, gaining 13 seats from the previous election to a total of 48. The SNP garnered 45% of the popular vote in Scotland, an 8% gain from the 2017 UK general election.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/election-2019-50766014|title=Scotland election results 2019: SNP wins election landslide in Scotland|last=|first=|date=Dec 13, 2019|work=BBC|access-date=Dec 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Nicola Sturgeon]], leader of the SNP, said: \"It couldn't really be any clearer from the results of this election that Scotland doesn't want a [[Boris Johnson]] government, it doesn't want to leave the European Union, and it wants to be able to determine its own future, whatever that future turns out to be.\"<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/dec/14/sturgeon-scotland-wants-different-future-from-rest-of-uk|title=Sturgeon: Scotland wants different future from rest of UK|last=Gayle|first=Damien|date=Dec 14, 2019|work=The Guardian|access-date=Dec 14, 2019}}</ref> This was in response to the Scottish Conservatives campaign, that, according to Sturgeon, focused solely on opposing a second referendum on Scottish Independence.<ref name=\":1\" /> Given Johnson's opposition to a second referendum, Sturgeon stated the Scottish Government could pursue a legal course of action to try to give the [[Scottish Parliament]] the power to call a referendum.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www-tmp.thenational.scot/news/18073959.sturgeon-take-legal-action-stop-johnson-indyref-block/|title=Sturgeon could take legal action to stop Johnson indyref block|last=Newsdesk|first=National|date=Dec 2, 2019|work=The National|access-date=Dec 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Procedure==\n{{Main|Referendums (Scotland) Act 2020}}\nWhile the Scottish Parliament could potentially hold an ''advisory'' referendum on the question of independence without the approval of the UK government, a ''binding'' referendum would require a section 30 order from the UK government, or an amendment to the Scotland Act 1998 by the UK Parliament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ukconstitutionallaw.org/2017/03/13/stephen-tierney-a-second-independence-referendum-in-scotland-the-legal-issues/|title=Stephen Tierney: A Second Independence Referendum in Scotland: The Legal Issues|first=Constitutional Law|last=Group|date=13 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instituteforgovernment.org.uk/explainers/second-referendum-scottish-independence|title=StackPath|website=www.instituteforgovernment.org.uk}}</ref>\n\n===Referendums Act===\nIn May 2019, the Scottish Government introduced the Referendums Bill to the Scottish Parliament as part of a three-tiered approach to constitutional change. This Bill, when passed, will form the statutory basis for all future referenda being held under Scots Law under the instruction of the Scottish Government.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.parliament.scot/parliamentarybusiness/Bills/111844.aspx|title=Referendums (Scotland) Bill|date=2019-06-14|website=www.parliament.scot|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref> This legislation would form the legal basis of a further independence referendum. The current Scottish Government intends to seek a Section 30 order or an amendment to the Scotland Act 1998 to ensure that the result of a future referendum can be indisputably binding.\n\nThe Bill was passed at Stage 3 by the Scottish Parliament on 19 December 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-50288237|title=MSPs back principles of indyref2 framework bill|website=BBC News|language=en-gb|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref>\n\n===Details===\nThe constitution is a 'reserved' matter of the United Kingdom government under the Scotland Act 1998. For a future referendum on Scottish independence to have a binding outcome, it would need to receive the consent of the British Government through a Section 30 order.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1998/46/contents|title=Scotland Act 1998|last=|first=|date=|website=Legislation.gov.uk|publisher=|access-date=25 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/scottish-independence-sorry-david-cameron-you-cant-prevent-second-referendum-scotland-1513014/|title=Scottish independence: Sorry David Cameron, you can't prevent a second referendum in Scotland|last=Kelly|first=James|date=|website=ibtimes.co.uk|publisher=[[International Business Times]]|access-date=25 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/politics/14580305.Scotland_put_on_stand_by_for_another_independence_referendum_after_Brexit_vote/|title=Scotland put on stand-by for another independence referendum after Brexit vote|last=Gardham|first=Magnus|date=25 June 2016|website=heraldscotland.com|publisher=[[The Herald (Scotland)|The Herald]]|access-date=25 June 2016}}</ref> The Scottish Parliament could approve a \"consultative referendum\" on the subject of independence, which would enable the referendum to take place without the approval of the British Parliament.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.scot/parliamentarybusiness/Bills/19017.aspx|title=Sewel Convention|date=2010-10-15|website=www.parliament.scot|access-date=2016-11-17}}</ref> Under the Sewel Convention, the Scottish Government is able to issue a \"legislative consent motion,\" which would signal to the United Kingdom Parliament that Scottish Government has deemed it necessary to alter a law enacted by the UK Government or to change the scope of the devolved government's powers in some manner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.scot/parliamentarybusiness/CurrentCommittees/52668.aspx|title=Scrutiny of Legislative Consent Memorandum|last=Memoranda|first=Legislative Consent|date=2012-06-28|website=www.parliament.scot|access-date=2016-11-17}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n===2016===\n[[Scottish Secretary]] [[David Mundell]] stated, on 26 June 2016, that \"if the people of Scotland ultimately determine that they want to have another [independence] referendum there will be one\", and added \"Could there be another referendum? The answer to that question is yes. Should there be another referendum? I believe the answer to that question is no.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thecourier.co.uk/fp/news/politics/scottish-politics/213848/second-independence-vote-is-publics-choice-mundell/|title=Scotland put on stand-by for another independence referendum after Brexit vote|last=McPherson|first=Gareth|date=26 June 2016|publisher=DC Thomson |work=[[The Courier (Dundee)|The Courier]]|access-date=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Nicola Sturgeon's -ScotRef announcement.webm|thumb|First Minister Sturgeon delivering her 13 March announcement]]\nOn 13 October 2016, Sturgeon announced that an Independence Referendum Bill will be published for consultation the following week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-37634338|title=SNP's Nicola Sturgeon announces new independence referendum bill|date=13 October 2016|website=bbc.com|publisher=BBC|accessdate=13 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017===\nOn 13 March 2017, Sturgeon announced she would seek Scottish Parliament approval to negotiate with the UK Government for a [[Section 30 of the Scotland Act|Section 30 order]] enabling a legally binding second independence referendum.<ref name=\"13marchscotgov\" />\n\nOn 16 March 2017, ahead of the scheduled debate, Theresa May responded by broadcasting a message where she said that \"now is not the time\" for a second referendum on Scottish independence, as it would be unclear what the people of Scotland would be voting for.<ref name=\"Rejected BBC 16Mar2017\"/> Ruth Davidson later appeared at a press conference in Edinburgh and stated her position that \"we will maintain that it should not take place when there is no clear public and political consent for it to happen\".<ref name=\"Rejected BBC 16Mar2017\" />\n\nThe debate began on 22 March 2017, but following that day's [[2017 Westminster attack|Westminster terrorist attack]], it was suspended before a vote could take place. The vote was subsequently rescheduled for 28 March, a day before Theresa May was scheduled to trigger Article 50.<ref>{{cite news |first= Severin |last=Carrell |url= https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/mar/23/scottish-parliament-postpones-vote-second-independence-referendum |title= Scottish parliament postpones vote on second referendum |work= The Guardian |date= 23 March 2017 |accessdate= 24 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March 2017, the Scottish Parliament voted 69\u201359 on Motion S5M-04710, in favour of holding a second referendum on Scottish independence.<ref name=\"bbc-secondreferendum\">{{cite web|title=Scottish Parliament backs referendum call|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-39422747|website=BBC News|accessdate=28 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.scot/parliamentarybusiness/28877.aspx?SearchType=Advance&ReferenceNumbers=S5M-04710&ResultsPerPage=10|title=Motions, Questions and Answers Search|last=Office|first=Chamber|date=2016-06-16|access-date=2017-03-29}}</ref> Prior to the passage of the motion, a [[Scottish Green Party|Green Party]] amendment was passed, by the same margin, that seeks to enable 16 and 17 year-olds and EU citizens the opportunity to vote in a referendum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.scot/parliamentarybusiness/28877.aspx?SearchType=Advance&ReferenceNumbers=S5M-04710.5&ResultsPerPage=10|title=Motions, Questions and Answers Search|last=Office|first=Chamber|date=2016-06-16|access-date=2017-04-03}}</ref>\n\nThe full-motion, with the Green Party amendment in italics:\n\n<blockquote>That the Parliament acknowledges the sovereign right of the Scottish people to determine the form of government best suited to their needs and therefore mandates the Scottish Government to take forward discussions with the UK Government on the details of an order under section 30 of the Scotland Act 1998 to ensure that the Scottish Parliament can legislate for a referendum to be held that will give the people of Scotland a choice over the future direction and governance of their country at a time, and with a question and franchise, determined by the Scottish Parliament, which would most appropriately be between the autumn of 2018, when there is clarity over the outcome of the Brexit negotiations, and around the point at which the UK leaves the EU in spring 2019''; believes that this gives people in Scotland a choice at a time when there is both the most information and most opportunity to act; further believes that 16 and 17-year-olds and EU citizens, who were excluded from the EU referendum, should be entitled to vote, and considers that this referendum is necessary given the Prime Minister\u2019s decision to negotiate a hard exit from the EU, including leaving the single market, which conflicts with assurances given by the UK Government and prominent Leave campaigners, and which takes no account of the overwhelming Remain vote in Scotland.''</blockquote>\n\nFollowing the 2017 UK general election, Sturgeon announced that the Scottish Government would postpone legislation on the proposed second referendum on Scottish independence until at least autumn 2018, when it was believed that the outcome of Brexit negotiations would become clearer.<ref name=NicolaDelays>{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-40415457 |title= Nicola Sturgeon puts Scottish independence referendum bill on hold|work=[[BBC]]|date= 27 June 2017 |accessdate= 27 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n===2018===\nOn 25 May 2018, the Scottish National Party published its \"Growth Commission\" report, which detailed the economics of an independent Scotland when maintaining close alignment to British fiscal policy. The report noted that it would take \u00a3450 million to set up an independent state, with an initial budget deficit of around 6% of GDP. The report, additionally, suggested that an independent Scotland would negotiate a share of the UK national debt, while continuing to use the [[Pound Sterling]] as currency for at least a decade. Scotland would only consider an independent currency, once certain economic goals had been met. Despite not having a separate currency on independence, the report suggested that Scotland would set up a central bank to act as a lender of last resort. According to the Growth Commission, Scotland would seek an open migration policy to allow for its population to grow.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-44237956|title=What's in the SNP's growth commission report?|work=BBC News|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nScottish Conservative leader Ruth Davidson responded to the report by saying: \"For me, the most important issue is making sure our children get a good education. The first minister used to claim that that was her priority too\u2014how times have changed. It's hard to see how dragging Scotland back down the rabbit hole of a debate on independence is going to improve our schools.\" Richard Leonard, Scottish Labour's leader, stated that the report, \"will exasperate millions of people around the country who just want the first minister focused on public services\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-44224884|title=Scotland 'can match top small countries'|work=BBC News|date=24 May 2018|accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2019===\nIn March 2019, the SNP conference adopted an amendment version of the Growth Commission as party policy on the economics of independence.  This amended version established that it is now SNP policy for an independent Scotland to create a new currency at the earliest feasible point of independence to enable fiscal sovereignty, with Pound Sterling being a transitional currency for Scotland.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-48069470|title=SNP members change leadership's currency plan|date=2019-04-27|access-date=2019-06-16|language=en-GB}}</ref> First Minister Sturgeon also announced the establishment of a 'Social Justice Commission' to develop the social argument for independence to complement the SNP's new economic policy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/bbf70b34-69c7-11e9-80c7-60ee53e6681d|title=Subscribe to read|website=Financial Times|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2019, Sturgeon proposed holding a second referendum before the end of the Scottish Parliamentary session in May 2021.<ref name=\"Sturgeon 2019\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-48026430 |title=Scottish independence: Sturgeon wants indyref2 by 2021 |work=BBC|date= 24 April 2019 |accessdate=24 April 2019}}</ref> Legislation has been introduced in the form of the 'Referendums (Scotland) Bill' to govern future referenda, on any subject, in Scotland held by the Scottish Government. The Scottish Government is working on a three-pronged approach to constitutional change:\n\n*Firstly, a referendum on independence through the Referendums (Scotland) Bill is a matter of intent of the government to allow Scotland a say on independence.\n*Secondly, cross-party talks are to be held to enable any areas of agreement on changes to devolution to be explored.\n*Lastly, the Scottish Government is establishing the [[Citizens' Assembly of Scotland]] to discuss the most prominent issues faced by contemporary Scottish governance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gapi.io/6OUb|title=Citizens' Assembly of Scotland|website=Scottish Government News|language=english|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref>\n\nThe civic campaign group [[Voices for Scotland]] launched in April 2019 to secure a pro-independence majority in Scotland through societal engagement. This group was established by the [[Scottish Independence Convention]] which is made up of cross-party and grassroots organisations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/indyref2-campaign-group-launches-with-elaine-c-smith-on-board-1-4914657|title=Indyref2: Campaign group launches with Elaine C Smith on board|website=www.scotsman.com|language=en|access-date=2019-06-16}}</ref>\n\nOn the same day as the passing of the [[Referendums (Scotland) Act 2019]], Nicola Sturgeon officially published the Scottish Government's request to Prime Minister [[Boris Johnson]] for the transfer of legal authority to hold a referendum on independence. This request set out the constitutional history of Scotland's place in the United Kingdom and that the Scottish Government would deem either a Section 30 order or an amendment to the Scotland Act as a satisfactory means of transferring the power over independence referendums.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.scot/publications/scotlands-right-choose-putting-scotlands-future-scotlands-hands/|title=Scotland's right to choose: putting Scotland's future in Scotland's hands - gov.scot|website=www.gov.scot|access-date=2019-12-27}}</ref> Sturgeon's intention is for the referendum to be held in 2020.<ref name=\"for 2020\">{{cite news |first= Libby |last=Brooks |url= https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/15/nicola-sturgeon-to-demand-powers-for-2020-referendum |title= Nicola Sturgeon to demand powers for 2020 referendum |work= The Guardian |date= 15 October 2019 |accessdate= 31 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2020===\nSturgeon's 2019 request was rejected by the UK government in January 2020.<ref name=\"bbc2020\">{{cite web|title=Scottish independence: Johnson rejects Sturgeon's indyref2 demand|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-51106796|website=BBC News|accessdate=14 January 2020}}</ref> In his official response, Johnson wrote that Sturgeon and Salmond had promised that the 2014 referendum would be a \"once in a generation\" vote, that both the Scottish and UK governments had pledged to implement the outcome of that vote, and that his government therefore \"cannot agree to any request for a transfer of power that would lead to further independence referendums\".<ref name=\"bbc2020\" />\n\nThe Scottish Parliament passed a motion introduced by the Scottish Government on 29 January 2020 to endorse a new referendum on independence. The motion was carried 64 votes to 54.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://inews.co.uk/news/scotland/scottish-parliament-independence-indyref2-vote-rebuffed-1379613|title=Scottish Parliament backs indyref2 this year \u2014 but is swiftly rebuffed|website=inews.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> This was on the same day that the Parliament resolved to continue flying the [[Flag of Europe]] after the UK's withdrawal from the European Union.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/brexit-msps-vote-to-keep-flying-eu-flag-at-scottish-parliament-after-heated-debate-1-5082706|title=Brexit: MSPs vote to keep flying EU flag at Scottish Parliament after heated debate|website=www.scotsman.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\n== Issues ==\n===Scotland's future relations with the EU and EEA===\n{{Brexit sidebar}}\n[[File:United Kingdom EU referendum 2016 area results.svg|thumb|The results of the [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum|European Union membership referendum]] by voting areas. Scotland, [[Northern Ireland]], [[London]], and [[Gibraltar]] voted in majority to remain in the [[European Union]], contrasting with Wales and the rest of England, who ultimately carried the result of [[United Kingdom withdrawal from the European Union|leaving]].<br />{{legend|#0069b5|Leave}} {{legend|#ffc010|Remain}}]]\nFollowing the EU referendum result, Sturgeon said she would communicate to all EU member states that Scotland had voted to stay in the EU.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/live/2016/jun/23/eu-referendum-result-live-counting-leave-remain-brain-in-europe|title=Nicola Sturgeon says second Scottish referendum 'highly likely' \u2013 as it happened|date=24 June 2016|newspaper=The Guardian}}</ref> An emergency Scottish cabinet meeting on 25 June 2016 agreed that the Scottish Government would seek to enter negotiations with the EU and its member states, to explore \"options to protect Scotland's place in the EU\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jun/25/sturgeon-seeks-urgent-brussels-talks-to-protect-scotlands-eu-membership|title=Sturgeon to lobby EU members to support Scotland's bid to remain|first1=Severin|last1=Carrell|first2=Jennifer|last2=Rankin|date=25 June 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"stv250616\">{{cite web |url=http://stv.tv/news/politics/1358598-sturgeon-to-seek-eu-talks-to-protect-scotland-s-memebrship/ |title=Sturgeon to seek EU talks to 'protect' Scotland's membership |first=Aidan |last=Kerr |work=STV News |publisher=STV |date=25 June 2016 |accessdate=27 June 2016}}</ref> On 28 June 2016, Sturgeon said that \"independence [...] is not my starting point in these discussions. My starting point is to protect our relationship with the EU.\"<ref>{{cite news |author=Press Association<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Nicola Sturgeon says independence vote would be proposed 'if best or only way to protect EU place'|url=https://www.thecourier.co.uk/fp/news/politics/scottish-politics/215192/nicola-sturgeon-says-independence-vote-proposed-best-way-protect-eu-place/ |newspaper=The Courier |location=Dundee, Scotland |date=28 June 2016 |access-date=28 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nAfter a summit of EU leaders on 29 June 2016, Sturgeon held meetings with some EU officials.<ref name = \"greenland\"/> She raised the possibility of parts of the UK remaining within the EU, or for these areas to have special arrangements with the EU, after the UK leaves.<ref name = \"greenland\">{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-scotland-greenland-idUSKCN0ZJ08R |title='Reverse Greenland', anyone? Scots eye post-Brexit EU options |work=Reuters |first1=Alastair |last1=MacDonald |first2=Elisabeth |last2=O'Leary |date=3 July 2016 |accessdate=4 July 2016}}</ref> [[David Edward]], a former justice of the [[European Court of Justice]], suggested that these arrangements would relate to policy areas that have been devolved to Scotland.<ref name = \"greenland\"/>\n\nSturgeon also met European Commission president [[Jean-Claude Juncker]], who commented that \"I will listen carefully to what the first minister will tell me... but we don't have the intention, neither [[Donald Tusk]] nor myself, to interfere in an inner British process that is not our duty and this is not our job.\"<ref name = \"rajoy2906\"/> [[Manfred Weber]], leader of the [[European People's Party Group]], and [[Guy Verhofstadt]], leader of the [[Alliance of Liberals and Democrats for Europe Group]], indicated that they were supportive of Scotland remaining an EU member.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/fastft/2016/06/24/scotland-n-ireland-can-stay-in-eu-says-merkel-ally/|title=Fast FT|first=FT|last=Membership|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet |user=GuyVerhofstadt |number= 746302049927708672|date= 24 June 2016|title= It's wrong that Scotland might be taken out of EU, when it voted to stay. Happy to discuss w. @NicolaSturgeon next time she's in Bxl. #EUref|author=Guy Verhofstadt |author-link= Guy Verhofstadt}}</ref><ref name=\"Herald Scotland 26-6-16\">{{cite web | title=EU leaders tell UK 'hurry up and leave' | website=Herald Scotland | url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/news/homenews/14580576.EU_leaders_tell_UK___39_hurry_up_and_leave__39_/ | accessdate=26 June 2016 | quote=Guy Verhofstadt, highlighted Scotland's case to remain, saying that it was \"wrong\" that the country faced being pulled out of the EU despite 62 per cent of the population voting to remain}}</ref> [[Gunther Krichbaum]], head of the Bundestag's Committee for EU Affairs, made supportive comments about Scotland becoming a member state of the EU.<ref>{{cite web|last=Carrel|first=Paul|title=Scotland welcome to join EU, Merkel ally says|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-eu-scotland-germany-idUSKCN0ZC0QT|website=Reuters.com|date=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Prime Minister of Spain|Spanish Prime Minister]] [[Mariano Rajoy]] said: \"[be] very clear Scotland does not have the competence to negotiate with the European Union\".<ref name = \"rajoy2906\"/> He also stated his opposition to the EU negotiating with \"anyone other than the government of United Kingdom\" and that \"if the United Kingdom leaves... Scotland leaves\".<ref name = \"rajoy2906\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36656980 |title=Brexit: Spain and France oppose Scotland EU talks |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=29 June 2016 |accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref> Similarly, the [[President of France|French President]], [[Fran\u00e7ois Hollande]], stated: \"The negotiations will be conducted with the United Kingdom, not with a part of the United Kingdom\".<ref name = \"rajoy2906\"/>\n\nThe Scottish European and External Affairs Committee held an evidence session on 30 June 2016, asking a panel of four experts (Dr Kirsty Hughes of [[Friends of Europe]], Prof Sionaidh Douglas-Scott of the Queen Mary School of Law at the [[University of London]], Sir David Edward and Prof Drew Scott of the [[University of Edinburgh]]) what they felt was the best way to secure the Scottish-EU relationship.<ref name = \"experts\"/> Hughes stated that \"the simplest and most obvious way would be to be an independent state and transition in and stay in the EU\", Douglas-Scott said that \"Legally there are precedents. [...] But there were also political difficulties\", referring to [[Catalonia]] in member state Spain. Edward believed \"Scotland makes quite a good fit with Iceland and Norway\", referring to the [[European Economic Area]] and the [[European Free Trade Association]], while Scott hinted that Scotland could be a successor state, meaning the rest of the UK would leave but Scotland would retain its seat.<ref name = \"experts\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36673126 |title=Brexit: Scottish independence 'simplest EU option' |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=30 June 2016 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe new UK Prime Minister [[Theresa May]] met with Sturgeon on 15 July 2016 in [[Edinburgh]], when May stated that she was \"willing to listen to options\" for Scotland,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36800536 |title=Brexit: PM is 'willing to listen to options' on Scotland  |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=15 July 2016 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> although she later stated that some options were \"impracticable\".<ref name = \"ippr\"/> Sturgeon then publicly stated that she had five tests for any future arrangements.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36878081 |title=Brexit: Sturgeon sets out key Scottish interests that 'must be protected' |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=25 July 2016 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> The [[IPPR]] thinktank stated that [[Unionism in Scotland|Scottish unionists]] needed to provide options for Scotland, if they wished to retain the British union.<ref name = \"ippr\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-36877869 |title=Think tank says unionists must offer Scotland EU options |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=24 July 2016 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> The [[Scottish Labour Party]] published an 'Action Plan' in July 2016, focusing on the economy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-36897565 |title=Scottish Labour publish Brexit economy 'action plan' |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=27 July 2016 |accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn their manifestos for the [[2017 German federal election]], the [[Free Democratic Party (Germany)|Free Democrats]] and the [[Alliance 90/The Greens|Greens]] stated that EU membership would remain an option for Scotland and Northern Ireland (as well as for the rest of the UK), if they left the UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-08-30/german-parties-snub-u-k-to-back-scotland-s-push-to-defy-brexit |title=German Parties Snub U.K. to Back Scotland's Push to Defy Brexit |first=Alan |last=Crawford |work=Bloomberg |publisher= |date=30 August 2017 |accessdate=31 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, a report for the [[European Parliament Committee on Constitutional Affairs]] was published to look at the implications on the UK's withdrawal from the European Union on Scotland, Wales and Gibraltar and their future relations with the EU. The report suggested that Scotland would be unlikely to be rejected as a member of the EU, should it become independent, noting that \"not since [[Charles de Gaulle|de Gaulle\u2019s]] veto on UK membership in the 1960s has a democratic country respecting the rule of law been refused admission\". However, it affirmed that Scotland's independence would have to be accepted by the United Kingdom for Scotland to obtain EU membership: \"There now seems to be a consensus that, were Scotland to become independent by legal means, it could join the [European] Union\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/RegData/etudes/IDAN/2017/583118/IPOL_IDA%282017%29583118_EN.pdf|title=The Impact of the United Kingdom's withdrawal from the European Union on Scotland, Wales and Gibraltar|first=Michael|last=Keating|publisher=[[European Parliament]]|date=April 2017|accessdate=6 December 2018|page=19}}</ref>\n\n====Possible EFTA membership====\nIn November 2016, Sturgeon confirmed to members of the Scottish Parliament that the Scottish Government was considering joining the [[European Free Trade Association]] (EFTA) and the [[European Economic Area]] (EEA), based on the model of [[Norway]] and some other countries, to \"protect [Scotland's] place in the single market\" of Europe even if the United Kingdom as a whole does leave in a \"hard [[Brexit]]\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-37993028|title=Nicola Sturgeon confirms 'Norway model' option|date=2016-11-16|newspaper=BBC News|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-11-17}}</ref> The SNP's 2017 General Election manifesto stated that \"the Scottish Government [led by the SNP, had] published proposals that would keep Scotland in the Single Market, even as we left the EU.\"<ref>''Scottish National Party Manifesto 2017''. p. 8.</ref> Christophe Hillion, a Professor of European Law at the [[University of Oslo]] who was invited to deliver an expert opinion to the Scottish Parliament, said that while there is scepticism about UK accession to EFTA in Norway, Scotland is viewed much more positively, and that the EFTA member states would likely welcome an independent Scotland as a member.<ref name=\"thenat\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenational.scot/news/16097931.eea-likely-to-welcome-an-independent-scotland/|title=EEA 'likely to welcome' an independent Scotland|date=2018-03-20|work=The National}}</ref>\n\n===Legislative consent in disapplying EU law===\nThe [[Scotland Act 1998]] empowers the [[Scottish Parliament]] to legislate in policy areas devolved to Scotland, but one of its clauses obliges the Scottish Parliament to ensure its legislation is compatible with European law.<ref name=\"taylor 260616\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-36635012|title=Could the Scottish Parliament stop the UK from leaving the EU?|last=Taylor|first=Brian|date=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC|work=BBC News|accessdate=27 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Renwick\">{{cite news|url=http://europe.newsweek.com/could-scotland-really-veto-brexit-474963|title=Could Scotland Really Veto Brexit?|last=Renwick|first=Alan|date=27 June 2016|work=Newsweek|publisher=|accessdate=28 June 2016}}</ref> For the UK to completely leave the EU, it would need to remove that obligation.<ref name=\"Renwick\" /> If the UK Parliament wishes to legislate on policy areas devolved to Scotland, or if it wishes to amend the powers devolved to Scotland, by convention it needs the Scottish Parliament to pass a \"[[legislative consent motion]]\".<ref name=\"taylor 260616\" /><ref name=\"Renwick\" /> On 26 June 2016, Sturgeon said she would ask the Scottish Parliament to withhold consent if she thought it was not in Scotland's interests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-36633371|title=Nicola Sturgeon: Scotland could veto Brexit|date=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC|work=BBC News}}</ref> Giving evidence to a House of Lords committee before the EU referendum, [[David Edward]] suggested the consent of the Scottish Parliament would be needed for this legislation.<ref name=\"taylor 260616\" />\n\nMedia reports suggested this might give the Scottish Parliament a veto over UK withdrawal from the EU,<ref name=\"taylor 260616\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/scotland/holyrood-may-exercise-veto-m93tgd3b6|title=Holyrood may exercise veto|last=Allardyce|first=Jason|date=26 June 2016|work=The Times}}</ref><ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/2016/6/25/12031254/no-brexit-article-50|title=\"Bracksies\": how Brexit could wind up not actually happening|last=Matthews|first=Dylan|date=25 June 2016|website=vox.com}}</ref> but under the Scotland Act 1998 the UK Parliament could ultimately override the \"veto\" as it is based only on parliamentary convention.<ref name=\"taylor 260616\" /><ref name=\"Renwick\" /> Alternatively, the UK Parliament could choose to disregard the obligation for the Scottish Parliament to observe EU law.<ref name=\"Renwick\" /> The then Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, [[Theresa Villiers]], said that the UK Government would consult with the devolved governments and noted that it was for the UK Parliament to decide whether to leave the EU by repealing the [[European Communities Act 1972 (UK)|European Communities Act 1972]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-northern-ireland-36633939|title=EU referendum: Theresa Villiers says parliament sovereign|date=26 June 2016|publisher=BBC|work=BBC News|accessdate=27 June 2016}}</ref> In its ruling in the [[R (Miller) v Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union|case]] brought by [[Gina Miller]] regarding the UK Government's authority to invoke Article 50, the [[UK Supreme Court]] unanimously ruled that the devolved governments did not have a veto as the convention was unenforceable in law.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38721650|title=Supreme Court Brexit ruling: What happens next?|date=25 January 2017|publisher=BBC|work=BBC News|accessdate=28 January 2017}}</ref> Speaking later that week the Secretary of State for Scotland, [[David Mundell]], said that the bill needed to invoke Article 50 would not require consent, but also said he was working under the assumption that the \"Great Repeal Bill\" needed to remove European legislation from UK statutes would require co-operation from the devolved bodies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-38757264|title=Mundell: Holyrood to be consulted on Great Repeal Bill|date=26 January 2017|publisher=BBC|work=BBC News|accessdate=28 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Responses to the prospect of a referendum==\n:''See also, for comparison [[2014 Scottish independence referendum#Responses]]''\nResponses by politicians to the possibility of a second referendum have been pro-independence (and pro-referendum), pro-union, or pro-federalism.\n\n====In support of a referendum====\n\nScottish Greens co-convener [[Patrick Harvie]], on 13 March 2017 welcomed the confirmation from the First Minister that she is seeking a Section 30 Order from the UK Government to give the Scottish Parliament temporary power to call a referendum on independence.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://greens.scot/news/greens-welcome-referendum-call|title=Greens Welcome Referendum Call|date=2017-03-13|work=Scottish Greens|access-date=2017-03-13|language=en}}</ref> This was re-affirmed in the Scottish Parliament on 29 January 2020 when the Greens voted with the government for a referendum to be held.\n\n[[Scottish Socialist Party]] spokesman [[Colin Fox (political activist)|Colin Fox]] said the SSP would \"work as hard as anyone to deliver a Yes vote for independence\", but warned that making Scotland's EU membership a central and \u201coverarching\u201d issue of the debate would be \u201ca risky strategy\u201d and said it ran the risk of side-lining economic and social challenges facing Scots.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thenational.scot/news/15153561.Pro_independence_parties_throw_their_weight_behind_ScotRef_decision/|title=Pro-independence parties throw their weight behind ScotRef decision|date=14 March 2017|accessdate=14 March 2017|publisher=The National}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/03/13/nicola-sturgeon-could-derail-brexit-scottish-referendum-demand/|title=Theresa May rules out Nicola Sturgeon's plans for a new Scottish independence referendum before Brexit, as Lords pass landmark Brexit bill following MPs' vote|date=13 March 2017|accessdate=14 March 2017|newspaper=The Telegraph}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Scottish Independence Convention]] backs calls for a referendum. As a result, the Convention established [[Voices for Scotland]] as a civic campaign for independence based on conversations and discussions of what Scotland could look like. <ref>{{cite news |url=https://bellacaledonia.org.uk/2018/09/18/announcing-a-new-national-campaign/ |title=Announcing a New National Campaign |first=Robin |last=McAlpine |work=Bella Caledonia |publisher=Bella Caledonia |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.commonspace.scot/articles/13296/new-campaign-organisation-aims-take-independence-movement-next-level |title=New campaign organisation aims to take independence movement 'to the next level' |first=Sean |last=Bell|work=CommonSpace |publisher=CommonSpace |date=18 September 2018 |accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nA few days before the 2017 General Election, Sturgeon was asked about the prospect of a third referendum if the proposed second one did not result in a vote in favour of independence.<ref name=\"PandJ\">{{cite news|url=https://www.pressandjournal.co.uk/fp/news/politics/westminster/general-election/1261080/nicola-sturgeon-jeered-refusing-rule-third-independence-referendum-within-years/|title=Nicola Sturgeon jeered after refusing to rule out third independence referendum within a few years|date=6 June 2017|accessdate=6 June 2017|newspaper=The Press and Journal}}</ref> She refused to rule out a third referendum within a few years, saying that, \"I don't think it's right for any politician to dictate to a country what its future should be. I think that should be a choice for the people of Scotland.\"<ref name=\"PandJ\" />\n\nAlison Evison, President of the [[Convention of Scottish Local Authorities]] (COSLA) and [[Scottish Labour]] councillor for Aberdeenshire has stated her support for a referendum on independence, stating \"We can strengthen it [democracy] by enabling the voice of Scotland to be heard through its formal processes and that must mean a referendum on independence\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundaypost.com/fp/labour-councillor-and-cosla-president-calls-for-second-independence-referendum/|title=Labour councillor and Cosla president calls for second independence referendum|last=Post|first=The Sunday|website=Sunday Post|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\nFormer First Minister [[Alex Salmond]] has shown support for a further independence referendum, claiming it is inevitable but only after what he predicts will be the \u2018humiliation\u2019 of Brexit becomes apparent for a clear choice to be made.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/alex-salmond-scottish-independence-indyref-brexit-humiliation-snp-a7887236.html|title=Alex Salmond calls for second independence referendum after Brexit 'humiliation'|date=2017-08-10|website=The Independent|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\n====Opposed to a referendum====\n\n=====British party leaders=====\nIn November 2019 during the lead up to the [[2019 United Kingdom general election|UK general election]], leader of the Conservatives and Prime Minister [[Boris Johnson]] stated that a conservative government would not permit a second independence referendum, vowing to \"protect our magnificent union\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/news/newsscotland/boris-johnson-wont-give-scots-a-second-independence-referendum/ar-BBXlKhO|title=Boris Johnson won't give Scots a second independence referendum|last=Bussey|first=Katrine|date=Nov 26, 2019|work=MSN|access-date=Dec 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\nFormer Labour Party leader [[Jeremy Corbyn]] said in March 2017 that a referendum would be \"absolutely fine\" and that \"I don't think it's the job of Westminster or the Labour Party to prevent people holding referenda.\" However, a spokesman for Corbyn later said: \"Labour continues to oppose a further referendum in the Scottish Parliament and would campaign against independence if one were held.\"<ref name=\"BBC News Corbyn 2017\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-39244890|title=Scottish independence: Jeremy Corbyn says indyref2 'absolutely fine'|date=11 March 2017|website=BBC News|accessdate=13 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nFormer [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]] leader [[Tim Farron]] in March 2017, said: \u201cScottish Liberal Democrats stood for election last year on a platform to oppose a new independence referendum. That is what we will do.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.libdems.org.uk/scottish_liberal_democrats_will_oppose_second_referendum|title=Scottish Liberal Democrats will oppose second referendum|last=http://www.libdems.org.uk/|date=2017-03-13|work=Liberal Democrats|access-date=2017-03-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\nA spokesperson speaking on behalf of Cameron's successor as Conservative Party Leader and Prime Minister, [[Theresa May]], said in October 2016: \"The prime minister and the government does not believe that there is a mandate for [a second referendum]. There was one only two years ago. There was an extremely high turnout and there was a resounding result in favour of Scotland remaining in the UK.\"<ref name=\"bbc.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-37708545|title=New Scottish independence bill published|date=20 October 2016|work=BBC}}</ref>\n\n=====Scottish party leaders=====\nInterim [[Scottish Conservatives|Scottish Conservative]] leader [[Jackson Carlaw]] has stated his opposition to a referendum. He has said; \"We will not support another independence referendum for a generation.\" and that the Scottish Government should focus on its domestic agenda. He has stated that 40 years is what he sees as the time needed between referenda.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/election-2019-50588843|title=General election 2019: Jackson Carlaw answers your questions on the election|website=BBC News|language=en-gb|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\n[[Scottish Labour]] leader [[Richard Leonard (Scottish politician)|Richard Leonard]] is against a referendum on independence. He has stated that Scotland should seek a new devolution settlement rather than becoming an independent country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/opinion/columnists/why-it-s-time-for-home-rule-for-scotland-richard-leonard-1-5081354|title=Why it's time for Home Rule for Scotland \u2013 Richard Leonard|website=www.scotsman.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> However, Leonard has said that [[UK Labour Party]] policy on independence and a referendum should be decided by the Scottish branch of the party rather than by the whole UK party. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/en-gb/news/newsscotland/richard-leonard-tells-labour-chiefs-scottish-party-will-decide-indyref2-position/ar-BBZ4PkQ|title=Richard Leonard tells Labour chiefs Scottish party will decide IndyRef2 position|website=www.msn.com|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref>\n\n[[Scottish Liberal Democrats]] leader [[Willie Rennie]] said in March 2017, \"We stood on a platform last May where we said we were against independence and against another independence referendum\",<ref name=\"MACMAHON 2017\">{{cite web | title=Rennie: My MPs will vote to block indyref2 | website=ITV News | date=11 March 2017 | url=http://www.itv.com/news/border/2017-03-11/rennie-my-mps-will-block-indyref2/ | accessdate=2 April 2017 | last=MACMAHON | first=PETER}}</ref> he also said, \"No independence referendum, either at Westminster or in the Scottish Parliament \u2013 that's the view of the Liberal Democrats.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-39248104|title=Willie Rennie wants Scottish independence poll blocked|date=2017-03-12|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-03-17|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Opinion polling==\n{{see also|Opinion polling on Scottish independence|Scottish Independence#Public opinion|Opinion polling for the Scottish independence referendum, 2014}}\n[[File:IndependentScotland.png|thumb|440x440px|Results of polls to 31 January 2020]]\nIn nearly every opinion poll following the EU membership referendum, participants are asked to respond to the question or subtle variation of:\n\n<blockquote>If the referendum was held again tomorrow, how would you vote in response to the question: ''Should Scotland be an independent country?''</blockquote>\n\nutilising the final six words (in italics) as in the 2014 referendum question. A response of \"Yes\" therefore is for Scottish independence and response of \"No\" for remaining in the United Kingdom.\n\nPolls vary in how weightings are applied (methods of which are not described by the polling organisations) and in which participants are excluded from the final data (based on how likely they are to vote). There is an inherent \u00b1 3% [[margin of error]] based on a sample size of ~1,000.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 14px; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Date(s)<br />conducted\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Polling\nMethod\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Includes 16 and 17 year-olds?\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Polling organisation/client\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Sample size\n!Yes \n!No\n!Undecided\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Lead\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Notes\n|-\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"background: rgb(0, 129, 66); width: 100px; color: white;\" | !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"background: rgb(220, 36, 31); width: 100px; color: white;\" | !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"background: gray; width: 90px; color: white;\" | \n|-\n|data-sort-value=\"2020-03-26\" |24&ndash;26 Mar 2020\n|Online \n|Yes\n|[https://www.drg.global/wp-content/uplo